title: imperial chicken
directions: Grate loaf of bread into fine crumbs.
Dry overnight.
Mix crumbs with grated cheese; add garlic salt.
Dip salted chicken into melted butter.
Roll in crumbs.
Bake one hour at 350° until fork-tender.

title: apple crisp
directions: Slice apples in greased baking dish.
Mix together dry ingredients and margarine.
Press on top of apples.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serve warm with ice cream or whipped cream.

title: marinated carrots(serves 12 to 15)
directions: Peel carrots.
Cook until tender; cool and slice.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well; refrigerate overnight.
Will keep for a long time.

title: jesus' enchiladas
directions: Utensils:
Large frypan and a large cookie sheet.

title: crockpot ground beef chili
directions: In a large frying pan, cook meat, onion, and green pepper until meat is not pink. Put into a Pam-sprayed 6 quart crockpot. Combine tomato puree, salsa, tomatoes, broth, and water. Add seasonings to liquid and mix. Mix into meat mixture in crockpot. Cook on high for 4 hours or low for 8 hours. Add kidney beans last twenty minutes of cook time.

title: swedish pineapple cake
directions: Stir the ingredients in the order listed.
Do not drain pineapple or mix with a mixer.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Pour mixture in an ungreased baking pan (9 x 13-inch).
Bake 35 to 40 minutes.

title: ready to eat pickle salad
directions: Slice cukes in bowl.
Add onions.
Sprinkle salt and celery seed over them.
Bring sugar and vinegar to a boil.
Turn off heat; let cool, then pour over cukes.
Stir well.
Add green pepper.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
These are more tasty after the second day, also crisper.

title: mom's meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease loaf pan lightly.
Melt butter and saute onion.
Combine meat and all other ingredients.
Add sauteed onions.
Dust top of meat loaf with cornflake crumbs. Bake 1 hour.
Broil last 5 minutes.
Let sit 10 minutes before slicing.

title: tylene's oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream sugars and oleo or butter.
Add eggs, cold water and vanilla.
Stir in dry ingredients, then add oatmeal.
Drop by teaspoons onto ungreased pan.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 375°.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Place first five ingredients into large mixing bowl. Beat on high speed for 20 minutes to form stiff peaks, don't underbeat. Fold in Cool Whip. Spoon mixture over crumbs; top with remaining crumbs.

title: dessert pizza
directions: Spread sugar cookie dough onto pizza pan and bake at 375 degrees for 12-15 minutes.
Let cool.
Combine cream cheese, sour cream, sugar, and almond extract.
Mix well.
Spread over cookie. Arrange fruit.

title: chicken delight
directions: Cover bottom of shallow 2-quart glass baking dish with dried beef. Wrap each chicken breast with slice of bacon and secure with toothpick. Combine
sour cream and soup.
Pour over chicken breasts which have been place on beef in a single layer.
Bake, uncovered, at 250° for 3 1/2 hours or 2 1/2 hours at 325°. Serve over rice.

title: rolled apple pie
directions: Melt the margarine in a long baking dish. Mix the flour, Crisco and milk. Roll in a ball and then roll out thin. Spread the apples on dough. Generously sprinkle with apple pie spice. Roll up in a long roll (jelly-type roll) and cut into slices about 1/2 to 3/4-inch and place in dish with margarine, apple side up.

title: punch
directions: Combine ingredients.
Stir well to dissolve sugar.
Freeze in wide-mouth container.

title: corn dogs
directions: Combine all ingredients except hot dogs.
Roll and dip hot dogs in batter and fry in hot oil until golden brown.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan, place one layer of crackers.
Mix pudding with 3 cups milk.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Spread 1/2 pudding mixture over crackers in pan.
Place another layer of crackers over pudding.
Spread last 1/2 of pudding mixture over crackers. Top with one last layer of grahams.
Top with chocolate frosting. Refrigerate.
Tasty and simple!

title: biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients together, roll into biscuits.
Bake at 400° on a cookie sheet for about 12 mins.

title: sour cream coconut cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed, using real butter and 8-inch cake pans. When completely cool, split layers, making 4 layers.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream or mix well shortening, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Mix well.
Drop on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes.
This is a soft cookie.
Ice, if desired.

title: cheesy apple crisp
directions: Peel and slice apples.
Arrange apples in four greased 13 x 9 x 2 inch baking pans.
Combine water and lemon juice, sprinkle over apples.
Combine flour, sugar, cinnamon, and salt; cut in butter until crumbly.
Stir in cheese lightly.
Spread over apples.
Bake at 350° for 30 - 35 minutes or until apples are tender and topping is crisp.
Served with shipped cream or ice cream.
Yield:
100 servings.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Place 3 teaspoons per cup of hot water. This is a nice change from hot chocolate on a cold day.

title: pecan pie
directions: In a large bowl, stir the egg, syrup, sugar, margarine and vanilla.
Put in a 10-inch crust or tart shells. Bake about 35 minutes or until done.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into 9-inch square pan. Bake at 425° until golden brown.

title: truffles
directions: In a double boiler, melt chocolate over medium heat.
Stir in milk, vanilla and salt until well mixed.
Refrigerate 45 minutes.

title: zucchini muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease muffin tins lightly with oil. Mix dry ingredients thoroughly.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Add to dry ingredients.
Stir until dry ingredients are barely moistened.
Batter will be lumpy.
Fill muffin tins 2/3 full. Bake until lightly browned, about 20 minutes.
Yield:
12 muffins.

title: greek pizza
directions: Mix all ingredients (except muffins).
Spread on muffin halves.
Cut into quarters.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: barbecue beef
directions: Brown meat and chili powder.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer 2 to 3 hours, stirring occasionally.

title: "trees" casserole
directions: Layer items in casserole dish; top with grated cheese, then bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: chinese hamburg
directions: Saute onions, celery and pepper.
Add hamburger meat and brown, draining off fat.
Add undiluted soup, vegetables, and if desired, water chestnuts and mushrooms.
Sprinkle with soy sauce (2 tablespoons) and garlic salt.
Heat thoroughly and serve over rice, thinning with a little water or sherry, if necessary.

title: standard two-egg cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs and dry ingredients alternately with milk, a small amount at a time.
Beat and add vanilla.
Pour into 2 x 9-inch layers pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Makes about 18 to 20 cupcakes.

title: weight watchers turkey dish
directions: Brown meat, onion and garlic.
Add tomatoes and taco mix. Pour into 8-inch pan.
Mix milk, egg and cornbread mix together. Pour over meat mixture.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: baked fish on grill
directions: Place 2 to 3 pats of butter under each fillet on aluminum foil.
Place 2 to 3 pats on top of each fillet.
Slice onion and pop out rings.
Lay on top.
Slice lemon in thin slices.
Place on top of onion.
Sprinkle with garlic salt and pepper to taste. Roll foil around and seal.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes (depending on size of fillets), turning once.
This may also be baked in a preheated oven.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Cook spaghetti; drain thoroughly.
Set aside.
Bake chicken breasts and cut into bite size chunks.
Saute mushrooms in butter. Mix chicken chunks, mushrooms and spaghetti with sour cream and chicken soup.
Place ingredients into a buttered casserole and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and bread crumbs.
Bake at 300° for 40 minutes (uncovered).

title: almond bread
directions: Mix eggs, sugar and oil together.
Blend well.
Add the flour, baking powder and nutmeg.
Mix well.
Fold in chopped nuts. Grease a cookie sheet.
Form dough into 2 loaves on a cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° to 350° for 20 minutes.

title: waffles
directions: Combine
flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Add egg yolks, milk
and
butter.
Mix
well, then fold in beaten egg whites. Pour
mixture in waffle iron.
Makes approximately 12 waffles.

title: beef and potato casserole
directions: Brown ground beef in shortening.
Drain.
To the boiling water, add onion and simmer 5 minutes.
Add mushroom soup, salt and pepper to cooked onions.
Cover bottom of 1 1/2-quart casserole dish with layer of potatoes.
Cover with a thin layer of ground beef.
Top with onion soup mixture.
Continue alternating layers.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes to an hour or until potatoes are tender.
Extra water may be added if mixture is too dry.
Yield:
4 to 6 servings.

title: spaghetti sauce with meat balls
directions: Mix together first 7 ingredients.
Shape into balls.
Brown in shortening.
Add rest of ingredients.
Simmer 2 hours.
Remove cover last hour.
Serve with Parmesan cheese.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Mix beef, bread crumbs, pepper, egg, salt, soy sauce and milk together.
Let set in refrigerator for 1 hour.
Shape mixture into walnut size balls.
Cook slow in skillet until done.
Drain fat and remove meatballs.
Blend flour and oil.
Cook to boiling, stirring constantly.
Should be smooth and bubbly.
Reduce heat and simmer 1 minute.

title: sausage and spanish rice
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Cook sausages until browned; reserve sausage and pour off drippings except for 2 tablespoons.
Add onions and green peppers and saute until onion is tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients; pour into a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Top with sausages and bake for 30 minutes.
Serves 4.
Preparation time is 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: roll-ups
directions: Spread softened cream cheese on slices of dried beef.
Roll up.
Cut in slices and put toothpick through each.

title: frosted cranberry salad
directions: Drain juice from pineapple and add enough water to make one cup.
Boil and add to Jell-O.
Mix well and let cool.
Add 7-Up to Jell-O and chill until nearly set.
Add pineapple and cranberry sauce.
Chill until set.
Beat Dream Whip and cream cheese together until smooth.
Add nuts to Dream Whip, then pour mixture on top of Jell-O.
Chill for several hours.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Combine 2 tablespoons butter and flour; cook gently.
Remove from heat; stir in seasonings and cream.
Fold in beans.
Place in a shallow 2-quart dish.
Cover with cheese, then crumbs (corn flakes) mixed with 1 tablespoon butter.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: never-fail banana dump cake
directions: Dump shortening, sugar, eggs and bananas in bowl and mix.
Dump in the rest of the ingredients and mix well.
Use a greased 9 x 13-inch pan and dump mixture in.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes.

title: tex mex
directions: Brown and drain beef, add onion, picante sauce and chili powder.
Simmer.
Add tomatoes and olives.
Top with cheese and sour cream.
Serve on tortillas or with soft shells.

title: country-style steak
directions: Cut the steak into small pieces.
Roll in flour and brown in skillet.
Place the browned steak into crock-pot and pour the soup and water over top.
Salt and pepper.
Cook on high for 2 to 3 hours or on low for 5 to 6 hours.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Beat eggs and water; add to cake and pudding mixes.
Add butter and chips.
Beat for 2 minutes.
Bake at 350° in a greased and floured tube pan for 50 minutes.
Sift powdered sugar on top after removing from pan.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: I cook my spaghetti in chicken broth.
Remove chicken from broth and debone.
While spaghetti is cooking, put all other ingredients in heavy boiler.
Heat until cheese is melted.
Add chicken.
Place in glass dish.
Put in oven; heat until bubbly.

title: twice-filled potatoes
directions: Bake foil wrapped potatoes in a 375° oven for 1 hour until lightly squeezed.
Remove foil.
When cool enough to handle, slice top quarter off.
Scoop out inside without breaking skin.
Place scooped out potato in large bowl.
Add cottage cheese, yogurt, celery, red pepper, chives, mustard, horseradish and thyme.
Fill shells with filling.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake on cookie sheet in a 375° oven until cheese is melted.
Makes 4 servings.

title: baked chicken and rice
directions: Combine rice and soups and pour into 9 x 13-inch baking pan. Place chicken parts on top.
Sprinkle onion soup over chicken. Cover with foil.
Bake 2 hours in 325° oven.

title: golden grahams s'mores
directions: Grease rectangular pan (13 x 9 x 2-inch).
Heat syrup, margarine and chips to boiling, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; stir in vanilla.
Pour over cereal in bowl; toss until coated.
Fold in marshmallows one cup at a time.
Press in pan with buttered back of spoon.
Let stand 1 hour.
Cut into 2-inch squares.
Store, loosely covered, at room temperature up to 2 days.
Makes 24 squares.

title: cold oven cake
directions: Do not preheat oven.
Mix well.
Pour in a greased and floured tube pan.
Bake 1 hour and 20 minutes at 325°.

title: meat loaf puff
directions: In a large bowl, combine the 1 beaten egg and milk.
Stir in soft bread crumbs, onion, 1 1/2 teaspoons of salt and 1/8 teaspoon pepper.
Add ground beef; mix well.
Put meat mixture into an 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Drain off excess fat.
Arrange tomato slices atop partially baked meat loaf. Sprinkle with a little salt and pepper.
Cover with American cheese slices.

title: craft dough recipe
directions: The recipes in this section were written by some of the kids in the Redfield Headstart Class of 1993-94.
Enjoy reading and if you feel daring, use at your own risk.

title: coleslaw
directions: In large bowl, stir together first 4 ingredients until smooth. Add cabbage, green pepper and onion.
Toss to coat well.
Cover. Chill.
Makes about 6 cups.

title: warm scallop and rice salad
directions: In 1-quart casserole dish, combine leeks, pepper and garlic. Cover and microwave 2 minutes. Add rice and 3/4 cup water. Stir well and cook 5 minutes, uncovered,
and 3 minutes covered. Add scallops and cook 3 minutes. Add remaining ingredients; stir and serve.

title: hot potatoes with salad dressing(this recipe is good with polish sausage or reubens.)
directions: Boil potatoes until tender.
Peel and slice.
Make salad dressing by blending sugar and flour in a large saucepan.
Add fat, vinegar, water, salt, pepper and dry mustard.
Cook 2 minutes, then remove from heat.
Add slightly beaten egg yolks and mix well.
Place potatoes in a baking dish, then pour hot dressing mixture over them.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: rhubarb cream pie
directions: Put rhubarb in an unbaked pie shell.
Beat egg.
Add sugar, flour, cream, melted butter and vanilla.
Mix well and pour over rhubarb.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes, then turn oven down to 350° for another 30 minutes.

title: fritoli casserole
directions: Place 2 cups corn chips in a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Brown meat with onion in skillet, stirring to keep meat crumbly.
Add undrained beans and olives, water, salt and 3/4 cup cheese.
Mix well and spread over chips in casserole.
Sprinkle remaining chips and cheese over top.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: mom's plain pound cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating each thoroughly when added.
Add flavoring and fold into flour. Mix well on slow speed with mixer.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: mostaccioli
directions: Cook mostaccioli shells until tender and drain.
Cook ground beef and season to taste.
Add to spaghetti sauce.
Grate the two cheeses in separate bowls.
Layer your shells and sauce in a large cake pan.
Cover each layer with yellow cheese.
Smother top with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour or until cheese is hot and melted.

title: chocolate peanut butter pie
directions: Beat eggs with 3/4 cup butter, melted chocolate and sugar for 5 full minutes until smooth and thick.
In separate bowl, beat peanut butter with remaining 1/4 cup butter.
While you are beating, add up to 1/3 cup of the cream in order to make the peanut butter spreadable consistency that will swirl readily into the mixture.

title: lemon pie
directions: Cook in double boiler until thick.

title: pear preserves
directions: Boil sugar and water rapidly 2 minutes.
Add pears and boil gently 15 minutes.
Add 1 1/2 cups sugar and 1 thin sliced lemon. Cook rapidly until fruit is clear, about 25 minutes.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix corn, flour, sugar and salt together.
Combine well beaten eggs, melted butter and milk.
Mix with corn mixture.
Pour into a greased casserole dish and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Stir from bottom 2 or 3 times during the first 30 minutes.
Place casserole in a pan of water (about 1 inch).

title: cranberry relish
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients, mixing well.
Add remaining ingredients, stirring until blended.
Chill.
Stor in airtight container in refrigerator.
Yields 1 quart.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Cut up artichoke hearts and mix with mayo and Parmesan cheese in 9 x 9-inch square baking dish.
Sprinkle top with cheese if desired.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Recipe can be doubled and placed in oblong baking dish.

title: working girl's apple pie
directions: Peel and slice enough apples to fill 9 x 13-inch pan 3/4 full. Sprinkle with cinnamon, 1 tablespoon flour and 1 cup sugar.
Mix in bowl butter, 1 cup sugar, 1 cup flour and eggs.
Pour mixture over apples.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: american chop suey
directions: Boil macaroni.
Brown hamburger and add onion.
Drain off oil.
Add spices and tomato soup.
Simmer.
Drain macaroni and add to mixture, heating for about 10 minutes.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese when serving.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Dissolve cornstarch in water.
Mix with pineapple and sugar. Add eggs and vanilla; mix well.
Pour into well-greased (with oleo) casserole.
Sprinkle with cinnamon; dot with oleo.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: pork barbecue
directions: Have pork cut into small pieces.
Mix all ingredients and cook slowly for 7 to 8 hours or until meat falls into pieces.
Serve on 18 to 20 buns.

title: italian burgers
directions: Shape hamburger into patties.
Fry on one side.
Turn patties over and put 1 slice of onion and 1 slice of bell pepper ring on top.
Sprinkle Italian seasoning over top of pepper rings.
Put 1 slice cheese on each.
Pour tomato sauce over patties.
Cook over medium heat for 10 minutes.
Serve with rice or pasta.

title: cucumber pickles
directions: Bring vinegar, sugar and spices to boil.
Add cucumbers and onions
and
bring	to a second boil.
Pack in sterilized jars and seal.

title: heavenly hash cake
directions: With fork, beat eggs.
Add sugar, butter and vanilla.
Add cocoa and flour; stir nuts in.
Pour batter into 13 x 9 x 2-inch cake pan.
As soon as cake is done, sprinkle miniature marshmallows on hot cake and immediately put on icing.
Do not use mixer.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and cocoa well until all lumps are out of mixture.
Mix egg yolks, milk and vanilla well.
Mix all ingredients together in a black skillet and cook slowly on stove eye, stirring constantly, until thick and creamy. Add butter and pour into pie shell.
Top with egg white meringue and bake until golden brown.
Makes two 9-inch pies.

title: orange oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix together shortening, sugar and brown sugar.
Add egg, vanilla, flour, salt and soda.
Mix well.
Add orange juice, oatmeal and chocolate bits.
Shape into balls and bake on cookie sheet for 15 minutes at 350°.

title: grilled lemon chicken
directions: Marinate chicken in soy sauce and lemon juice for 1 to 2 hours. Sprinkle with pepper and garlic powder.
Grill on barbecue for 10 to 15 minutes.
Baste with marinade and turn midway.
Discard marinade.
Do not use on cooked chicken!
(Good served with rice pilaf.)

title: grandma nell's sour cream sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugar and lard; add eggs and mix.
Add cream (to sour, leave out overnight or add 1 teaspoon lemon juice).
Add vanilla; add soda, powder and flour.
Roll out and cut out choice of cookies.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Do not brown on bottom.
If brown, cooked too long.

title: tomato sauce for ham
directions: Combine 7-Up, catsup, oleo, sugar, vinegar, Worcestershire sauce and salt.
Thicken with cornstarch.
Cook 15 to 20 minutes. Pour over ham and heat.

title: macaroni tuna salad
directions: Cook macaroni.
Drain.
Stir in tuna, soup and Miracle Whip. Serve warm as a casserole or cold on a plate of lettuce.

title: potato soup
directions: Peel and dice 2-quarts potatoes.
Cover with water and cook until tender. Peel and chop medium onion. Saute in butter until tender.

title: hodgepodge soup
directions: Sprinkle with celery seed; simmer at least 1 hour.
Nice to use in crock-pot.
May also be frozen.

title: cinnamon apples
directions: In a large saucepan over medium heat, bring water, candies and sugar to a boil, stirring constantly until candies and sugar are dissolved.
Reduce heat; carefully add apples.
Cook, uncovered, until apples are tender. Cool slightly. With a slotted spoon, transfer apples to a serving dish. Pour sugar syrup over apples. Cover and refrigerate for at least 3 hours.

title: grandma's old-fashioned macaroni and cheese
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cook macaroni according to package directions until not quite done.
Drain.
Put one-half of macaroni in buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer one-half of grated cheese on top.
Add remainder of macaroni and finish layering with other half of cheese.
Pour evaporated milk over the top.
Add tomatoes and green peppers on top.
If liquid is not visible, add additional liquid (milk).
Cover with aluminum foil.
Bake at 325° for 2 hours.
Remove foil and add crushed cornflakes the last 20 minutes of baking time for a crisper topping.

title: chocolate chip oats and caramel bars
directions: Mix together cookie dough and oatmeal. Reserve 1 cup. Press in 13 x 9 pan. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until dough puffs and appears dry. In small bowl, combine flour, caramel topping and vanilla together. Sprinkle chocolate chips over partially baked crust. Drizzle evenly with caramel mixture. Crumble the 1 cup reserved dough over caramel. Bake for an additional 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown. Cool 10 minutes. Run a knife around the edges of pan.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Cut peppers in half; remove seeds.
Precook peppers in boiling salt water for 5 minutes.
Cook beef and onion until meat is browned.
Season with salt and pepper.
Add tomatoes, water, uncooked rice and Worcestershire sauce.
Cover and simmer until rice is tender, about 15 minutes.
Stir shredded cheese into beef and rice mixture.
Stuff peppers and stand upright in baking dish. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: bauern fruhstuck(farmer's breakfast)
directions: Peel, cube and boil the potatoes.
Peel and dice the onions. Cube and fry the uncooked sausage (if chosen).
Melt the margarine in a pan.
Lightly saute the onions, then brown potatoes.
Mix the eggs and milk, then add salt, sweet paprika, ground nutmeg and pepper (to taste), chives and the precooked sausage (if chosen).

title: popcorn cake
directions: In large glass mixing pitcher, combine margarine, oil, caramels and miniature marshmallows.
Alternate microwaving and stirring until ingredients become a pourable mixture.
Place popcorn in large mixing bowl.
Pour candy sauce over popcorn and toss to mix.
Little by little, stir in candies and peanuts. Press with oiled or greased fingers into well-greased angel food cake pan with loose bottom.
Cool until firm, then remove from pan.
Store tightly closed in foil or plastic wrap.
To serve, slice with sharp knife.

title: puffed wheat bars
directions: Put puffed wheat and peanuts or raisins in a greased bowl. Melt marshmallows with margarine and brown sugar, adding vanilla when melted.
Pour over puffed wheat and peanuts or raisins.
Put into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Let stand before cutting into bars.

title: bread custard pudding
directions: Heat the milk in a saucepan and set aside. Put bread crumbs in a mixing bowl and pour the milk over this. Add the salt and sugar. Beat the eggs and add to the mixture. Add the butter and the vanilla extract and mix well. Pour the mixture into a 1 1/2-quart greased baking dish and set the dish in a larger size baking pan. Pour hot water into the larger pan to within 1-inch of the top of the dish.

title: kissing ball
directions: Combine first seven ingredients until well blended. Refrigerate until firm at least 2 hours.
Shape into a ball and roll in sesame seed until completely coated.
Place on serving dish and decorate with cheese spread, mistletoe and parsley sprigs.
Serve with crackers.
Makes 1 (about 4-inch) ball.

title: apple crumb pie
directions: Line a 9-inch pie plate with pastry.
Arrange apples in unbaked shell.
Mix 1/2 cup sugar and cinnamon; sprinkle over apples.
Mix flour with the other 1/2 cup sugar; cut in butter until crumbly. Sprinkle over apples.
Bake at 400° for 35 to 40 minutes or until done.
(If pie browns too quickly, cover edge with foil.)

title: nacho dip
directions: Brown hamburger with onion.
Drain.
Mix with remaining ingredients in crock-pot until the cheese is melted, stirring occasionally.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: honey cookies
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Sift together flour, soda and baking powder.
Mix both groups together.
Stir in 1/2 cup chopped nuts. Roll into 2 rolls.
Store in refrigerator overnight.
Slice and bake for 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.

title: apple pancakes
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Combine egg yolks and milk. Pour into dry ingredients and stir well.
Stir in butter and apples.
Fold in egg whites.
Let batter stand a few minutes, then bake on hot griddle.

title: orange sherbet
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Place in ice cream freezer and churn until firm.
Makes 1/2 gallon.

title: garden pasta salad
directions: Drain mixed fruit, reserving liquid.
Drizzle fruit with vinegar and set aside.
Cook pasta in boiling water until tender; drain and cool slightly.

title: hot chicken supreme
directions: Combine all ingredients, except potato chips. Stir well. Spoon chicken mixture into a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Top with chips. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: cornerstone raisin bran muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake in greased muffin tins at 400° for 12 minutes.
Makes 6 dozen.
Mixture may be placed in tightly closed container and kept in refrigerator for up to 6 weeks.

title: fruit dip
directions: Let cream cheese thaw to room temperature.
Mix with the marshmallow cream with a mixer.
Refrigerate until ready to use. Dip fruit and eat.

title: chicken capri
directions: Dip breasts in flour, salt and pepper.
Brown in frying pan. Put in baking dish.
Mix soup, wine and cheese and pour over chicken.
Top with almonds.
Cover with foil and bake slowly in a 350° oven for about 1 hour.

title: calico beans
directions: Cook the
bacon
and onions together; add beef that has been drained.
Combine
the
entire
recipe in large casserole baking dish; mix thoroughly. Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: white texas sheet cake
directions: In a large saucepan, bring butter and water to a boil.
Remove from the heat.
Stir in flour, sugar, eggs, sour cream, vanilla, salt and baking soda until smooth.
Pour into a greased 15 x 10-inch baking pan.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 22 minutes or until cake is golden brown and tests done.
Cool for 20 minutes.

title: chocolate nut pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and cocoa.
Add mix.
Beat eggs and add to mixture.
Melt margarine and add to mixture.
Stir in vanilla and coconut.
Pour mixture into shells and sprinkle chopped pecans on top.
Bake at 325° for 60 minutes.
Pies freeze really well.

title: nacho chicken
directions: In a bowl, combine soup, 2/3 cup cheese, milk, chile peppers and green onion.
Put 1/2 cup chips in bottom of 1 1/2-quart casserole. Top with 1/2 of the chicken cubes. Top with 1/2 of the soup mix. Repeat layers (chips, chicken and soup).
Sprinkle top with remaining Cheddar cheese. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes. Garnish edges with tomatoes, black olives and tortilla chips, if desired.

title: dilly bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Combine cottage cheese, sugar, onion, butter, dill seed, salt, soda, egg and yeast.
Mix well. Add flour and blend thoroughly.
Cover.
Rise in warm place until doubled in size (1 hour).
Punch dough down.
Mold into greased 8-inch round 1 1/2 to 2-quart casserole.
Let rise 30 to 40 minutes more.
Bake at 350° about 40 to 50 minutes.

title: nutty peach crisp cake
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Layer ingredients in order listed in ungreased pan (13 x 9 x 2-inch).
Bake for 55 to 60 minutes.
Let stand at least 15 minutes before serving.
Serve warm or cool and, if desired, with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: chocolate raisin cookies
directions: Blend sugar and oil; cream in eggs.
Add dry ingredients, then oatmeal.
Mix thoroughly; fold in chocolate chips and raisins. The batter will be thick.
Add a small amount of milk.
Bake in a 350° oven for 10 minutes.

title: potatoes with skins
directions: Melt butter, salt and pepper.
Add potatoes.
Cover with foil and bake for 1/2 hour.
Then put on cheese (can add Cheddar cheese also).
Then bake, without foil, for 20 minutes.
Then add peppers, pimento and parsley and heat for a few more minutes.

title: chicken a la king
directions: Melt margarine and stir in flour.
Add chicken broth and cook on low heat until thick.
Add remaining ingredients and heat to boiling.
Pour in casserole.
Top with biscuits.
Bake at 450° until biscuits are golden brown, about 12 minutes.

title: ladyfingers
directions: Soften margarine to room temperature.
Mix margarine, sugar, flour and nuts until dough holds its shape.
Form into small balls and shape into fingers or crescents.

title: apple bundt cake
directions: Mix well. Pour in Bundt cake pan.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Lightly brown coconut in butter.
Stir often.
Save 2 tablespoons for garnish.
Press remaining coconut over the bottom and sides of greased 8-inch pie pan.
Cool.

title: chocolate nut bars
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine cracker crumbs and margarine and press into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 8 minutes.
Reduce oven to 350°.

title: salmon potato strata
directions: In large bowl, combine salmon, onion, celery, eggs, milk, 1/2 teaspoon salt, dill and pepper.
Mix well.
Place half of potatoes in greased 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle with 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Spread half of salmon mixture over potatoes.
Repeat with remaining potatoes, salt and salmon.

title: mean mountain mamma's mud-slide pie
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Pat into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes (not a minute longer).
Cool thoroughly.

title: cornbread dressing
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients together and bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.
While hot, break into pieces.
Add salt and pepper and poultry seasoning.
Mix with chicken broth.
Bake again for 1 hour.
Bread can be baked the night before.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together and form into small balls, slightly smaller than a ping-pong
ball.
Bake
for
to 30 minutes at 300°.
Do not overbake.
Makes about 75.

title: fried new potatoes
directions: Cook bacon in a large skillet until crisp; drain on paper towels. Crumble and set aside, reserving drippings in skillet. Cook potatoes in drippings 10 minutes or until browned; turn frequently. Drain. Place potatoes in serving dish; sprinkle with salt, pepper and crumbled bacon.

title: clam spread
directions: Melt cream cheese, milk and Worcestershire sauce.
Drain clams, shrimp or crab; add chives.
Heat and mix together.
Serve with vegetables.

title: mystery salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add tomatoes.
Mix in blender.
Stir in Tabasco sauce.
Pour into mold.
Refrigerate. Serves 12.
Extremely low in calories.

title: creole salad
directions: Wash the zucchini thoroughly.
Do not peel, but slice it wafer-thin.
Prepare the other vegetables and one hour or so before serving, toss them all together.
When ready to serve, toss again with olive oil and wine vinegar to taste.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: calico beans
directions: Cook hamburger and onion until done. Drain off fat and add rest of ingredients.
Mix and bake 1 hour at 350°.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown the hamburger, onion and pepper together.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Thicken with flour, if needed.

title: quiche
directions: Bake pie shell at 375° for 5 minutes.
Sprinkle bacon into pie shell.
Top with cheese.
Combine eggs, half and half, nutmeg, salt and pepper in bowl; mix well.
Pour over cheese.
Dot with margarine.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: basic pizza dough
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
In a large bowl, dissolve yeast in water.
Add oil, salt and sugar and mix well.
Gradually add flour, a little at a time, mixing thoroughly.
Knead dough about 5 minutes or until smooth.
Set aside to rise; do not play with dough.
Grease pizza pan well. Shape dough.
Spread sauce over dough.
Add cheese and other toppings.
Bake on bottom rack 15 minutes (check after 12).

title: russian borscht
directions: Wash, peel and grate beets coarsely.
Place all ingredients in large soup kettle.
Bring to boil and reduce to simmer until beets are tender.
Remove from heat, cover and chill.
Serve cold with scoop of sour cream in the middle of soup bowl.
Wonderful on hot summer night!

title: pepper jelly turnovers
directions: Cut cheese and butter into flour.
Quickly stir in water and shape into a ball.
Chill overnight.
Roll dough very thin and cut with biscuit cutter into 5-inch circles.
Fill half with jalapeno jelly.
Fold over and crimp edges with fork.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: kerri's pink tortellini
directions: In saucepan melt butter over medium heat.
Add onion and saute until translucent (about 5 minutes).
In blender puree tomatoes until smooth.
Add pureed tomatoes, basil, salt and pepper to saucepan.
Reduce heat to low; simmer 10 minutes. Whisk in cream. Simmer 5 minutes more.
Meanwhile, cook tortellini according to package directions.
Transfer to a warm serving bowl.
Add sauce, toss well.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Makes 4 servings, 560 calories each.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix together with electric mixer sour cream, cream cheese and seasoning.
Spread on tray.
Sprinkle with green onion, then shredded lettuce, chopped tomato and finally shredded Cheddar cheese.
Serve with large tortilla chips.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix cornmeal and sugar in large bowl.
Add milk, eggs and margarine, chopped into pieces.
Add coconut last.
Pour into shell.
Bake at 325° for about 45 minutes, or until golden brown and knife stuck in middle of pie comes out clean.

title: bacon wrapped scallops
directions: Rinse scallops; drain on paper towels.
Season with pepper. Preheat broiler.
Cut each bacon slice in half crosswise.
Wrap each scallop in a piece of bacon.
Place on a broiling pan; broil about 6 inches from heat, turning 10 to 12 minutes, until bacon is crisp and scallops are opaque throughout.
Remove from broiler; drain on paper towels.
Serve.
Yields 4.

title: chili beans
directions: Brown hamburger.
Pour off grease.
Add onions and peppers to hamburger.
Next add all tomato paste and tomato sauce.
Add all other ingredients.
Cook slowly, at least 1 hour for flavors to blend.

title: crock-pot chili
directions: Brown the beef in a large skillet.
Drain and place in a slow cooker.
Saute chopped onions in a small amount of shortening. Stir in chili powder and cook a minute longer.
Add remaining ingredients to the beef mixture.
Cook 8 to 10 hours on low setting or 1 1/2 hours on high and then 5 hours on low.

title: chocolate trifle(death by chocolate)
directions: Bake brownie mix by directions in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Prick top of warm brownies with fork; drizzle with Kahlua.
Let cool and crumble.
Prepare pudding mix by directions, omitting chilling. Place 1/3 of crumbled brownies in 3-inch trifle dish.
Top with 1/2 pudding, whipped topping and crushed candy bars.
Repeat layers twice, ending with crushed candy bars.
Chill 8 hours.

title: country corn bread
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Grease muffin cups and heat for 2 to 3 minutes in oven.
Combine all ingredients and fill muffin cups 2/3 full.
Bake in hot oven for 20 to 25 minutes until golden brown. Yields 12 muffins.

title: easy chicken casserole
directions: Melt margarine and combine with stuffing and broth.
Place half of this mixture in a 9-inch square pan and save the other half for the top.
Place chicken over stuffing.
Mix soup and sour cream and pour over chicken.
Top with remaining stuffing mixture. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: holiday cranberry salad
directions: Fix Jell-O (with less water) and stir in cranberries.
Chill until firm.
(Could use 8 x 12-inch flat dish.)
Add crushed pineapple to cream cheese (juice also).
Cream well.
Spread over Jell-O.
Sprinkle with chopped pecans.

title: breakfast punch
directions: Put juices in a ring jello mold.
When partially set, add cherries and orange slices so they will show when frozen firmly. Overnight is best.
Put ring (unmolded) in a punch bowl.
Pour the ginger ale in the bowl.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix together and chill overnight.

title: italian grilled sirloin steak
directions: Put stewed tomatoes, green pepper and Mozzarella cheese in a bowl and mix together.
Put about a tablespoon (or more) on each steak, then roll steak.
In another bowl mix Italian bread crumbs, Romano and Parmesan cheese and garlic powder.
Dip and roll steak in this mixture.
You might need toothpicks to hold together.
Cook on grill in foil until steak is done.
You can pound steak to make it thin or have it sliced very thin.
Serves 6.

title: apple pie
directions: Place 1 crust in pie plate and brush crust with milk.

title: san francisco chicken
directions: Brown chicken on both sides in oil over medium heat.
Remove chicken and add garlic in the skillet.
Saute for a minute. Combine broth, soy sauce, brown sugar and crushed red pepper. Place chicken in skillet and pour sauce over it.
Cover tightly and simmer over low heat for 20 minutes.
Remove chicken to serving platter.
Stir in cornstarch dissolved in water.
Stir and cook until thickened.
Pour over chicken.

title: baked beans
directions: Combine all ingredients except bacon.
Use casserole dish. Put bacon strips on top.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: cherry peach cobbler(makes 8 to 10 servings)
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Combine cherry and peach filling in 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Combine sugar and cinnamon in small bowl. Separate each biscuit into 2 sections; dip each section in margarine, then in sugar-cinnamon.
Arrange on top of filling. Bake 18 to 20 minutes, until golden brown.
Serve warm.
Bake time:
20 minutes.

title: weight watchers milkshake
directions: Put in blender all ingredients.
Add ice cubes to make a thick shake.

title: fried corn
directions: Fry bacon; remove from skillet, leaving the drippings. Crumble bacon and return to skillet. Add corn, water, pimentos and jalapenos. Salt and pepper to taste. Cook away water and stir-fry briefly.

title: dorito casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Add chili and stir until heated. Put into 9 x 13-inch pan and cover with sour cream.
Lay cheese slices on top. Crush Doritos and sprinkle on top.
Bake at 300° for 15 minutes or until cheese melts.
Serve with taco sauce, if desired.

title: fudge
directions: Cook milk, sugars and butter about 15 minutes.
Add morsels, vanilla, marshmallow cream and nuts.
Pour into lightly greased pan.

title: lemonly cheesecake
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water and allow to jell slightly. Cream the cream cheese and sugar together.
Add lemon juice.
Whip together Jell-O and cream cheese mixture.
Fold in Cool Whip. Pour into crusts.
Fruit may be added for topping.

title: sweet garlic pickles
directions: Drain pickles and slice; put into large glass container or crock (punch bowl can be used).
Add sugar, garlic, vinegar and pepper and mix together.
Fold the cheese cloth 3 or 4 times to make it dense enough to hold the pickling spices, celery seed and mustard seed.
Fold up the spices in the cheese cloth to make a small bundle; tie ends with cord.
Bury bundle of spices in middle of pickles.
Sprinkle turmeric over top.
Loosely cover container with plastic wrap.
Daily for the next 5 days, remove bundle, stir, replace bundle and cover.
Fill jars with tight lids.
No need to refrigerate.

title: gravy baked pork chops
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sprinkle salt and pepper on chops and then brown on both sides in a 10-inch skillet over medium heat. Drain off drippings.
Pour around chops a mixture of 1 can cream of mushroom soup, evaporated milk and water.
Bake 45 minutes or until done.
Stir gravy.

title: apple pie cake
directions: Mix well in a large bowl.
Divide into three aluminum pie pans.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes.
If pie gets too brown before done, cover with foil.
Pies freeze well after cooked.

title: turkey casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients in a 2-quart casserole sprayed with nonstick cooking spray.
Add additional water or chicken broth as desired for consistency.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes or until bubbly.
Garnish with cranberry sauce.
Makes 6 servings.

title: blueberry quick bread
directions: In large bowl, with fork, mix flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
With pastry blender, cut in butter or margarine until mixture resembles fine crumbs.
Stir in walnuts.

title: broccoli nut casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to directions on package; drain.
Add soup, mayonnaise and chopped peanuts.
Mix well.
Add eggs and onion.
Mix well.
Melt margarine and pour over bread crumbs. Pour broccoli mixture into greased pan.
Sprinkle with grated cheese and top with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: italian beef
directions: Add 4 to 5 pounds of thinly sliced roast beef (or venison) to other ingredients.
Simmer 1 hour or all day on low in crock-pot.

title: gramma's soft christmas cookie
directions: Cream shortening, sugars, eggs and vanilla; set aside.
Combine salt, soda, baking powder, nutmeg, cinnamon, ginger and flour.
Add flour mixture to shortening mixture.
Begin adding buttermilk as the flour/shortening mixture gets dry.
Your dough will be sticky. Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Roll out dough onto a floured surface.
Cut out cookies about 1/4-inch thick.
Bake in a preheated 400° oven for about 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool cookies, then frost with your favorite frosting.

title: crispy potato wedges
directions: Cut potatoes into four wedges; chop onion.
Spread both out in 9 x 12-inch pan.
Add oil, cheese and seasoning salt.
Mix together by hand until potatoes are thoroughly coated.
Bake at 400° for about 45 minutes or until potatoes are tender on inside, crisp on outside.
Good dipped in sour cream.

title: beef stir-fry(preparation time: 15 minutes; cooking time: 10 minutes)
directions: Partially freeze steak; slice into thin slices across the grain.
Marinate steak strips in teriyaki sauce, 1 tablespoon oil and cornstarch for 30 minutes.
Heat remaining oil.
Stir-fry peppers and onions for 3 minutes.
Remove.
Stir-fry beef (1/2 time for 2 to 3 minutes).
Drain.
Return all ingredients.
Cook until hot.
Serves 4.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream butter, shortening and sugar until light and fluffy. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift flour with cocoa, salt and baking powder.
Add flour mixture, alternating with milk, to creamed mixture.
Add vanilla and blend well.

title: dump cake
directions: Grease 9x13 inch cake pan.
Add both cans of fruit filling. Pour dry cake mix over fruit.
Then pour the melter butter over the top of the dry cake mix.
Spread chopped nuts over top.
Bake at 325° for one hour.
Good served warm with ice cream or cool whip.

title: pepper beef
directions: Heat pan; add oil and garlic.
When garlic turns brown, remove.
Add beef, cut in small thin pieces, and fry a few minutes.
Season with salt and pepper.
Add soup stock and continue to cook a few seconds.
Add mixture of cornstarch, soy sauce and water.
Cook until thickens, stirring slowly.
Add green peppers and ginger.
Heat thoroughly and serve hot with rice.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: chicken and mushrooms
directions: In skillet in margarine, cook chicken until brown, then remove chicken from skillet.
In addition, add a tablespoon of margarine; cook mushrooms, onions and garlic powder until tender and liquid is evaporated.
Stir often.
Add soup, milk and pepper and heat until boiling.
Return chicken to skillet.
Cover and cook over low heat for 5 minutes or until chicken is no longer pink.
Stir often.
Serve with noodles or rice.

title: "get well" soup
directions: Brown hamburger with chopped celery, onion and green pepper. Drain well. Place all ingredients in large crock-pot or Dutch oven. Simmer on low for several hours.
Enjoy!

title: sausage and zucchini stew
directions: Cut sausage into 1-inch pieces.
Drain and chop tomatoes. Brown sausage in heavy skillet over low heat until cooked.
Add onion.
Cook until soft (if necessary, add a bit of oil). Add everything else except cheese.
Stir-fry gently for 5 minutes (no longer).
Serve with cheese.

title: dillon's raisin bread
directions: Mix and knead well, then bake until done.

title: vegetarian meatballs
directions: In a large bowl, combine all ingredients.
Form into balls of desired size and place in casserole dish.
Cover with 3 to 4 cups of cream gravy and bake in 350° oven for 40 minutes.

title: mama's rice pudding
directions: Mix milk and pudding, stirring until thickened.
Add remaining ingredients.
Microwave on High, 8 to 10 minutes, stirring 3 times.

title: chocolate crackler
directions: Mix oil, chocolate and sugar.
Blend in eggs, one at a time; mix well.
Add vanilla.
Combine dry ingredients and add to chocolate mixture.
Chill several hours or overnight.
Drop teaspoon of dough into powdered sugar and form into a ball.
Place 2-inches apart on greased cookie sheets.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes in 350° oven or until almost no imprint remains when touched lightly in the center.

title: enchilada pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Slice onion and peppers.
Add garlic. Drain tomatoes; cook beef in a large skillet until brown.
Remove with slotted spoon.
Add onion and peppers; cook until soft, about 15 minutes.
Remove with slotted spoon and return meat to pan. Add tomatoes, vinegar, cumin, oregano, 1/2 teaspoon salt and 1/4 teaspoon pepper.

title: lamb pie
directions: Have lamb cut in 2-inch cubes; and the excess fat trimmed off. Roll each piece of lamb in seasoned flour; place in hot oil; add sliced onion.
Brown lamb well on all sides.
Pour off oil; add boiling water, cover and simmer slowly 1 1/2 hours.
Add vegetables and marjoram; cook until carrots are tender.
Remove to casserole or baking dish.
Pour thickened gravy over meat and vegetables.
Cover with canned biscuits and bake until biscuits are done.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown meat, then add mushroom soup.
Heat and stir soup through.
Layer in bottom of lasagna pan:
chips, hamburger mixture, enchilada sauce (a little less than 1 can) and slices of cheese.
Repeat again, ending with crushed chips and sauce.
Heat in oven at 325° for 30 minutes or until mixture bubbles.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Stir together the flour, baking powder, cinnamon, soda and 1 teaspoon salt.
Combine eggs, pumpkin, sugar and oil; beat until combined.
Add dry ingredients; beat until well combined.
Spread batter in an ungreased 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool.
Frost with Cream Cheese Frosting; cut into bars.
Makes 36.

title: chocolate pudding milk shake
directions: Pour milk into blender.
Add remaining ingredients; cover. Blend at high speed 15 seconds or until smooth.
Serve at once. (Mixture thickens as it stands.
Thin with additional milk, if desired.)

title: 7 layer jello
directions: Place bread cubes in lightly greased 2-quart casserole.
In large bowl, beat together the eggs, yolks, sugar, vanilla, orange peel and cinnamon.
Pour over bread cubes.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Bake in preheated 350° oven until knife inserted near center comes out clean, 50 to 60 minutes.
Serve with cream or milk, if desired.
Makes 8 servings.

title: baked macaroni and cheese
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cook macaroni in boiling salted water according to package directions until barely tender.
Drain well. Return to saucepan.
Add sour cream, cheese and milk.
Mix well. Put into small greased baking dish; sprinkle on paprika.
Bake at 325° for about 25 minutes.
Serves 2.

title: black bean luau salad
directions: Combine all in a bowl.
Dress with a good vinaigrette and toss. Nice to be served on a bed of greens.

title: bagna caoda(italian fondue)
directions: Cook garlic and anchovies in olive oil for 15 minutes (until anchovies have dissolved).
Transfer to an electric frypan/skillet and add butter.
Chop up a selection of vegetables such as Chinese cabbage, mushrooms, celery, cauliflower, green and red peppers, broccoli, artichoke hearts, etc., and set out in bowls.
You can also have a selection of chopped, bite size meats such as beef, pork or chicken.
Place your choice of vegetable or meat in the fondue to cook.
Serve on French bread slices.

title: tabuli(wheat salad)
directions: Cover wheat with boiling water.
Let sit for 2 hours (quickie: boil the wheat) until all the water is absorbed.
Mix all ingredients.
Refrigerate about 1 hour.

title: sourdough bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Mix all ingredients and store in refrigerator until ready to use.
Take out as many as you need. Keep the rest of dough refrigerated.

title: zucchini bread
directions: In a blender pour 1 cup vegetable oil. Add zucchini and blend. Add vanilla and eggs, again blend.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Mix first (6) ingredients well with spoon, pour into greased, floured pan.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Cook rice according to directions.
Mix everything except cheese and put into a 3-quart casserole.
Bake for 30 minutes in 350°.
Top with grated cheese and put back in oven to melt.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Rinse mushrooms and pat dry; remove stems.
Chop stems and combine with garlic.
Add this to sausage cooked until browned. Drain off extra grease.
Stir in shredded cheese, mixing until cheese begins to melt.
Spoon mixture into mushroom caps that have been spooned out (remove black part from inside).
Place in pan and bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: pull-apart yeast bread
directions: Cut each roll in half; dip in butter and roll in cheese. Arrange rolls in a lightly greased 10-inch tube pan.
Cover and let rise in a warm place (85°) free from drafts for 1 hour or until doubled in bulk.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Remove from pan and cool on a wire rack.

title: chili
directions: In half an inch of oil or bacon fat, saute onions, peppers and garlic until soft.
In another pan, brown ground beef.
Drain the fat from the beef and add the beef to the onion and pepper (or add the onion and pepper to the beef).

title: meatball yummies
directions: Combine beef, bread crumbs, egg and 2 tablespoons Prime Choice.
Mix and shape into 1-inch meatballs.
Brown in oil in skillet.
Drain fat from skillet. Combine 1/3 cup Prime Choice, brown sugar and butter with meatballs in skillet.
Simmer, covered, for 15 minutes or until done.
Makes about 2 dozen meatballs.

title: butterfinger pie
directions: Let ice cream set out for a few minutes.
Add Cool Whip and Butterfingers (that have been crumbed).
Mix together and add to crust and put in freezer.

title: king ranch chicken casserole
directions: Saute onion and bell pepper in hot oil
in large skillet over medium heat for 5 minutes, or until tender.
Stir in chicken and next 7 ingredients.
Remove from heat.

title: spinach madeleina
directions: Cook
spinach
as
directed;
drain and reserve liquid. Melt butter over low heat;
add flour, stirring until blended and smooth,
but
not
brown.
Add onion and cook until soft. Add spinach
liquid
and milk slowly, stirring constantly, to avoid lumps.
Cook until thickened and smooth.
Add seasonings and cheese
which
has
been cut in small pieces.
Stir until cheese melts.
Combine
with cooked spinach.
Drain artichoke hearts and cut in quarters.
Scatter hearts over bottom of 8 x 8-inch buttered pan.
Pour spinach mixture over top.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: baked coconut custard
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a bowl beat eggs just enough to blend evenly.
Stir in sugar and salt.
Slowly, beating with a fork, add the scaleded milk and vanilla.
Stir in coconut.
Pour into buttered custard cups.
Set cups in a shallow baking pan; pour 1 inch of water into the baking pan.
Bake for 45 minutes or when a knife inserted in custard comes out clean.
Custard will be firm when it cools.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt
butter in pan.
Mix sugar, flour and milk and add to margarine
in
pan.
Add peaches and bake at 375° for about 45 minutes.

title: pink stuff
directions: Mix well.
Chill for several hours.
Serve as a salad or dessert.

title: bacon cheddar puffs
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Bring milk and margarine to a boil over medium heat.
Add flour, all at once, stirring until mixture forms a ball and leaves side of pan.
Remove from heat.
Add eggs, one at a time, stirring until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients. Drop by teaspoonfuls on greased foil-lined cookie sheet.
Bake 25 minutes until puffed and golden brown.
Wrap securely and freeze.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Place bread in bottom of greased casserole.
Sprinkle with sausage and top with cheese.
Combine other ingredients and beat well and pour over mixture in pan.
Refrigerate overnight and bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: party ham and cheese biscuits
directions: Slice rolls in halves lengthwise; layer ham and cheese.
Put rolls together; cut as individual rolls.
Melt together the margarine, poppy seed, Worcestershire sauce and mustard.
Pour over rolls.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cover with foil before baking.
This can be done ahead of time and refrigerated or frozen before baking.

title: blond brownies
directions: Melt margarine over low heat, then set aside to cool.
Beat eggs until light, then beat in syrup, sugar and cooled margarine. Sift flour and baking powder and stir into egg mixture.
Stir in vanilla and nuts.
Spread into greased 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: cheesy hash brown casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Microwave potatoes for about 5 minutes or until partially thawed. Mix 3/4 bag of cheese, soups, sour cream, onion, salt and pepper in large bowl. Add potatoes; mix and pour into a Pam-sprayed 13 x 9 Pyrex dish. Cover with foil and bake for approximately 1 hour. Uncover and add remaining shredded cheese. Continue baking until golden brown.

title: stir-fried cabbage
directions: Combine sugar, vinegar, soy sauce, salt and cayenne; mix well. Heat the oil over medium heat.
Add cabbage and stir-fry for 2 to 3 minutes until cabbage is well coated with the oil.
Remove from the heat and stir the liquid mixture into the cabbage.
Serve hot or cold.
Serves 4.

title: gary's honey glazed wings
directions: Combine ingredients and marinate at least 4 hours or overnight (plastic bowl), turning over 1 to 2 times.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, in a huge casserole dish for 45 minutes or until wings are all glazed.
Last 3 to 4 minutes, broil to crisp.

title: applesauce-nut cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients in ungreased oblong pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inches, with fork, scraping corners frequently, until moistened.
Stir batter vigorously with fork 1 minute; scrape sides with rubber spatula.
Spread batter evenly in pan. Bake until top springs back when touched lightly in center, 34 to 40 minutes.
Cool; loosen cake from sides.
Cut and serve directly from pan.
Store any remaining cake loosely covered in refrigerator.

title: 6-week bran muffins
directions: Pour water ove 100% Bran in small bowl and set aside.
In giant bowl cream sugar and Crisco; add eggs and beat well after each.
Add buttermilk and stir.
Add All-Bran, then soaked bran and stir.
Sift flour, soda and salt together.
Add gradually. Bake 16 to 20 minutes at 375° (350° with honey).
Fruit may be added as desired.
Batter will store in refrigerator for 6 weeks.

title: crystal garden
directions: Note: Bluing may be hard to find.
Look in laundry section of grocery store.
Blue bottle next to starch and bleach products.

title: surprise cake
directions: Mix flour and sugar; set aside.
Melt in saucepan, margarine, water, Crisco and cocoa.
Add to flour and sugar and stir well. Mix buttermilk, eggs, soda, salt and vanilla.
Add to other mixture.
Hand mix, well.
Pour into a jelly roll pan (10 x 15-inch).
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Pour icing on cake while cake is hot.

title: guacamole dip
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Serve with chips.

title: charlotte's sugar cookies
directions: Beat all ingredients together. Add flour until mixture becomes too stiff for mixer. Knead batter. Roll out on floured surface and cut with cookie cutter. Bake at 325° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Add
all
ingredients together and bake at 325° to 350° until soft.
Yields 2 pies.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Saute mushrooms and onion in 3 tablespoons butter.
Set aside. Melt remaining butter; add flour and stir.
Add broth and cook until thickened.
Add spices, cream and sherry and cook for 10 minutes.
Cook vermicelli and drain.
Mix half of sauce with vermicelli and mushrooms.
Put into greased casserole.
Sprinkle with olives and chicken.
Pour remaining sauce over top and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: love letters
directions: Heat oven to 475°.
Measure flour by sifting.
Blend flour, sugar and salt.
Cut in butter and rinds until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Blend sour
cream in evenly.
Gather dough into firm ball.
Divide in half.
Roll on well floured board to 1/8-inch thickness.
Cut in 3 x 2-inch pieces; fold ends to center, overlapping slightly.
Seal with tiny piece of candied cherry. Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Brush tops with water; sprinkle with sugar.
Bake 6 to 8 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: never fail whipped cream frosting
directions: Mix together flour and milk.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Let cool.
Cream together butter, Crisco and sugar at high speed for 4 minutes.
Add cooled flour mixture and beat an additional 4 minutes.
Add vanilla and coloring if desired.
Mix thoroughly.

title: asian shrimp delights
directions: In bowl, combine shrimp, scallions, water chestnuts, wasabi-horseradish mayonnaise, cilantro, lime juice and salt. Cover with plastic wrap and chill.
Spoon shrimp mixture into phyllo shells. Garnish with cilantro, if desired.
Makes 15 servings.

title: easy stroganoff
directions: Brown steak in oil, add soups and 1 can of water.
Simmer 1 1/2 hours or until meat is tender.
Stir in sour cream and serve over cooked noodles.

title: green beans
directions: Mix ingredients and simmer 20 to 30 minutes.

title: oatmeal bars
directions: Mix flour, oatmeal, sugars, shortening or butter, eggs and vanilla together until moist.
Butter baking pan.
Spread dough in pan.
Bake at 350° until brown.
Cool; cut into squares and serve.

title: meat loaf
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients except hamburger; mix well.
Add hamburger; mix lightly but thoroughly.
Press into loaf pan.
Bake 1 hour.
Drain; let stand 5 minutes.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix last 6 ingredients together.
Add broccoli.
Pour in 2-quart casserole dish.
Crumble Ritz crackers over top.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 25 minutes.

title: taffy apple salad
directions: Drain pineapple and combine juice with sugar, flour and vinegar. Add egg and blend well. Cook and stir until thick.
Cool completely. Fold in peanuts, apple, pineapple and Cool Whip.

title: crescent cheese bars(easy and quick)
directions: Roll out 1 package of crescent rolls in 9 x 13-inch ungreased pan.
Cream cheese, egg yolk, vanilla and sugar.
Beat until creamy and pour over rolls in pan.
Place 2nd package of rolls on top.
Beat the egg white until foamy, not peaked.
Pour over, then sprinkle 1/4 cup sugar on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Blend all ingredients.
Use as dip for vegetables.

title: southern peach cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in baking dish.
Add sugar, milk and peaches; mix well.
Add flour; mix until well blended.
Bake in moderately hot oven (375°) until top is golden brown.
Serve with or without cream.

title: perfect chocolate cake
directions: Combine cocoa and water, stirring until smooth.
Combine butter, sugar, eggs and vanilla; beat at high speed 5 minutes until light and fluffy.
Combine dry ingredients.
Add to sugar mixture alternately with cocoa mixture, beating at low speed beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Do not overbeat.
Pour into 3 greased 9-inch pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: fruit bowl
directions: *Watermelon, cantaloupe, bananas, strawberries, grapes, peaches, nectarines can be used.

title: m.g.'s shortbread
directions: In a large bowl, let butter soften to room temperature.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add half the flour; mix by hand.
Add rest of flour and mix.
Form into smooth oblong ball.
Put in greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Push flat and evenly all over pan.
Poke billions of holes in dough with fork.
Push all the way through to pan.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes or until edge just gets tan.
Cut.
Cool. Remove from pan.

title: italian pot roast
directions: You will need 1 large cooking bag

title: chocolate nut bars
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine crumbs and margarine; press firmly on bottom of 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake 8 minutes. Reduce oven temperature to 350°.
In small saucepan, melt 1 cup chocolate chips with milk and vanilla.
Spread chocolate mixture over prepared crust.
Top with remaining 1 cup chocolate chips, then nuts; press down firmly.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool. Chill if desired.
Cut into bars.
Store loosely covered at room temperature.

title: cobbler
directions: Mix milk, flour and sugar together.
Melt butter in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour batter in the melted butter.
Pour fruit in middle.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until crust is brown.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour boiling water over oats and margarine.
Let stand 20 minutes.
Add sugars, eggs and vanilla.
Sift in remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: snow drift salad
directions: Cook water, pineapple and sugar together.
Pour over Jell-O. When cool, fold in cream and cottage cheese.
Chill.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix pretzels, oleo and 3 tablespoons sugar.
Line bottom of casserole (9 x
12-inch) with mixture and bake at 400° for 8 minutes.
Let cool
minutes.
Mix
jello,
water and strawberries.
Chill in
refrigerator
while pretzel mix cools. Mix cream cheese, sugar
and
Dream
Whip.
Spread on top of cooled pretzel mixture covering all edges.
Carefully spoon strawberry mixture on top and chill thoroughly.

title: family casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion; drain.
Add drained green beans and tomato soup; cover and simmer.
Cook noodles in water; drain. Combine meat mixture with noodles.

title: logan bread
directions: Mix together flours, oatmeal, brown sugar, honey, molasses and powdered milk.
Add eggs and rest of ingredients, stirring well. Pour into 4 (9 x 9-inch) greased cake pans and bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.
The bread is extremely rich and one piece is enough per meal.
It is an excellent winter camping bread as the high oil content prevents it from freezing like other breads.

title: cream puff cake
directions: Heat water and oleo to rolling boil.
Stir in flour; stir vigorously until mixture forms a ball.
Beat in eggs all at once. Grease a 13 x 9-inch cake pan.
Spread mixture on bottom and a little up sides.
Bake 35 minutes at 400°.
Let cool.

title: milk shake
directions: Place ice cream, milk and chocolate syrup or jam into a mixing bowl.
Beat with rotary egg beater or mixer until well blended. Pour in a cold glass to serve.
Makes 1 serving.

title: cherry sherbet
directions: In blender container, blend undrained cherries and undrained pineapple at medium speed until pureed.
Add remaining ingredients and blend until well combined.
Pour into a 13 x 9-inch baking pan. Cover with aluminum foil.
Freeze until frozen about 3 inches from edge, about 4 to 5 hours.

title: pepper cabbage
directions: Sprinkle salt over shredded cabbage and diced green peppers. Blend well.
Add sugar, vinegar and water.
Mix well and chill for 1 hour.
Mix well again and serve.

title: covered wagon
directions: Line loaf pan with bacon slices.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: dutch goose casserole
directions: Put 1/2 of
meat on bottom of baking dish.
(Canned hamburger is also good.)
Add
potatoes,
cabbage,
onion
and
seasoning. Top with remaining meat.
Add water.
Bake covered 1 1/2 hours in 350° oven.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions in salted water until tender.
Drain.
Arrange in a greased baking dish.
Layer chicken on top.
Combine mayo, soup and lemon juice in a bowl, then pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Cover with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: mexican fruit cake
directions: Mix together eggs, baking soda and pineapple.
Add flour, sugar and nuts. Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cook until done on 250°.

title: casey's chicken dried beef casserole
directions: Line Pyrex baking dish with slices of dried beef.
Wrap each piece of chicken in a strip of bacon and place on top of the dried beef.
Mix soup and sour cream; pour over chicken.
Cover tightly and bake at 350° for 3 hours.

title: one dish breakfast
directions: Place slices of bread in bottom of casserole dish.
Sprinkle cooked, crumbled sausage over bread, then sprinkle cheese over sausage.
Mix well beaten eggs with half and half.
Pour over mixture.
Bake for approximately 30 minutes at 375°.
Remove and serve immediately.
Enjoy with hot coffee.

title: caramel pie
directions: In a large pot, place the Eagle Brand milk (remove labels). Cover the cans of milk with water.
Bring to boil and boil at a steady boil for 3 hours.
May have to add water during cooking time.
When 3 hours are up, drain hot water off of cans and replace with cold.
Let milk cool off.
Open cans and stir milk up smooth. Pour into pie crust.
Place in fridge; let chill well.
Place Cool Whip on top of caramel.
May add chopped nuts or drizzle chocolate syrup to dress it up.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Heat potatoes in juice until near boiling.
Drain and place in mixer bowl.
Beat until creamy.
Add margarine, sugar, pudding (dry) and raisins; beat well.
Pour in casserole dish, cover.
Top with marshmallows and bake until golden brown.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Combine bread crumbs, cheese, salt and pepper.
Dip the chicken breast in melted butter and then in bread crumbs, being careful to coat breasts evenly.
Place breasts in a baking dish and bake for 30 to 35 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: walnut yogurt ring
directions: Cream butter with 3/4 cup sugar until light and fluffy.
Beat in eggs, 1 at a time, until blended.
Stir in yogurt, lemon peel and vanilla.
Sift flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt together.
Add to creamed mixture, stirring until smooth.
Add 3/4 cup walnuts.
Turn half of the batter into a greased, floured 9-inch tube pan.

title: s'mores
directions: Grease a pan.
Heat corn syrup, butter and chocolate chips to a boil; remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour over cereal in large bowl; stir until completely covered.
Fold in marshmallows, one cup at a time.
Press mixture into pan.
Let stand 1 hour. Cut into squares.

title: hot cheese loaf
directions: Slice top off loaf and remove bread from center.
Combine all ingredients and fill hollowed loaf.
Put top slice on loaf and wrap in foil.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 325°.
Serve with Fritos scoops.

title: santa's thumbprints
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Beat Crisco and sugar until fluffy.
Beat in egg and vanilla.
Add combined oats, flour and salt; mix well. Form 1-inch balls; roll in nuts.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased baking sheet; press centers with thumb or paw.
Fill with preserves.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes or until golden brown. Remove to wire rack.
Cool completely.

title: floyd's golden grill barbecue sauce
directions: Mix ingredients and bring to a boil. Let set overnight.

When ready to use heat sauce and keep hot (not boiling) while basting chicken. ( If desired you may marinate chicken with the hot sauce for about an hour before cooking. ) Place chickens over coals and baste frequently turning as needed. Cooks chicken to a golden brown color. (No tomato in the ingredients to burn.) Makes enough for 8 to 10 chicken halves. GOD BLESS!
GOOD LUCK!
AND GOOD COOKIN'!!!

title: peach salad
directions: Heat pineapple and juice; then pour gelatin and dissolve. Cool in refrigerator until slightly congealed.
Add buttermilk and congeal more.
Add nuts and Cool Whip.
Blend well and congeal.

title: ham and cheese muffins
directions: Mix ingredients in order.
Spoon into well greased muffin tins.
Bake at 425 degrees for 15 minutes.
Serve immediately.

title: baked cauliflower
directions: Cook whole cauliflower in boiling water until tender, 15 minutes.
Cook bacon, remove and crumble; set aside.
Add onion to 2 tablespoons bacon drippings.
Cook until tender.
Stir in soup and milk; add cheese.
Place drained, cooked cauliflower in 1-quart casserole.
Pour sauce on top.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Garnish with reserved bacon.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: cranberry raisin pie
directions: Mix sugar, water, flour and then raisins.
Beat smooth and stir in remaining ingredients.
Put into an unbaked pie shell and cover with a lattice top.
Bake in a 425° oven for 10 minutes. Reduce heat to 350° and bake 30 to 40 minutes longer.

title: shake and bake
directions: Thoroughly mix all ingredients in a bowl.
Pour into a jar with a lid and store on a shelf or in the refrigerator.
Use as needed for breading meat or poultry.

title: chopped beef ball
directions: Mix all together into a ball.

title: play dough recipe
directions: Mix dry ingredients; add liquid.
Mix well and knead.
Store in tightly closed container.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Place in tightly covered container overnight.

title: no-bake fudge cookies
directions: Mix cocoa,
margarine, sugar and milk.
Boil one minute. Remove from heat.
Add oatmeal, butter and vanilla.
Stir until oats are covered.
Drop by teaspoon onto wax paper.
Cool.

title: chocolate cream dessert
directions: Prepare chocolate pudding as directed on package, using 3 cups of milk.
When cooled, spread over cream cheese layer.

title: hershey bar pie
directions: Melt candy in top of double boiler.
Cool for a while (just a few minutes when set in cold water) and stir in Cool Whip.
Pour into pie shell and chill.
(I use a package of slivered almonds, toasted, and put a few extra in the pie; garnish the top with them, too. Place them around edge of pie, making about a 1-inch border.)

title: banana split pie
directions: Melt sugar, beaten eggs and butter on stove top until creamy. Pour into pie shells.
Slice bananas on top.
Spread with drained crushed pineapple.
Spread whipped topping over all and chill.

title: glaze orange
directions: Combine sugar, butter and orange rind.
Blend in cream and beat until of spreading consistency.

title: 7-up - lime jello salad
directions: Mix softened cheese and Jell-O together thoroughly.
Heat the pineapple until it boils, then mix with the cheese and Jell-O mixture.
Add the 7-Up and mix well, then place in refrigerator to gel.
(If you are in a hurry, you may place in the freezer for a while.)

title: lemon brownies
directions: Melt the butter and mix powdered sugar and flour.
Pat into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: calico beans
directions: Brown beef, bacon and onion.
Drain fat.
Add rest of ingredients.
Bake at 300° for 3 hours, covered.

title: caramel frosting
directions: Cook brown sugar and milk over medium
heat to the soft ball stage (230°).
Remove from stove and add cream of tartar. Stir very little to blend the cream
of tartar.
Set aside and cool to lukewarm.
Beat until it thickens to frost cake.

title: fried oyster patties
directions: In bowl, beat eggs well.
Add flour, preferably with a whisk, a small amount at a time.
Mix in oil, salt and pepper.
Gently stir in oysters with the juice.
Heat margarine and shortening in skillet.
Spoon batter into pan for patties.
Fry, like fritters, over moderate heat.
Remove and keep warm on absorbent paper until ready to serve.
Makes at least 1 dozen patties.

title: lazy day lasagna
directions: Layer in this order (everything uncooked), lasagna noodles, 1/2 pound hamburger, cottage cheese or Ricotta, onion, pepper, mushrooms, Mozzarella cheese and 1/2 jar spaghetti sauce.
Repeat these steps again.
*Cover pan with foil.
Bake at 350° for 90 minutes.
Let stand for 10 minutes.

title: broccoli-rice seafood casserole
directions: Steam broccoli; set aside (chop when cool).
Saute onions, bell pepper and seafood in margarine.
Add Cheez Whiz; stir while adding cream of mushroom soup.
Add chopped broccoli and rice. Stir well.
Spread into baking pan; sprinkle bread crumbs over top.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: fruit cake cookies
directions: Cream oleo, sugar and vanilla.
Add eggs and beat.
Mix dry ingredients.
Mix all fruit and nuts together.
Pour part of the dry ingredients over the nuts.
Pour cream mixture into nuts and fruit.
Dissolve soda in water; pour over mixture.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes.

title: poppy seed muffins
directions: Combine sugar, margarine and eggs until creamy.
Blend in baking powder, salt, nutmeg, milk and poppy seed.
Fold in flour until moistened.
Bake at 400° for 18 to 20 minutes in greased muffin tins.

title: southern fried oysters
directions: Drain oysters.
Coat them with cracker meal.
Dip each oyster in egg and water mixture.
Have another dish of cracker meal mixed with the salt and baking powder.
Dip oysters in this and fry in deep fat, about 5 minutes or less. (These are light and wonderful.)

title: fried salmon patties
directions: Roll
crackers until fine.
Mix with other ingredients. Drop by tablespoons and fry with butter.

title: chipped beef dip
directions: Blend cream cheese until softened.
Add sour cream and Miracle Whip; blend until well mixed.
Add garlic powder; fold in chopped chipped beef and dill pickles.

title: cheese and ham snacks
directions: Remove crusts from bread.
Butter one side of bread.
Cut into quarters.
Press carefully into miniature muffin tins, butter side down.
Put deviled ham, sour cream and a small piece of cheese into bread cups.
Heat in a 325° oven until cheese is melted.
Serve hot with drinks.
Yield:
Depends on number of muffin tins you own.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix first two ingredients. Then add next four.

title: berry good lemon tarts
directions: Combine egg yolks, sugar and lemon juice in a heavy saucepan, stirring until blended. Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, 5 minutes or until mixture thickens.
Remove from heat and stir in butter and lemon rind.
Let cool and spoon evenly onto prepared puff pastries or tart shells. Cover and chill thoroughly.
Garnish with whipped cream, blueberries, blackberries or strawberries. Fills 24 small tart shells.

title: egg custard pie
directions: Melt margarine in milk over low heat.
Add sugar to beaten eggs and add vanilla.
Pour into milk mixture while it is still over heat; mix well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes; reduce heat to 325° for 20 minutes or until custard is done but still "jiggly".

title: anna belle's cake
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, baking powder and flour together, then take milk and butter and heat to boiling point.
Add this to first mixture.
Add vanilla and bake.
Put into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Frost with Broiled Frosting.

title: marinated veg. salad
directions: Combine choice of leftover, canned or frozen vegetables.
I prefer green beans, yellow beans and kidney beans.
Corn, frozen peas (thawed), fresh diced carrots may also be added. Diced seeded tomatoes are also nice.
Add one chopped onion and chopped green pepper. Best marinated overnight.

title: molasses teething biscuits
directions: Combine.
Roll out thinly.
Cut into finger length sticks. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Boil squash and onion until tender.
Drain well and mix with cheese and chiles.
Pour into buttered baking dish.
Bake 15 minutes at 375°.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: Heat soup and cheese together in double boiler until cheese is melted.
Add milk and mushrooms to mixture.
Cook noodles (or macaroni); drain well.
Mix noodles into mushroom soup mixture and add corned beef.
Place in greased casserole.
Cover with seasoned bread crumbs, browned in butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: broccoli cauliflower salad
directions: Clean broccoli and break into small pieces. Clean cauliflower and break into small pieces. Fry bacon until good and crispy. Lay on paper towel and pat off excess grease. Crumble.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until foamy.
Add oil, sugar, zucchini and vanilla; mix lightly.
Add remaining ingredients; mix until blended.
Pour into 2 loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: easy apple dumplings
directions: Put
margarine,
sugar,
cinnamon and 7-Up in saucepan. Bring to	a
boil.
Pat out biscuits in hand or with a rolling pin. Fill
with chopped apples.	Pinch together.
Put pinched side down in pan.
Pour syrup over all and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: ben's favorite cornbread(club member: ben steadman)
directions: Melt butter in cast-iron skillet.
Mix cornmeal, flour, egg and buttermilk together.
Add butter, but leave small amount of butter in skillet.
Pour mixture into heated skillet and bake for 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: sock it to me cake
directions: Mix chopped pecans, cinnamon and brown sugar.
After you have mixed cake mix, sour cream, Wesson oil, sugar and eggs, pour half of batter into a greased tube pan.
Sprinkle nut mixture on cake, then pour balance of batter over nut mixture.
Bake at 375° for approximately 45 to 55 minutes.
Cool cake in pan for 25 minutes. Put on plate.
Glaze.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix by hand Crisco oil, eggs, sugar and vanilla.
Add flour and cinnamon.
Mix good by hand.
Add apples and nuts or raisins. Grease and flour Bundt pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours (in my oven, 1 hour and 5 minutes).

title: lemon pie
directions: In a saucepan, combine sugar, cornstarch and lemon juice.
Mix well.
