Add beaten egg yolks, milk and melted butter.
Cook until it comes to a boil and becomes thick.
Remove from heat; add a little lemon rind.
Pour into pie shell.
Cover with meringue. Bake until browned.
Also good in a graham cracker shell.

title: banana surprise
directions: Slice Twinkies oblong.
Place in the bottom of an oblong dish or cake pan.
Slice bananas on top of that.
Mix pudding as directed and spread on top of the bananas.
Spread Cool Whip on top of the pudding.
Refrigerate for a couple of hours before serving. Serves 15.

title: italian party mix
directions: Place butter in a 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish; microwave, uncovered, at High for 50 seconds or until melted.
Stir in salad dressing mix and next 3 ingredients.
Add cereal, pretzel sticks and nuts to butter mixture; toss gently.
Microwave, uncovered, at High for 4 to 5 minutes or until thoroughly heated, stirring after 2 minutes.
Let cool; store in airtight container.
Yields 8 cups.

title: mandarin salad
directions: Cook almonds and sugar together over low heat. Stir constantly until almonds are coated. Cool and break apart.
Put lettuce, romaine, celery and onions in plastic bag.
Drain mandarin oranges. Add Sweet-Sour Dressing.
Add orange segments to plastic bag. Close bag and shake until everything is coated. Add almonds. Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: danish pastry apple bars
directions: Combine flour and salt; cut in margarine and butter.
Beat egg yolk in measuring cup; add enough milk to make 2/3 cup liquid. Mix well.
Stir into flour.
Roll half of dough into jelly roll pan.
Sprinkle cold cereal on dough.
Top with apples; sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.
Roll out remaining dough to fit top. Seal edges.
Beat egg whites until frothy; brush over top of dough.
Bake until golden brown.
Glaze warm bars with powdered sugar, milk and vanilla mixture.

title: lo-cal salad dressing
directions: Blend by shaking in a jar and letting stand for several hours before use. Always shake before using. For extra tang, add 1 teaspoon of Dijon mustard. Contains 33 calories per tablespoon.

title: spaghetti casserole
directions: Layer half of cooked spaghetti in pan.
Combine hamburger and spaghetti sauce.
Spread one can of cream of mushroom carefully over spaghetti.
Spoon half of hamburger mixture over soup.
Place half of olives over this if desired.
Sprinkle half of both cheeses and repeat layers.
Cover with foil that has been sprayed with Pam so it doesn't stick to cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Combine sugar, corn syrup, peanuts and salt in a 1 1/2-quart microwavable dish.
Microwave on High for 8 minutes, stirring once after 4 minutes.
Stir in butter and vanilla; microwave 2 minutes more.
Stir in soda and pour on greased baking sheet, pulling until thin.
Cool.
Break into pieces.
Makes 1/4 pound.

title: cheese bread
directions: In a large bowl, combine 1 1/2 cups flour and yeast.
Heat cheese, water, sugar and salt just until warm, stirring constantly. Add to flour mixture and add egg.
Beat with electric mixer on low for 1/2 minute, scraping bowl. Beat 3 minutes on high.
Stir in as much of the 2 to 2 1/2 cups flour as you can mix with a spoon.

On a floured surface, knead in enough of the remaining all-purpose flour to make a moderately stiff dough that is smooth and elastic. Shape into a ball in a greased bowl. Turn once, cover and let rise in a warm place until double.

title: cranberry apple salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water; add cranberry sauce.
Chill until partly set; add other ingredients.
Chill.
Serves 6 to 8. Good with turkey or chicken.

title: skillet chicken supper
directions: In a paper bag, combine flour, salt and paprika.
Add chicken a few pieces at a time to coat.
In 10-inch or larger skillet melt margarine and brown all chicken pieces.
Push to side of skillet and add vegetables, salt and pepper to taste.
Cover all with soup.
Simmer 40 to 50 minutes until chicken is done and vegetables are tender.
Remove from skillet and add sour cream to soup mixture to make gravy.

title: hamburg potato bake
directions: Brown meat and onion lightly.
Grease casserole.
Place layer of potatoes and sprinkle with salt and pepper; then layer of meat and repeat.
Pour heated soup over top and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for about one hour or until potatoes are done.
Can also be done at 225° for 2 to 3 hours.

title: plum cake
directions: Mix ingredients. Pour into Bundt pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: onion quiche(delicious for a brunch or to serve new year's eve)
directions: Cook onion in 1/4 cup butter until tender but not brown. Place in unbaked pie crust.
Combine cheese with flour and pepper; add eggs and milk.
Pour over onions.
Bake at 375° for about 35 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.
Serve in wedges or squares.

title: my way chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Spray cookie sheet with cooking spray. In a large bowl and using electric beater, cream margarine.
Add sugars and beat until light and fluffy.
Beat in egg and vanilla.

title: hot rolls
directions: Dissolve
yeast
in
water.
Add sugar, salt and 1/2 of the flour.
Beat
thoroughly for 2 minutes, then add eggs and shortening.
Gradually
beat
in remaining flour until smooth. Let rise
until
double.
Make
into rolls and let rise until double. Bake at 400° for about 20 minutes.

title: cheese zucchini crisps
directions: Combine cornflake crumbs, cheese and seasonings; place in plastic bag.
Dip zucchini strips in butter, then shake in bag of crumbs to coat.
Place on baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for about 10 minutes.
Yields 4 servings.

title: white lemon pecan fruit cake
directions: Cream
the butter.
Add sugar, then egg yolks, one at a time, and beat well.
Gradually
add
2 cups of flour with the baking powder.
Use other 2
cups of flour to dredge fruit and nuts.
Add lemon flavoring,
then fruit.
Fold in by hand with beaten egg whites.
Let stand overnight in refrigerator.
Next morning, put in pan and bake in a slow oven (250°) from 2 to 3 hours (nearer 3 hours).
Makes 1 angel cake pan.

title: marinated sliced tomatoes
directions: Place tomatoes in an 11 x 7 x 1 1/2 inch dish.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over tomatoes.
Cover and chill. Serves 10 to 12.

title: wesley's chocolate chip cookies
directions: Blend oats in blender to a fine powder.
In
a large bowl with mixer, cream the butter and both sugars until light and fluffy. Beat in eggs and vanilla.
In another bowl, combine oatmeal powder, flour, salt, baking powder and baking soda.
Add oat mixture to butter mixture; beat just until blended.
With wooden spoon, stir in chocolate and nuts or raisins.
Roll dough by rounded tablespoonful into balls.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 350°.

title: frozen cranberry salad
directions: Wash and drain dandelion leaves.
Mix oil, vinegar, garlic, salt and pepper in a small bowl.
Pour over dandelion leaves in small bowl, tossing to coat leaves.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: sausage balls
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles in salted boiling water for 10 minutes; drain. Cook onions and pepper in butter until tender.
Add to noodles. Add soup, diluted with 1/2 cup water.
Flake tuna in large pieces and fold into noodles.
Pour 1/2 of mixture into casserole dish. Cover with a layer of cheese.
Put on remaining noodle mixture. Top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: aunt d's coleslaw
directions: Mix the dressing the night before you intend to use it.
Mix the coleslaw and dressing together before the meal.
The coleslaw looks dry at first, but do not be fooled.
There is plenty of dressing.
This recipe doubles really well for 2 pounds of coleslaw.
Enjoy.

title: shrimp - rice salad
directions: Garnish with tomato wedges.

title: hot spiced tea
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together.
Store in airtight container.
To use, measure 1 teaspoon per cup.
One quart serves 6.
Use 1/3 cup dry mix to one quart of boiling water.

title: rack of lamb
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place lamb on a rack in a greased large roasting pan; brush with mustard.
In a small bowl, combine the bread crumbs, parsley, salt and pepper.
Press onto the meat. Combine butter and garlic; drizzle over the meat.
Bake, uncovered for 35 to 40 minutes or until meat reach desired doneness.
Yield: 8 servings.

title: cinnamon twist
directions: Combine sugar and cinnamon.
Roll biscuits into 9-inch rope. Bring ends together and pinch to seal.
Dip in melted margarine. Coat with sugar mixture.
Twist into a figure eight.
Put on greased baking sheet.
Sprinkle with walnuts.
Bake in preheated oven for 10 to 12 minutes or until done at 400°.
Dough may be twisted into hearts, shamrock or Christmas designs, if desired.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly and pour into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350°
for 45 minutes.

title: cream puffs
directions: Combine water, shortening and salt.
Bring to boil.
Reduce to low heat and add flour.
Beat until mixture forms a smooth, compact ball and cleans sides of pan.
Remove from heat and beat in eggs thoroughly, one at a time.
Beat mixture until smooth and velvety. Drop by spoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for about 40 minutes or until golden brown and almost dry.
Serve with whipped topping made from nonfat dry milk and flavored with vanilla.

title: cream cheese bars
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar, butter and vanilla together.
Spread 1 package crescent rolls out in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread mixture over rolls.
Put second package of crescent rolls on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: tropical chicken salad
directions: Boil chicken.
Use broth to make soup.
Dice chicken and add remaining ingredients.
Refrigerate 1 hour or overnight.
Hard rolls recommended.

title: pork chops with apricot stuffing
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Reserve 4 mushrooms for garnish.
Slice remainder.
Saute mushrooms, onion and celery in 1/4 cup butter until tender.
Reserve 4 apricots; chop remainder and add to mushroom mixture along with bread crumbs, sage and parsley; set aside.

title: party salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Drain pineapple and reserve 1/2 cup of syrup; add reserved syrup to jello.
Chill until it starts to set.
Fold in rest of ingredients.
Chill until firm in 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.

title: shortcake
directions: Mix and put in a 9 x 12-inch greased and floured pan.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: kosher crock dill pickles
directions: Stir until salt is dissolved.
For a 2-gallon crock triple brine recipe.

title: hungarian beef stew
directions: Cut meat into 1-inch chunks.
In 5-quart Dutch oven over medium heat in hot butter, cook onions until lightly brown.
Add meat, paprika and salt.
Reduce heat to low. Cover and simmer 1 1/2 to 2 hours until meat is fork-tender. Stir in sour cream. Heat through (do not boil).
Serve over noodles.

title: lemon tea
directions: Start with fresh cold water.
Bring water to a boil in a nonreactive saucepan.
Add tea bags and steep for 7 minutes. Remove tea bags.
Add sugar, stirring to dissolve.
Add lemon juice while tea is still warm.
Pour into pitcher.
Add the cold water.
Cover and chill.
Serve over ice.

title: borscht(russian beef, vegetable soup)
directions: Boil beef in a large stockpot.
Add bay leaf.
Boil beef until tender (approximately 1/2 hour).
Skim foam that develops and discard.
In the beef broth, add carrots, onion, celery, beets and bell pepper.
Boil until beets are nearly white.
Add potatoes and tomato sauce.
After the potatoes are tender, add the cabbage and parsley.
Boil until cabbage is tender.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease a shallow 2-quart baking dish.
Mix chicken and vegetables and layer in bottom of dish.
Pour soup, salt and pepper over chicken.
Combine baking mix, milk and butter. Pour over top of chicken and soup.
Bake for 45 minutes or until brown.

title: three cheese brunch
directions: Mix together and bake in greased 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for approximately 40 minutes.
Can also use a big sheet pan.

title: never fail sugar cookies
directions: Mix dry ingredients as for pie and cut in shortening.
Add other ingredients and roll thinly.
Cut.
Bake on cookie sheet at 375° until golden brown.

title: rice pudding with raspberry sauce
directions: Heat sugar, water, gelatin and salt in a 2-quart saucepan, stirring constantly, until gelatin is dissolved, about 1 minute. Stir in milk, rice and vanilla.
Place saucepan in bowl of iced water, stirring occasionally, until mixture mounds slightly when dropped from a spoon, about 10 minutes.
Beat whipping cream in a chilled bowl until stiff.
Fold whipped cream into rice mixture. Pour into ungreased 6 cup mold or serving bowl.
Cover and refrigerate until firm, about 3 hours.
Unmold by dipping briefly in warm water and loosening edge with spatula; invert on serving plate.
Serve with Raspberry Sauce.

title: date bars
directions: Beat eggs yolks with sugar, stir until creamy.
Mix flour, baking powder and salt; then add nuts and dates.
Then beat egg whites stiff and add alternately with other ingredients.
Bake in a flat pan for 30 minutes in slow oven at 350°.
When cool, cut into squares.

title: primer's hot sauce
directions: Blend together ingredients in food processor until preferred consistency.
Store in refrigerator.

title: blue cheese bites
directions: Place the biscuit quarters into 2 (8-inch) round baking dishes.
Melt together the margarine and Blue cheese (can also use Parmesan).
Pour mixture over biscuit pieces, coating all good. Bake at 400° for 15 minutes, until golden brown.

title: dark cherry salad
directions: Add 1 cup hot boiling water to jello.
Stir good.
Add 1 cup cold water.
Stir good so jello will dissolve.
Let set until almost congealed.
Add 1 cup sweet dark cherries, pecans and Cool Whip.
Mix well.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: monster cookies
directions: Coconut and/or chocolate chips may be used in addition to, or instead of, M&M's and nuts.

title: fabulous funnel cakes
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Add combined milk and egg, mixing until smooth.
Holding finger over opening, fill 3/8 to 1/2-inch funnel with 1/4 cup batter.
Place funnel near oil; remove finger and pour batter into 1-inch of hot oil, using circular motion to form 4-inch spiral.
Fry until golden brown, turning once; drain on paper towel.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Serve warm.

title: squash supreme
directions: Put squash and onions in 2-quart saucepan with enough water to cover.
Boil until tender; drain and mash.
Add other ingredients and mix well.
Pour into well-buttered 2-quart casserole dish and bake 40 minutes at 375°.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: fruit filling for pie(diabetic)
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Mix all ingredients together and place in pie crust.
Bake until fruit is tender, about 45 minutes.
If a two-crust pie is desired, cover unbaked pie with second crust. Cut air vents in top and flute edges.
Cover fluted edges with foil to prevent excessive browning (remove foil after 30 minutes). Bake as before.

title: sour cream banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding according to package.
Add sour cream and Cool Whip and stir thoroughly.
Layer bottom of dish with wafers, then add a layer of sliced bananas and pudding mixture.
Repeat layers and allow to cool before serving.

title: turkey soup
directions: Boil carcass or chicken until meat falls away from bones. Strain and save liquid.
Cut meat into bite size pieces and place back in liquid.
Add other ingredients; bring to a boil, then let simmer for at least 2 hours.
Stir occasionally to keep corn from sticking.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: chocolate chocolate chocolate cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together; pour in a greased and floured Bundt cake pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: elephant ears
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/4 cup warm water; let stand 5 minutes. Combine flour, 1 1/2 tablespoons sugar and salt in
a large bowl. Cut 1 cup butter into flour mixture with a pastry blender until a coarse meal.
Combine milk, egg yolk and yeast mixture; add to flour mixture.
Chill 2 hours.
Turn dough onto a floured surface; knead 1 to 2 minutes.
Cover and let rest 10 minutes.
Roll dough into an 18 x 10-inch rectangle on a lightly floured surface; brush with 2 tablespoons melted butter.
Combine 2 cups sugar and cinnamon; sprinkle 1 cup of mixture over dough.
Roll up jelly roll fashion, starting at long side; pinch long edge (do not seal ends).
Place roll, seam side down, and cut into 18 (1-inch) slices.
Sprinkle a portion of remaining cinnamon-sugar mixture lightly over waxed paper.
Roll each slice out to 1/8-inch thickness, turning over once.
Carefully transfer slices to an ungreased baking sheet.
Spread each pastry with remaining melted butter; sprinkle with remaining cinnamon-sugar mixture and pecans. Bake at 400° for 10 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool on wire racks.

title: banana bran muffins
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Stir in bran.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Add all at once to flour mixture, stirring just to moisten.
Fill greased muffin pans 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes about 10 muffins.

title: mary b's cheese cupcakes
directions: Mix first four ingredients together until smooth.
Take 1 vanilla wafer cookie and place, rounded side down, in cupcake paper and fill 3/4 full with cheese mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cupcakes will rise then fall in middle.
Cover with cherry pie filling.

title: spaghetti saladeverton, missouri
directions: Combine all ingredients and refrigerate overnight.
You may add other vegetables.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onion in oleo about 5 minutes.
Add rice, salt, water and mushrooms.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Cook frozen vegetables until done, not soft.
Put in big casserole.
Heat soup and Cheez Whiz until melted.
Combine all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes uncovered.
Can put onion rings on top.
(Can eliminate rice.)

title: indian pudding
directions: Gradually add cornmeal to scalded milk, stirring constantly and continue to cook in double boiler for 20 minutes.
Add all the other ingredients and turn into buttered baking dish.
Pour 1 cup cold milk over top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve with Cool Whip or vanilla ice cream.

title: crock-pot beans
directions: Brown and drain sausage.
Crumble.
Add all other ingredients. Place in crock-pot on low 10 to 12 hours.

title: peach pie
directions: Cut bread into strips.
Mix remainder of ingredients together.
Pour on top of bread.
Bake at 350° until brown and crispy.
I use a long Pyrex.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients thoroughly and cook on low heat until smooth and thick.
Cool.
Add whipped topping.
Serve on a tray with an assortment of fruits (grapes, apples, oranges, pineapple chunks, cherry, strawberry, pear, etc.).
Yields 2 cups dip.

title: **molasses crinkles
directions: Mix first four ingredients.
Sift together remaining ingredients and stir in.
Let stand overnight in refrigerator. Roll in small balls, dip in sugar and sprinkle a few drops of water on top.
Bake in hot oven at 375° about 10 to 12 minutes.

title: basic brown soup stock
directions: Place bare bones in a roasting pan, and roast at 425°, without lid, for 2 hours.
Place the roasted bones in a large soup pot. Add unpeeled vegetables: chopped celery, yellow onions and carrots.
(Yellow onion skins give color to stock.)
Bring to heavy simmer and cook for 8 hours.
Strain stock and store.

title: sausage bread
directions: Brown sausage.
Add large jar of olives, Colby cheese, Mozzarella cheese and green onions; set aside.
Roll each dough loaf into rectangle; spread with filling, then sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Roll like jelly roll and bake at 400° for 15 minutes with seam side down.
Makes 3 loaves.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Combine the flour, cream of tartar, baking soda and salt and sift again.
Set aside.
Cream the butter and sugar until fluffy, about 3 minutes.
Add the eggs, 1 at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add the flour mixture in 4 parts and beat thoroughly, after adding each part.
Wrap dough in plastic wrap and refrigerate for at least 1 hour.
Preheat oven to 400°.
Roll dough into balls about the size of a walnut, then roll each in the sugar-cinnamon mixture.
Place about 2 inches apart on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for about 8 to 10 minutes, or until just lightly browned, but still soft.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: cavatini
directions: Brown hamburger; drain.
Add onion and green pepper.
Cook until tender.
Add pepperoni and mushrooms; set aside.
Cook macaroni; drain.
Add spaghetti sauce to hamburger mixture.
Place half the macaroni in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Then use half of each ingredient at a time.
Layer the hamburger, Mozzarella cheese, the Provolone cheese and repeat layers.
Top with Parmesan.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: waffle brownies
directions: Turn waffle iron to medium heat. Cream chocolate, butter, eggs and sugar.
Mix in flour, vanilla and nuts.
Place by teaspoonfuls on waffle iron. Cook 3 minutes.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Cook and drain macaroni. Place in casserole dish sprayed with Pam.
Add tuna, soup, cheese and peas (if included).
Microwave at Medium setting for 30 minutes.
May place potato chips on top before cooking.

title: mulled cider
directions: Put cider, lemon juice, lemon slices, sugar, molasses, cinnamon stick, cloves and allspice in medium saucepan.
Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring occasionally, until sugar dissolves.
Reduce heat to low and simmer 5 minutes.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Stir together sugar and syrup in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Cook 4 minutes on High.
Add peanuts; cook 3 more minutes.
Add butter and vanilla; stir well.
Cook 1 to 2 minutes until peanuts are brown and syrup is hot.
Add baking soda and mix until foamy. (The longer you stir, the darker the candy will get.)
Spread evenly on greased baking sheet.
Cool for 1/2 hour.

title: corn bread
directions: Place corn meal in mixing bowl.
Add onions, corn, eggs, oil, salt and milk.
Mix well and pour in well greased pan.
Bake in 400° oven about 40 minutes or until golden brown.

title: pickled whole hot peppers
directions: Wash peppers.
Cut 2 to 4 small slits in each hot pepper. Blanch hot peppers in boiling water for 3 minutes.
Immediately cool in ice water.
Drain well.
Lightly flatten hot peppers with a wooden spoon.
In a 3-quart saucepan, combine vinegar and remaining ingredients except garlic.
Bring to boil over medium-high heat. Boil for 5 minutes.
Place one clove of garlic in each hot pint jar.
Firmly pack peppers into jars, leaving 1/2-inch headspace. Immediately pour hot vinegar mixture over peppers, leaving 1/2-inch headspace.
Carefully run a non-metallic utensil down inside of jars to remove trapped air bubbles.
Wipe jar tops and threads clean.
Place hot lids on jars and screw bands on firmly.
Process in boiling water canner for 10 minutes.
Makes about 4 to 5 pints.

title: hot mexican cornbread
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Add milk and eggs.
Mix well. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Bake in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: diabetic oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together and add remaining ingredients.
Mix again.
Then bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Let cool, then put icing on cookies.

title: easy dumplings
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Beat egg until foamy and add milk.
Mix with flour mixture.
Drop by spoonfuls into broth.
Cover and steam for 15 minutes without lifting the lid.

title: crab meat au gratin
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt 4 tablespoons margarine in a medium sized pan.
Saute onion, green onions and parsley until onions are clear.
Stir in garlic, crab meat, salt and hot sauce. Reduce heat to low.
In separate pan, melt 2 tablespoons margarine.
Add flour and stir until brown.
Slowly stir in liquid and stir until thickened.
Add half of the Cheddar cheese.
Stir until melted.
Pour into crab mixture.
Turn into small greased casserole dish and top with Mozzarella and remaining Cheddar cheese.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes until all the cheese is melted and browned around the edges.

title: baked meatballs
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix all the ingredients thoroughly and shape the mixture into 1-inch balls.
(Use a small ice cream scoop if you have one.
It's a timesaver and it makes meatballs of uniform size.)
Place the meatballs in an ungreased jelly roll pan (15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inches).
Bake 10 minutes or until done. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: jim's oatmeal candy
directions: Mix all ingredients in cooker.
Boil 5 minutes. Remove from heat and add 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Stir in oats.
Drop by spoonful onto aluminum foil.

title: german green beans
directions: In large saucepan, fry bacon until almost done.
Add onion and fry until golden, about 5 minutes.
Add flour; blend in thoroughly.
Stir in sugar, vinegar and liquid from one can of beans.
Bring to boiling.
Discard liquid from remaining can of beans.
Add beans to pan; reduce heat and simmer until beans are heated through.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: russian tea
directions: Simmer fruit rinds, cinnamon and cloves in 2 quarts water slowly for approximately 20 to 25 minutes.
Strain and add to tea and fruit juices.
Add 2 1/2 to 3 cups of sugar to suit taste. Makes enough for 25.

title: kropsua
directions: Mix all together.
Pour 1/2 of mixture into a square pan. Bake 1/2 hour at 400°.
Sprinkle with sugar or syrup.
Makes 2.

title: 7-minute tuna casserole
directions: Combine 1/2 can of onion rings with other ingredients and place in greased casserole.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Sprinkle remaining rings on top.
Bake 5 minutes longer.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: peanut chews
directions: Cream sugar and margarine.
Add egg yolks and beat.
Add vanilla.
Mix together dry ingredients and add to sugar mixture; mix well.
Spoon mixture into an ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pat dough evenly over pan.
Bake for 12 to 15 minutes at 350°.
Do not overbake or the crust will crumble.
Remove from oven and cover with miniature marshmallows.
Return to oven for 1 or 2 minutes or until marshmallows are puffed. Do not melt marshmallows.
Remove from oven and cool while mixing corn syrup, vanilla, margarine and butterscotch morsels.
Melt over low heat.
Add peanuts and mix well.
Pour evenly over marshmallows.
Cool.
Place in refrigerator for an hour or two.
Remove and let sit at room temperature for several hours.

title: apple cobbler
directions: Sift the 2 cups flour and salt; add shortening (if it's lard, only use 1/2 cup; if vegetable shortening, use 2/3 cup). Mix up into size of split peas with 2 knives or pastry cutter. Add water slowly by teaspoons. Mix lightly until dough forms. Put layer of dough in bottom of bowl. Save enough dough to put on top.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine and put in a buttered casserole.

title: pea salad
directions: Combine vinegar, oil, pepper, salt and marinate peas, cucumbers and onions in this mixture.
Chill and serve on lettuce. Serves 6.
Contains 65 calories per serving.

title: yellow cake - best ever
directions: Cream sugar and butter until smooth.
Add eggs, one at a time, alternating with flour mixture (flour, baking powder and salt mixed together) and milk.
Add vanilla and butter.
Beat on medium speed until smooth.
Pour into 2 greased and floured cake pans.
Bake at 350° to 370° for 45 to 50 minutes or until cake is done with toothpick test.

title: asparagus roll-ups
directions: Combine cream cheese and Bleu cheese.
Spread on slice of white bread which has been rolled to flatten and trimmed of crust. Place cooked asparagus spear near edge of bread and roll jelly roll fashion.
Brush with melted butter.
Cut in half.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes at 375°.
Makes 16 pieces.

title: millionaire pie
directions: Cream together first five ingredients.
Pour evenly into pie crusts.
Mix Cool Whip, pineapple and pecans together.
Pour evenly into pie crusts (on top of creamed mixture).
Refrigerate until served.

title: turkey enchiladas
directions: Saute onion and garlic in 1/4 cup of the chicken broth.
Stir in turkey, chiles and oregano.
Heat thoroughly.
Set aside.
In saucepan, melt the butter.
Stir in flour.
Cook for 1 minute. Gradually stir in broth that is left.
Cook until slightly thickened.
Add sour cream.
Remove from heat.
Stir 1/2 cup of sauce into turkey mixture.

title: possum and sweet potatoes
directions: Turn possum loose and get the short ribs ready!
Boil them until tender.
Wash and put taters in pan, then in a hot 350° oven for about 1 hour or until they are soft.
Peel skins of taters and put in baking dish with ribs.
Put a small amount of sugar on potatoes and about a cup of broth in dish.
Bake in a 300° oven. This is good too, if you use backbone instead of ribs.

title: 5-minute fudge
directions: Combine sugar and cocoa.
Add corn syrup, milk and butter. Let boil 5 minutes.
After good boil begins, add vanilla and nuts. Beat until loses its gloss.
Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper.

title: marinated vegetable salad
directions: Combine green beans, peas, corn, onion and green pepper.
Mix together remaining ingredients and pour over vegetables. Refrigerate 24 hours, stirring occasionally.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Combine Cheddar cheese, half and half, Velveeta and margarine in a saucepan.
Warm over medium heat until melted.
Place hash browns in a casserole dish and pour the melted mixture over them. Let the dish set for 1 hour and then bake 1 hour in a 350° oven.

title: crescent roll pizza
directions: Bake rolls that have been flattened to form a crust on an ungreased cookie sheet for 10 minutes.
Cool well before assembling.

title: honey bee cookies
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Beat margarine, brown sugar, honey and egg in medium bowl on medium speed.
Stir in remaining ingredients. Drop the dough by teaspoonful onto an ungreased cookie sheet. Bake until set and light brown around edges.
Let stand 3 to 5 minutes before removing.
Makes 36 cookies.

title: salsa
directions: Mix ingredients together and keep refrigerated.

title: jo's banana punch
directions: Boil sugar and 6 cups water for 3 minutes; cool.
Mash the bananas in blender or food processor; add juice of lemons immediately.
Add frozen orange juice and pineapple juice.
Mix all ingredients, except 7-Up together.
Freeze in containers (1 to 2-cup size).
When ready to use, partially thaw.
Place in blender; add an equal amount of 7-Up.
Blend on high speed until smooth.
It's ready to serve! The foamy 7-Up may be added right to the punch bowl.
Makes 64 (4-ounce) servings or 32 (8-ounce) servings.

title: green chili and cheese brunch casserole
directions: Place buttered muffin halves face down in 13 x 9 x 2-inch casserole dish.
Brown and crumble sausage.
Mix in chiles. Layer sausage mix, alternating with cheese, over muffins.
Top with onion.
Combine beaten eggs with sour cream and pour over casserole.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Next day, remove and let stand at room temperature for 30 minutes.
Bake uncovered at 350°, approximately 35 to 40 minutes, and serve warm.

title: orange rice
directions: Cook rice in boiling water with salt.
Add orange peel and juice.
Drain and serve.

title: caesar bean salad
directions: Mix all ingredients except pepper and lemon wedges in a large bowl.
Cover and refrigerate at least 1 hour, stirring occasionally. Remove with slotted spoon and if desired arrange on salad greens. Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
If desired, additional snipped parsley and grated Parmesan cheese. Garnish with lemon wedges.
Makes 5 servings.

title: skillet barbecued chicken
directions: Season and cook chicken in covered skillet for 15 minutes in moderately hot oil.
Remove cover and brown chicken pieces.
Remove chicken just long enough to pour off oil, keeping in browned bits. In separate pan, cook onion in oil until tender.
Add all of remaining ingredients and simmer for 15 minutes.
Pour sauce over chicken in skillet.
Cover and simmer for 30 minutes to let flavors mingle and ripen.
Serve with plain boiled potatoes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: jell-o mold
directions: Dissolve Jell-O, 2 cups hot water, add sherbet and melt. Stir. Add drained oranges. Chill to set ring mold.

title: brown rice
directions: Mix and pour the ingredients in a dish and cook for 45 minutes.

title: joann's cornbread
directions: Mix all of this well (except cheese).
Put half of it in a hot iron skillet.
Then put all of the grated cheese on top.
Then put rest of meal mixture on the cheese (cheese is in middle).
Bake at 450° for 30 minutes.

title: japanese fruit cake pie
directions: Mix the margarine, sugar and eggs all together. Add the coconut, pecans and raisins.
Pour into a 9-inch pie shell, unbaked.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes, then reduce temperature to 300° for 50 minutes.

title: punch
directions: Freeze the cans of pineapple juice in 2 separate containers. About 5 minutes before serving, put 1 frozen pineapple juice in punch bowl.
Pour 4 liters of ginger ale over the frozen pineapple.
Serve and enjoy.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Place ingredients, one layer at a time, in a bowl.
Just before serving, add 1 1/2 cups grated cheese over top, then add about 6 or 7 slices of cooked bacon, crushed, or bacon bits.

title: marinated cole slaw
directions: Combine oil, vinegar, sugar, celery seed and salt.
Bring to a rapid boil.
Slowly pour hot mixture over cabbage, pepper and onion.
Do not stir.
Let set at least one hour.
Chill.

title: baked corn
directions: Mix all well.
Put in a greased casserole.
Top with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: onion-topped steak
directions: Diagonally slash outer edge of fat at 1-inch intervals to prevent curling.
Marinate beef as directed on envelope of meat marinade.
Mix sugar, cornstarch, mustard and salt in 1 1/2-quart saucepan.
Stir in water, orange peel, orange juice and lemon juice.
Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and boils.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Set oven control to broil or 550°. Place beef on rack in broiler pan.
Broil with top 2 or 3 inches from heat until brown, about 8 minutes.
Brush with orange sauce; turn over.
Broil until desired doneness, 8 to 10 minutes for medium.
Brush with orange sauce.
Sprinkle with onions.
Serve with sauce.
Makes 6 servings, 450 calories per serving.

title: scott's spaghetti sauce
directions: Melt butter over low heat. Add seasonings. Simmer 10 minutes over low heat. Add cheese and simmer 10 minutes more. Add sour cream and simmer over very low heat, stirring occasionally.

title: chocolate torte
directions: First Layer:
Melt margarine.
Add flour and nuts.
Press in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 2 cups boiling water.
Add frozen strawberries.
Cool, add pineapple, bananas, and nuts.
Pour 1/2 of mixture in dish and congeal.
Spread sour cream on top.
Pour in other half of jello.

title: cake mix cookies
directions: Combine the mix,
eggs and oil (it will be sticky). Stir in the chips, nuts or other. Drop by rounded tsp. onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for
9 to 11 minutes. Cool 1 minute on cookie sheet, then move to waxed paper.

title: creamed asparagus over toast
directions: Add melted oleo to flour to make a paste.
Add the milk.
Stir over heat until thickened.
Add 1/2 cup cream of chicken soup. Add salt and pepper.
Chives or onion are optional.
Add the asparagus and chopped ham.
Serve hot over toast.

title: butterhorns
directions: Scald milk.
When lukewarm, add yeast and the 1 cup of flour. Mix well; cover and let stand for 15 minutes.
Mix remaining ingredients like pie crust.
Add milk mixture and 3 well beaten eggs.
Knead into a ball and place in a bowl that has been coated with butter, turning to coat top of dough as well.
Let rise, free from any draft for about an hour.
Divide dough into fifths and roll each part like pie crust.
Brush with melted butter.
Cut into eighths and roll, starting at wide end, to form horns.
Place on ungreased sheets and let rise again for about 2 hours.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Frost with a butter frosting.

title: easy scratch cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar, milk and shortening; add eggs.
Beat with whisk by hand or spoon for 2 minutes or until well mixed.
Pour into greased cake pan.
Bake for 20 minutes or until done in middle; check with toothpick or fork.

title: "happy rolls"
directions: Measure the warm water and put it into a bowl.
Sprinkle the yeast on top of the water.
Let the yeast settle into the water. Mix all of the ingredients in a large bowl.
Place the dough on a floured board to knead it.
Knead dough for 10 minutes.
Put ball of dough into greased bowl.
Cover the bowl and put it in the sun or near heat.
Let it rise for one hour.
Take dough out of bowl. Punch it down and knead for several more minutes.
Divide the dough into 18 to 20 pieces.
Roll each piece into a ball and place on a greased cookie sheet.
Let dough rise until doubled.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: buttermilk coconut pie
directions: Combine the sugar and flour in a large bowl.
Add butter, buttermilk, eggs, vanilla and 2/3 of the coconut.
Mix well.
Pour mixture into shell.
Sprinkle with remaining coconut.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 5 minutes or until set.
Yields 8 servings.

title: cherry - o - pie
directions: Mix and put in individual pie shells or on a graham cracker base.
Put cherry pie filling on top if desired.

title: dora's small wonders
directions: Crush wafers fine. Add raisins, milk and finely chopped nuts. Mix well. Press mixture evenly into a greased 9 x 11 pan. Cover with foil and place in refrigerator for 24 hours. Cut into 1-inch squares and roll pieces in powdered sugar. These are wonderful. I sometimes substitute chocolate chips for raisins.

title: souvlaki(marinated skewered lamb)
directions: Quarter and separate onion pieces.
Quarter and then halve green peppers.
Halve tomatoes; divide lamb into 8 portions. Thread each portion on a skewer alternating lamb cubes with vegetables.
Combine remaining ingredients to marinade.
Cover pan that has the skewered lamb.
Refrigerate overnight.
Broil or grill for 20 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: pam's chicken noodle soup
directions: Remove skin and boil chicken.
Add other ingredients.
Simmer. Cook egg noodles according to package directions.
Drain.
Add to soup.
Enjoy.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix jellied cranberry sauce and 1 cup hot water in blender or mixer until liquid and smooth.
Dissolve both packages of gelatin in 1 cup of boiling water.
Add cranberry mixture and pecans to gelatin.
Put half of mixture in an 8-inch square pan and chill in fridge until firm, 30 to 35 minutes.
Spread sour cream and sugar over top of mixture.
Pour other half of gelatin mixture over sour cream and refrigerate until firm.

title: million dollar fudge
directions: Melt chocolate chips and candy bar over hot water. Bring to a boil the sugar, oleo and milk.
Boil 5 minutes. Add chocolate, vanilla, marshmallow cream, salt and nuts.
Beat by hand until well mixed.
Pour into pan and let cool.

title: carrot bread
directions: Mix sugar, salad oil and eggs together.
Add flour, soda and salt; mix with first ingredients.
Add vanilla, carrots and nuts. Bake 1 hour in greased pan.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: macaroni salad with shrimp
directions: Boil Creamettes until tender, about 10 minutes.
Drain well. Add shrimp, eggs, celery and onions; blend thoroughly.
Add salt, pepper and celery seed.
Mix in mayonnaise and dash of mustard. Sprinkle with paprika and chill before serving.

title: texas potatoes
directions: Mix together all of the ingredients and pour in greased baking dish.

title: chicken and broccoli pasta
directions: Wash and cut up chicken breasts into strips and lightly brown in 2 tablespoons of oil.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Meanwhile heat 5 to 6 quart sauce pot salted water boiling to cook noodles later. Next cut off broccoli flowers in half when chicken is almost brown toss in broccoli to soften.
Add about 2/3 package of bowtie pasta to boiling water cook as label directs; drain.
Toss noodles with chicken and broccoli.
When ready to eat microwave alfredo sauce for 2 minutes, pour over chicken and pasta serve with side salad if you like.

title: vegetables and pasta
directions: Cut vegetables in strips.
Stir-fry in oil 2 to 3 minutes until vegetables are tender-crisp.
Stir together spices and wine. Drizzle over veggies and toss to coat.
Heat through.
Add cooked, drained linguine and toss.
Add cheese; toss and serve hot.
Add cooked, cubed chicken breasts or crab for a main dish. Contains 192 calories per serving.

title: pepsi chicken
directions: Put chicken in skillet with butter to brown. Use salt, pepper and garlic powder to taste. Pour Pepsi and ketchup over chicken. Stir to mix Pepsi and ketchup. Simmer for 40 to 50 minutes or until chicken is done.

title: rice and chicken casserole
directions: In a bowl, mix soup and milk; reserve half of mixture.
In another bowl, mix remaining soup mixture, rice and mushrooms and liquid with half of onion soup mix.
Pour into shallow casserole. Place chicken on top.
Pour reserved soup over chicken.
Sprinkle with remaining onion soup.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Uncover; bake 15 minutes more.

title: congealed vegetable salad
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and bring to boil.
Pour over gelatin which has been dissolved in water.
Add remaining ingredients. Place in dish or ring mold and refrigerate.

title: boston baked beans(as they should be)
directions: Pick over beans; discard any imperfect ones.
Rinse well; place beans in a bowl.
Cover with cold water.
Soak overnight; drain.
Cover with water; bring to a boil.
Lower heat; simmer until skins split when blown upon.
Drain.
Pour into bean pot. Stir salt, mustard, ginger, molasses, brown sugar and maple syrup together with some boiling water; pour over beans.
Peel and push onion into center of bean pot.
Cube salt pork; place on top of beans.
Add enough hot water to cover beans.
Cover bean pot. Bake for 8 hours in a 250° oven.
Add hot water (if needed) to keep beans covered.
During the last hour of cooking, remove cover and increase temperature to 300°.

title: drop biscuits
directions: Blend all together and drop by spoonful on a cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Blend together shortening, sugar and eggs.
Sift together flour, cream of tartar, soda and salt.
Add to first mixture and mix.
Refrigerate 1 hour.
Then roll dough in balls the size of a walnut.
Roll in a mixture of 2 tablespoons sugar and 2 teaspoons cinnamon.
Place on cookie sheet 2 inches apart.
Bake until lightly brown but still soft.
(These puff up at first then flatten out.)
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 400°.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Stir all ingredients together and spread in a 9 x 12-inch dish.
Refrigerate until set.

title: pecan pralines
directions: Boil sugar and milk slowly.
Just before reaching soft ball stage, add pecans. When soft ball stage, remove from heat and let cool.
Beat until creamy. Drop mixture by spoonful on wax paper.

title: fruit punch(quantity)
directions: This punch can be frozen ahead.

title: marinated grilled vegetables
directions: Toss all vegetables in 1 cup dressing. Allow to stand at room temperature for 1 hour.
Grill vegetables 2 to 3 minutes per side, basting with vinaigrette.
Toss veggies in remaining dressing. Serve as a side dish with any entree.
Yields 6 servings.

title: lemon whippersnaps
directions: Mix by hand the cake mix, egg and Cool Whip.
Chill.
Form into 1 1/2-inch balls and roll in sugar.
Bake on greased cookie sheet, 2 inches apart, at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Watch carefully.
Do not let cookies get too brown.

title: pasta ala' daniel
directions: Heat saute pan with nonstick spray or small amount of oil. Cook chicken 3/4 of the way done.
Add wine.
Add vegies and some broth; reduce by 1/2.
Add pasta.
Cook 2 minutes and serve. Garnish with black olives.

title: chocolate peppermint squares
directions: Bake brownies according to package directions.
Mix powdered sugar, margarine, peppermint and milk.
Add a drop of green food coloring.
Spread over cooled brownies.
Melt unsweetened chocolate and dribble over top of brownies.

title: favorite soup
directions: Brown ground beef or use cubed ham.
Add potatoes, macaroni and seasonings.
Last, add corn.
Add a little milk just before serving.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix cinnamon with sugar.
Add margarine and cream well.
Add eggs and beat.
Add chopped apples and water.
Add flour that has been sifted with soda and beat together.
Bake in 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.
Glaze, if desired, but not really necessary.

title: tea cakes
directions: Preheat oven
Mix sugar and shortening.
Beat in eggs.
Blend
in
flour
using
slow
speed
on mixer.
Add nutmeg.
Turn
onto floured cloth and add more flour as needed to make dough stiff.
Roll thin, cut, decorate if desired, and bake on greased cookie sheet 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.

title: red cabbage slaw
directions: In a large mixing bowl place cabbage, apples and celery; sprinkle over lemon juice.

title: barbecue wieners
directions: Brown onions in salad oil.
Add all ingredients except wieners. Simmer for 15 minutes.
Split wieners and place in a shallow baking dish.
Pour sauce over them.
Bake in oven at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: orange chiffon jello mold
directions: Mix Jell-O, pudding and water in a heavy pan and bring to a boil.
Boil 5 minutes.
Cool.
Whip 1 package Dream Whip and mix in well in Jell-O mixture.
Fold in can of mandarin oranges and put in mold, two small cans.

title: bubble bread
directions: Let dough balls set out to thaw for 30 minutes.
Prepare Bundt pan with spray Pam.
Place dough balls, evenly arranged, in pan. Place half of chopped nuts over dough balls.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Cream butter, sugar and egg.
Add flour, baking powder and salt with milk.
Mix in blueberries.
Put in muffin pans.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: macaroni casserole
directions: Add all ingredients in order.
Dot with butter and crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° in a 2 1/2-quart casserole until brown, about 1 hour.

title: layered jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello.
Add strawberries, pineapple, bananas and nuts.
Pour 1/2 of mixture into a 13 x 9-inch glass dish. Refrigerate until firm.
Spread on sour cream.
Add remaining 1/2 of mixture and refrigerate.

title: zucchini drop cookies
directions: Cream the first 3 ingredients together, then add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Drop on greased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 375°.

title: picnic punch
directions: Open cans of orange juice and pineapple juice.
Pour contents into a 1 1/2-gallon container.
Fill a 6 ounce juice can with water and add the water to the container.
Repeat this step five more times.
Open the cans of lemonade and limeade and add them to the contents of the container.
Stir well.
Fill the container to the top with ice cubes.

title: pickles from ripe cucumbers
directions: Peel and slice cucumbers and onions thin.
Let stand overnight in salt water.
(One cup of salt to 1 gallon of water.)
Drain. Cook the remaining ingredients and pour over vegetables.
Boil and cook 15 minutes.
Process as desired.

title: monster cookies
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients in large pan.
Mix in remaining ingredients.
Place 6 large cookies on a cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Remove while still soft.

title: party sandwich spread
directions: Mix all ingredients and serve on crackers or bread.

title: baked macaroni and cheese
directions: In a saucepan, melt margarine over very low heat.
Remove from heat.
Mix flour and salt until smooth.
Pour in milk.
Stir constantly.
Cook over medium heat until lightly thickened.
Add cheese.
Stir constantly until cheese is melted.
Pour cheese on top and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 375° until brown and bubbly.

title: chicken fiesta
directions: Brown onion and green pepper in butter.
Add chicken, cream of mushroom soup, cream of chicken soup and chicken broth.
Heat this mixture.
Pour over crushed Doritos.
Spread in a greased pan. Add grated cheese on top.
Heat 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.
Makes 4 servings.

title: sunshine carrots
directions: Boil all above ingredients (except carrots and butter) for 1 minute.
Add butter.
Pour glaze over hot, cooked carrots.

title: apple lemonade
directions: Combine lemon peel, lemon juice and sugar, stirring until sugar is dissolved.
Add water and store in refrigerator.

title: quick and easy chicken spaghetti
directions: Mix well and cover with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° until hot and bubbly and cheese is melted.

title: vegetable-stuffed tomatoes
directions: Cover tomatoes with boiling water.
Let stand 1 minute.
Pour off water, cover with cold water and carefully peel off skins. Cut a 1/4-inch thick slice from top of each tomato.
Scoop out pulp and seeds; discard.

title: wayne's soup
directions: Brown beef; drain.
Put beef and all other ingredients in large pot.
Simmer for about 20 to 25 minutes.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix sour cream, Hellmann's mayonnaise, onion and Knorr vegetable soup mix.
Add spinach and water chestnuts; mix well. Chill 2 hours.

title: slushy punch
directions: Boil sugar and water until sugar is dissolved.
Cool.
Blend bananas and pineapple juice.
Stir in other juices, sugar and water mixture.
Freeze.
Remove from freezer 30 minutes before using.
Scrape.
Spoon into a punch bowl.
Slowly pour carbonated water down sides of bowl.
Enjoy.
Makes a wonderful punch for showers.
Yields 25 (4 ounce) servings.

title: creole spaghetti
directions: Brown the ground chuck with the onion; drain. Add all other ingredients together in a big pot and cook slowly about 30 minutes. Add some tomato juice to make right consistency.

title: zucchini chili
directions: In a large saucepan cook onion, carrots, and zucchini with 1/2 cup of water for 20 minutes.
Add kidney beans, tomatoes, and spices.
Cook for 30 minutes on medium heat.

title: sausage jambalaya
directions: Saute pepper and onion in butter.
Add 1 can chicken broth (mixed with water to make 4 cups liquid).
Dice or slice sausage. Add soy sauce.
Bring to a boil and reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 25 minutes.
Can be frozen.

title: artichoke salad
directions: Prepare rice according to package directions.
Cool.
Add onions, olives and green peppers.
Drain artichokes and save liquid.
Mix lemon juice, mayonnaise and liquid from artichokes and mix well.
Pour over rice mixture.
Add artichokes last. Refrigerate overnight.
Serve cold.

title: elaine's pizza dough
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Stir in remaining ingredients. Beat vigorously 20 strokes.
Let rest about 5 minutes.
Spread dough in pan.
Add pizza and desired toppings.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 2 small pizzas or you can use 1 large cookie sheet.

title: tossed egg salad
directions: Break lettuce in bite sized pieces in salad bowl.
Alternate layers of eggs and onion rings.
Combine next 7 ingredients for dressing.
Add to lettuce with cheese; toss slightly.
Makes 6 servings.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Shape into balls the size of walnuts.
Melt chocolate chips and mix with melted paraffin. Insert toothpick in balls and dip in chocolate mixture.
Place on wax paper to cool.

title: sweet and sour brisket
directions: Place brisket on onions and garlic.
Mix other ingredients; pour over brisket.
Cover and bake at 350° until tender, approximately 4 hours.

title: the best waffles
directions: Mix eggs, milk and oil with mixer or blender.
Slowly add dry ingredients, beat until smooth.
Pour batter from cup or pitcher onto center of hot waffle iron.
Bake about 4 minutes or until steaming stops.

title: almond bark candy
directions: Melt almond bark.
Stir in pecans, Rice Krispies and mini marshmallows.
Drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper.

title: brownies
directions: Sift the first 4 ingredients together.
Next place all ingredients in a large bowl.
Beat at low speed to mix, then 3 minutes at medium speed.
Use an 8-inch square pan.

title: apple torte
directions: Beat eggs, add sugar and beat until creamy.
Add dry ingredients gradually and fold in nuts and apples.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Makes 9 x 13-inch pan.
Serve with whipped cream. Better served warm.

title: breakfast syrup
directions: Mix all ingredients except maple flavoring.
Bring to good rolling boil.
Remove from heat and add flavoring.
Cool and put in jar and refrigerate.
Keeps well.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix all dry ingredients.
Add chopped onion, then milk and egg. Drop by spoonfuls into hot grease.
Cook until golden brown.
Drain on brown paper or paper towels.

title: orange-glazed fresh ham
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Place ham on rack in open roasting pan. Insert meat thermometer in thickest part of the ham.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours (allow 20 minutes per pound) or until meat thermometer registers 155°.

title: arizona chili
directions: Brown beef; drain excess fat.
In blender, place onion, celery, tomato sauce and water; blend well.
Add beans and remaining ingredients.
Add salt, pepper and chili powder to taste.

title: brownie chocolate cake
directions: Mix sugar, flour and salt; set aside.
In saucepan, put margarine, cocoa and water; bring to a boil.
Add to dry ingredients. Add beaten eggs, vanilla, baking soda and milk.
Mix well.
Pour into greased and floured sheet pan (17 x 10-inch). Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Frost while warm.

title: pecan crunch
directions: Beat until fluffy the egg whites, sugar and baking powder. Fold in graham crackers and chopped pecans.
Pour into well-greased pie pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes. Refrigerate 4 hours.

title: strawberry cheese cake - pie
directions: Cream the cheese. Mix whipped topping in the cheese. Spread on the pie shell. Mix the strawberries (washed and cut in pieces) with the glaze. Spread on top of cream cheese mixture. Garnish with whipped cream and serve.

title: chocolate sauce for fruit
directions: Melt chocolate chips and caramel sauce together.
Add milk. Keep warm.
Serve with strawberries, pineapple, sliced apples, etc.

title: uncooked oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine sugar, milk, cocoa and margarine and boil one minute. Combine oats and nuts in bowl and pour cocoa mixture over, mixing well.
Drop by teaspoon on waxed paper and let cool or place in refrigerator.

title: pumpkin spice muffins(heartwarming christmas 1991)
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs and pumpkin; mix.
Stir in dry ingredients.
Add vanilla.
Bake in greased and floured muffin pan for 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.
Yields 24.

title: cream of broccoli soup(12 servings)
directions: Cut broccoli flowerets from stems.
Reserve.
Chop broccoli stems.
Heat butter in 4-quart Dutch oven over medium-high heat. Saute garlic and onion in butter.
Stir in broccoli stems, cream, lemon juice, celery, bay leaves and broth.
Heat to boiling. Boil, uncovered, 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to medium.
Stir in broccoli flowerets, milk, parsley, sage and pepper.
Cover and cook 30 minutes.
Remove bay leaves.
Top each serving with cheese.

title: hamburger-corn pie
directions: Cook and stir hamburger, onion and garlic until meat is brown; drain (can be rinsed in hot water to reduce the fat).
Stir in tomatoes, corn, olives, chili powder and salt.
Heat to boiling. Pour into ungreased baking dish (9 x 9 x 2-inch or 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch pan or 2-quart casserole).

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Prepare broccoli according to directions.
Melt 1 stick oleo. Add cornbread mix, onion, eggs, sour cream and broccoli.
Melt other stick of oleo in baking pan.
Pour mixture into pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: fireside beans and canadian bacon
directions: Mix ginger, onion and Karo and pour over beans in a 2 quart ovenproof casserole.
Stir to mix well.
Arrange bacon slices over top of beans.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour or until bubbly.
During baking, baste bacon slices often with juices in casserole to glaze.
Makes 6 servings.

title: brown edge cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Beat eggs well and add alternately with flour.
Add vanilla.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet and bake in 375° oven approximately 5 to 8 minutes.

title: cauliflower cheese salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise and cheese; set aside.
Mix other ingredients. Add mayonnaise and cheese mixture.
Chill before serving.

title: potato filling
directions: Mix together; put in buttered pans or casseroles.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Makes large amount; can freeze some.

title: super bowl 'n roll
directions: Saute vegetables in oil a few minutes.
Add broth; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes.
Add milk, flour, salt and pepper.
Cook and stir until thick and bubbly.
Add cheese; stir until melted.
Serve with football rolls.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Boil
water,
margarine
and sugar for 10 minutes, then add flaked
coconut.
Pour
this mixture into ungreased sheet cake pan.
Sprinkle 2 1/2 cups miniature marshmallows over top of mixture, then sprinkle 1 cup of chopped nuts over marshmallows.

title: monkey bread
directions: Roll biscuit dough into balls.
Dip into butter and roll into cinnamon sugar mixture.
Drop into cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: apple dip
directions: Mix cream cheese and brown sugar well.
Put in shallow dish. Top with caramel topping and chill.
Goes best with Granny Smith apples.

title: fruity gelatin delight
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water in a medium bowl.
Add ice cubes to bowl.
Stir for 3 minutes or until melted.
Chill gelatin in refrigerator for 15 minutes.
Pour in apples, grapes, bananas and pecans.
Cover and chill for about 15 minutes.
Spoon about 1/4 of the gelatin mixture into a clear glass bowl.
Alternate layers of whipped topping, blueberries and remaining gelatin in a bowl ending with whipped topping.
Serve immediately.

title: pizza dough
directions: Warm the milk in the microwave on High for 35 seconds.
Stir sugar into warm milk, then stir in yeast.
Let stand 5 minutes to moisten yeast.
Sift flour and salt.
Add milk mixture and oil to flour.
Knead 5 to 10 minutes.
Grease pizza pan.
Spread pizza dough on pan.
Top with pizza sauce and your favorite toppings. Bake for 20 to 25 minutes at 400°.

title: pea salad
directions: Cook peas for 5 minutes.
Drain and cool.
Layer as follows: lettuce, peas, celery, onion, and green pepper.
Sprinkle with seasoned salt and pepper.
Add Baco's.
Spread 1/2 inch mayonnaise on top and sprinkle cheddar cheese on top of entire salad.

title: almond glaze for jam strips
directions: Beat ingredients together until smooth and of desired consistency.

title: avocado dip
directions: Put in small container.
Mix well.
Garnish with avocado seed to keep from turning brown.

title: chicken pie
directions: Cook onion in butter until tender.
Blend in flour and salt. Add broth all at once.
Cook and stir until thick and bubbly.
Add remaining ingredients.

title: chinese style fried rice
directions: Bring 1 cup of water to a boil in saucepan and stir in rice. Remove from heat. Cover and let stand 5 minutes.

title: pierogi(traditional polish christmas eve dish)
directions: Sift flour and salt in a bowl.
Add butter, mashed potato, egg and warm water.
Mix together and knead on floured board until smooth and satiny.
Divide dough and roll about 1/4-inch thick on floured board.
Cut with donut cutter (I use a glass dipped in flour as my grandmother did).
Press a teaspoon-sized dab of filling into dough, fold in half and press edges tightly.
Boil in water until they rise to the surface.
Top with finely rolled soda cracker crumbs and melted butter.

title: delicious fruit salad
directions: Heat juice, butter and lemon juice; mix sugar and flour, then slowly add to the beaten eggs.
Add a little to the hot liquid; mix and stir slowly into the boiling liquid.
Cook until thick; cool.
Pour over mixed drained fruit: apples, grapes, canned fruit cocktail (drained), canned pineapple chunks (drained), cherries and bananas.

title: over that cookie
directions: Bake at 300 degrees for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: chicken broccoli vegetable saute
directions: Heat 1 tablespoon margarine.
Cook chicken until browned on both sides.
Remove chicken.
In same skillet stir in remaining margarine, broccoli, carrots and mushrooms; cook 5 minutes.
Stir in soup, milk and pepper.
Return chicken to skillet.
Reduce heat to low; simmer 5 minutes or until chicken is tender.

title: fresh peach pie
directions: Cook sugar, cornstarch, water and salt until clear, then add 1 box peach Jell-O while mixture is still hot.
Let cool and pour over sliced peaches in bottom of baked crust.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: hopping john
directions: Saute ham, onion and hot sauce in oil.
Combine peas, ham mixture and rice; heat.
Garnish with thin slices of ham and mustard greens.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: apple walnut cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in a large tube pan or 2 loaf pans, 1 hour and 10 minutes, in a 325° oven.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Dissolve Crisco in warm water.
Add package of yeast.
Mix well and add sugar and flour to make a stiff batter.
Place in large bowl and cover.
Let rise until doubled in bulk or overnight.
Add enough flour until can roll on cookie sheet.
Cut in rolls 1/4 inch thick.
Put in greased pan.
Set in warm place until it has doubled in thickness.
Bake at 400° until brown.

title: easy cheese dip
directions: Brown hamburger meat and sausage. Drain. Mix with cheese and cheese dip. Heat on low until cheese melts. Eat with tortilla chips.

title: vegetable beef soup(made with ground beef)
directions: Brown ground beef and drain well.
Add tomatoes and sauce followed by remaining ingredients and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer at least 1 hour, or longer for better taste.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Cook cranberries in water until they pop.
Drain.
Dissolve jello mix and add everything else to it.
Sugar to taste.
(One cup to pot of berries.)
Chill in refrigerator until jello is solid.

title: roasted whole turkey or breast
directions: Rinse turkey or breast and dry with paper towels.
Rub with oil, then with salt and pepper.
Place in shallow roasting pan on a rack breast side up.
Do not cover and do not put water in pan. Place a thermometer in thickest part of turkey or breast.
Place in a preheated 325° oven on lowest rack and cook until thermometer reaches 175°.
Remove turkey from pan.
Pour water in pan and put back in oven until drippings have been dissolved.
Make gravy as desired.

title: play dough
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Allow your child to mix in the food coloring after it has cooled.
Keep in covered container.

title: orange salad
directions: Drain juice off pineapple and oranges; mix all ingredients. Do not dilute gelatin, just pour in with other ingredients. Chill.

title: king ranch chicken casserole
directions: Stew chicken until tender; reserve 1 cup broth.
Bone and cut into bite-size pieces.
Grease a 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish. Place tortillas or taco shells in bottom of dish.
Layer chicken on top.
Combine soups, onions, tomatoes and chicken broth in saucepan.
Cook over medium heat until hot.
Pour soup mixture over chicken.
Top with cheese.
Bake in 350° oven 50 to 60 minutes or until hot and bubbly.

title: paradise pumpkin pie
directions: Mix and pour over cheese mixture.
Cover edge of pie with foil.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.
Uncover edge; bake another 25 minutes or until knife comes out clean.
Combine and sprinkle over pie and bake 10 or 15 minutes more:

title: french doughnuts
directions: Drop some dough in cupcake tin (use paper liners).
Put some jelly in and another spoonful of dough on top.
Cook at 350°.

title: candy cookies
directions: Bring sugar, butter, milk and vanilla to a boil on medium-high heat.
Add chocolate or butterscotch chips and stir until melted. Add oatmeal, coconut and nuts.
Drop spoonfuls onto wax paper. Cookies will harden as they cool.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Cook spaghetti.
Place in buttered pie dish (this will be the crust).
Next, layer all other ingredients as listed.
Bake at 350° until cheese is melted and slightly brown.

title: rhubarb custard pie
directions: Slightly beat eggs; add milk.
Blend sugar, flour and nutmeg. Stir into egg mixture.
Mix in rhubarb.
Pour into prepared pie crust and dot with butter.
Cover with a lattice top.
Bake at 400° for 50 to 60 minutes, until brown.
Serve warm with whipped cream.

title: ham loaf
directions: Mix together first 7 ingredients.
In bottom of 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan, place melted margarine.
Mix together cloves, cinnamon and brown sugar; sprinkle on top of the margarine.
Next, place pineapple slices, raisins and maraschino cherries.
The meat mixture goes in the pan last.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: eggs a brunch
directions: Crumble sausage in skillet and cook until browned.
Drain; line bottom of a buttered 13 x 9-inch baking dish with crescent rolls, firmly pressing perforation to seal.
Sprinkle with sausage and cheese.
Combine remaining ingredients; beat well and pour over sausage.
Bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes or until set. Let stand 5 minutes; cut into squares.
Serve immediately.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: cherry chewbilees
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Set aside. Chop 1/2 cup nuts coarsely for topping.
Set aside.
Chop remaining 1/2 cup nuts finely.
For crust, combine flour and brown sugar.
Cut in Crisco until fine crumbs form.
Add 1/2 cup finely chopped nuts and coconut.
Mix well.
Remove 1/2 cup.
Set aside. Press remaining crumbs in bottom of pan.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes, until edges are lightly browned.

title: easy cherry cheesecakes
directions: Allow cream cheese to soften for 1 hour.
Combine with sugar, lemon juice, eggs and vanilla.
Beat until smooth.
Place 1 vanilla wafer in the bottom of each cupcake liner.
Pour cream cheese mixture over wafer until liner is half full.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool and spoon on cherry topping.
Makes 24.

title: margaret's homemade beef stew
directions: Season your meat with the salt, pepper and garlic salt.
Add water to a 1-quart pan.
Add seasoned meat.
Bring to a boil, then simmer for 3 hours.
After 3 hours, add raw vegetables and bring to a boil until tender.
Add green beans, corn, peas, etc., about 10 minutes before finished.

title: pizza chicken
directions: Scoop Pizza Quick onto chicken breasts.
Bake in oven at 350° for 35 minutes.
Add Mozzarella cheese.
Bake for an additional 10 minutes (cover with aluminum foil).

title: chicken cabbage bake
directions: Arrange cabbage wedges in deep 3-quart baking dish.
Top with half the onion rings and water.
Sprinkle with 1 teaspoon of the bouillon, 1/2 teaspoon salt, 1/4 teaspoon of nutmeg and 1/8 teaspoon of the pepper.
Place chicken quarters on top and add remaining onion rings.
Sprinkle with remaining bouillon, salt, nutmeg and pepper.
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Remove cover; adjust temperature to 375° and bake 15 minutes more or until chicken is brown and fork can be inserted with ease.

title: sesame green beans
directions: Steam green beans 10-15 minutes or until tender.
Add butter, soy sauce and sesame seeds.
Toss to coat.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Cream together the first 4 ingredients.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Chill.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: individual yorkshire puddings
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Spoon 1/2 teaspoon oil into bottom of each of 12 muffin pan cups.
Heat in oven 3 minutes.
Meanwhile, combine other ingredients in blender and blend until smooth.
Pour evenly into hot muffin cups.
Bake 13 to 15 minutes or until golden.

title: mary tobey's cranberry salad
directions: Mix cranberries, sugar, orange juice and pineapple.
Let set for 1 hour.
Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Let it start to set, then add cranberry mixture and nuts, if desired.
Pour into oblong dish.

title: dishpan cookies
directions: Use a large bowl from very beginning.
Mix brown sugar, white sugar, oil, eggs and vanilla together.
Then add flour and other dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Drop by spoonful on lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
You may cut this recipe in half for a small batch.

title: ham and pea soup
directions: In saucepan combine pea soup and chicken broth; stir in milk. Cook and stir until heated through.
Stir in ham and undrained mushrooms; heat through.

title: glossy chocolate frosting
directions: Mix the sugar, cornstarch and cocoa; add to boiling water. Cook until thick.
Remove from heat.
Add the butter, vanilla and salt.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain; mix soup and milk together.
Pour over broccoli.
Sprinkle cheese over this.
Mix Bisquick with margarine.
Sprinkle over whole mixture.
Cook at 400° until Bisquick is brown.

title: salmon supreme
directions: Melt 6 tablespoons margarine; stir in flour.
Gradually add milk; heat until thickened, stirring constantly.
Let cool. Alternate layers of salmon, sauce and crumbs in casserole; repeat layers.
Dot with butter; sprinkle with paprika.
Bake in moderate oven for 15 minutes; garnish with lemon.
Yields 4 servings.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Roll into balls (small) size of a small walnut.
Roll into a mixture of 2 tablespoons sugar and 2 teaspoons cinnamon.
Place about 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes, until very lightly browned, but still soft.
Very tasty, especially when fresh from oven.

title: sesame broccoli
directions: Combine soy sauce, vinegar and sugar in a small bowl.
Heat a large skillet or wok over medium heat.
Brown sesame seed and set aside.

title: creamy corn pudding
directions: Combine the flour, sugar and salt.
Set aside.
In a heavy saucepan, melt butter or margarine over low heat.
Add the mixture of dry ingredients, stirring constantly.
Gradually add milk and cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thickened and bubbly.
Remove mixture from
heat.
Stir in corn.
Beat eggs well.
Gradually stir about one-fourth of hot mixture into beaten eggs.
Add to remaining hot mixture, stirring constantly.
Pour into buttered casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: tomato scallop
directions: Melt 4 tablespoons margarine in skillet.
Stir in crumbs and toast until brown.
Set aside.
Melt 2 tablespoons margarine in pan.
Stir in onion.
Brown until golden.
Add tomatoes, tapioca and seasoning.
Cook 5 minutes.
Butter casserole and put in layer of crumbs.
Add tomato mixture, cheese and olives repeatedly.
Top with remaining crumbs.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: custard pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into 8-inch unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: shrimp creole
directions: In skillet, cook onion, celery and garlic in hot Crisco until tender, but not brown.
Add tomatoes, tomato sauce, salt, sugar, Worcestershire sauce, chili powder and hot sauce.
Simmer, uncovered, for 45 minutes.
Combine cornstarch with water; stir into sauce.
Cook and stir until mixture bubbles and thickens. Add shrimp and green pepper.
Cover; simmer 5 minutes.
Spoon the hot shrimp creole into the center of the parsley rice ring or serve separately.

title: french salad dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill.

title: cranberry nut muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare cranberries, nuts an orange peel; set aside.
Mix together flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and soda.
Cut in the shortening.
Stir in orange juice, egg and orange peel, mixing just to moisten; fold in cranberries and nuts. Bake 30 to 45 minutes.
Cool on rack 15 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool completely.
Bake in muffin pans.

title: stewed tomatoes
directions: Combine butter and sugar in heavy skillet. Cook over medium heat until melted and golden. Add tomatoes and salt, stirring well. Cover and reduce heat. Cook 20 minutes, until tender, stirring occasionally. Add pepper to taste. Thicken with soft bread crumbs, if desired.

title: apricot glazed carrots
directions: Prepare carrots according to cooking directions, drain. Combine remaining ingredients in a saucepan.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until preserves melt.
Stir in carrots; cook until thoroughly heated.
Garnish with apricot halves.

title: sausage brunch muffins
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Combine bisquick, milk, water, and egg; mix well.
Stir in sausage and cheese.
Fill greased muffin pan 2/3 full.
Bake at 425 degrees for 16-18 minutes or until golden brown.

title: crunchy bacon cole slaw
directions: Mix dressing and sugar in large bowl.
Add remaining ingredients, mix lightly.
Refrigerate. Serves 8 to 10.

title: quick chicken casserole
directions: Mix ingredients together and spread in a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish that has been sprayed with Pam.
Crumble 1 pack of Ritz crackers; place on top of meat mixture and put butter pats on top of crackers.
Cook at 350° for approximately 20 minutes.
Quick and good.

title: apple pecan cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix cake as directed on box. Pour half of mixture into a 13 x 9-inch pan that has been coated with a thin film of margarine. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until center is set. Combine 1/2 cup milk, 1/2 stick margarine and caramels and melt over low heat. Pour melted mixture over baked cake. On top of caramel mixture, put nuts and milk chocolate chips. Pour remaining cake batter over nuts and chocolate chips and bake at 250° for 20 minutes; then at 350° for 10 minutes. Cool. Cut into squares. Serve with whipped cream, if desired.

title: bubbles
directions: Combine, shake and let settle for 4 hours.
Store in refrigerator to keep longer.
Warm before using (or room temperature).
For outside use only.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Boil eggs (1 dozen) until ready.
Peel eggs; cut each egg in half, the long way.
Remove egg yellow and put in a bowl.
Put all egg whites on a tray or plate.
Add sandwich spread, mustard and pickle relish together.
Mix until creamy.
May need to add more sandwich spread if too stiff.
When all ingredients are mixed well, then dip mixture with spoon using another spoon to push mixture off into the egg white.
Add bacon bits just before serving.

title: sloppy joe under a bun
directions: Brown and drain ground beef.
Stir in Sloppy Joe sauce.
Mix well.
Transfer to 13x9 inch pan.
Sprinkle with cheese.
In bowl combine biscuit mix, eggs and milk until well blended.
Pour over cheese.
Sprinkle with sesame seeds.
Bake uncovered at 400° for 25 minutes or until golden brown.

title: pecan taffy strips
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg yolk and beat.
Add flour, cinnamon and vanilla.
Press into ungreased biscuit pan.
Beat 2 whites slightly and add 1 tablespoon sugar.
Spread over top with hand.
Press in nuts.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes; cut into strips while hot.

title: mom stephen's honey, fruit and nut breakfast cereal
directions: Cook and stir honey, margarine and spice until blended.
Cool. Combine and add sauce to other ingredients.
Place in greased pan in 350° oven for 20 minutes.
Stir occasionally.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Fry the first 4 ingredients until brown.
Add rest of ingredients.
Mix all together; top with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: jubilee salad mold
directions: Drain raspberries, reserving syrup.
Combine jelly and 1/2 cup water; heat and stir until jelly melts.
Add remaining 1 1/2 cups water and Jell-O; heat and stir until dissolved.
Remove from heat; add sherry, lime juice and reserved raspberry syrup.
Chill until partially set.
Fold raspberries and cherries into Jell-O. Pour into 6-cup mold.
Chill until firm.
Makes 8 servings.

title: cheese straws
directions: Mix ingredients; add water to form a ball.
Chill; roll out pastry to 1/4-inch thickness.
Cut in thin strips and twist.
Lay on papered tray and bake at 400° for 5 minutes.
Makes 2 1/2 dozen.

title: fruit medley pops
directions: In saucepan, combine sugar and water.
Bring to boil and boil 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add orange juice concentrate and stir until melted.
Add pineapple, lemon juice and bananas.
Mix well.
Pour into 25 (3 ounce) or 15 (5 ounce) paper cups. Partially freeze and insert wooden stick into center of each cup. Freeze solid.

title: gingerbread
directions: Beat together eggs, sugar, oil and molasses.
Mix together remaining ingredients and combine with first mixture.
Add 1 cup boiling water.
Mix well.
Pour into 1/2-inch flat pan and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: coconut custard pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly and add sugar and salt.
Add milk and vanilla.
Strain custard.
Add coconut to custard mixture, pour into unbaked pie shell and sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake in hot oven at 425° for 25 to 35 minutes or until knife comes out clean.

title: island cookies
directions: Combine flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt in small bowl.
Beat butter, brown sugar, granulated sugar and vanilla in large mixing bowl until creamy.
Beat in egg.
Gradually blend in flour mixture.
Stir in morsels, coconut and nuts.
Drop by slightly rounded tablespoonfuls onto ungreased baking sheets. Bake in preheated 375° oven for 8 to 11 minutes or until edges are lightly browned.
Let stand for 2 minutes.
Remove to wire racks to cool completely.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: strawberry jello salad
directions: Mix strawberry jello and 1 cup boiling water, stirring well, Add strawberries, bananas, pecans and pineapple.
Spread 1/2 of mixture in 9 x 13 pan and chill about 10 minutes, then spread with entire container of sour cream.
Next spread rest of jello mixture on top and chill another 10 minutes.
Top with Cool Whip.
Chill about 1 hour before serving.
Looks best in a glass dish.

title: easy tender pepper steak
directions: Sprinkle steak to taste with salt, pepper and garlic powder. In a heavy skillet, melt fat.
Add onions and seasoned meat.
Cook over medium heat, turning frequently, until browned.
Add green peppers and water to cover meat.
Cover pan and reduce heat. Simmer for 1 hour or until meat is tender.
Add more water during cooking, if necessary.
Serve over rice.

title: pecan pancakes
directions: Preheat lightly greased griddle or waffle iron to 350°.
Mix milk and eggs.
Add biscuit and baking mix and blend until batter is fairly smooth.
Stir in melted butter and ground pecans.
Cook pancakes 1 to 2 minutes on each side and waffles 2 to 3 minutes or until golden brown.
Yields 12 to 14 (5-inch) pancakes or 10 to 12 (5-inch) waffles.

title: smothered corn with chicken
directions: Cut up chicken to frying size pieces.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: mock fried chicken(heart healthy)
directions: *If using self-rising flour, decrease salt to 1/2 teaspoon.

title: chicken 'n noodles
directions: Place chicken in crock-pot.
Season with salt and pepper.
Add all liquid.
Cover and cook on low for 8 to 10 hours, on high for 4 to 5 hours.
Remove chicken from broth.
Turn crock-pot to high and add noodles.
Bone chicken and cut up meat.
Stir chicken into noodles.
Cover and cook 30 to 45 minutes.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Drain salmon and save liquid.
Flake salmon and remove bones and skin as desired.
Combine bread crumbs, seasonings and mayonnaise with reserved liquid.
