Add salmon and mix thoroughly. Pack into 9 x 5-inch greased loaf pan.
Sprinkle generously with paprika.
Bake 45 to 60 minutes in preheated oven at 350°.
Serves 8.

title: super banana pudding
directions: Mix together first six ingredients.
In large bowl or pan, layer bottom with vanilla wafers, then sliced bananas.
Cover with pudding.
Repeat until all pudding is used.
Chill well.
Makes a lot of yummy dessert.

title: taco salad
directions: In a salad bowl, arrange lettuce and radishes.
Cover and refrigerate.
Cook ground beef, onion, chili powder and garlic, stirring to break up meat.
Pour off fat.
Stir in tomatoes, chilies and salt; heat until boiling.
Reduce heat.
Cook for 5 minutes.
Pour mixture over lettuce and radishes.
Top with cheese and corn chips.
Serve immediately.

title: infallible pound cake
directions: Cream Crisco and
sugar
together.
Add
eggs
one at a time and beat
well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.	Take
cake
out
of oven; let cool 5 minutes and turn out of tube or Bundt pan.

title: hot pineapple cheese casserole
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients together. Pour in casserole dish. Mix cracker crumbs with butter. Spread over top. Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: lemon sponge pie
directions: Mix
sugar and flour thoroughly.
Stir in the juice and rind of	lemon and yolks of eggs.
Add melted butter and milk. Add beaten egg whites with wire whip.
Bake 45 minutes in slow oven, 325°, using 9-inch pie shell, "raw."

title: sausage and peppers
directions: Brown the sausage in frying pan for approximately 15 minutes. Sausage must be well browned.
(Use cooking oil to keep from burning.)
Use electric skillet at 400°.

title: seven-up cake
directions: Cream oleo, oil and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add flavoring, 7-Up and flour.
Bake in a tube pan 1 hour and 30 minutes at 325°.

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix together cake mix, butter and 1 egg.
Press in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix 3 eggs, cream cheese and powdered sugar together and spread on top of bottom layer.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: easy pineapple pie
directions: Put all ingredients in a large mixer bowl and beat until well mixed.
Put in two 8-inch graham cracker crusts.
Chill several hours.

title: chew bread
directions: Grease pan.
Mix brown sugar and margarine, melted, together. Add other ingredients.
Bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes.

title: rice pilaf with almonds
directions: Saute onion in margarine for about 5 minutes.
Add rice; saute 3 minutes.
Add broth, salt and raisins and bring to a boil. Remove from heat, cover and let stand 5 minutes.
Stir in almonds and parsley; fluff with fork.
Serves 4.

title: artichokes by chef tell
directions: Saute butter, onion and garlic.
Add spices, chicken stock and wine.
Bring to a boil.
Prepare artichokes by pulling off outside bottom leaves and trim the top straight.
Cook 20 minutes on the top side.
Then turn and cook for 40 minutes.
Baste the artichokes frequently.
Bake at 350°.

title: cheese snacks
directions: Blend biscuit mix, cheese, mayonnaise and milk thoroughly with fork. Shape into 1/2-inch balls.
Place on greased baking sheet. Bake at 450° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 30 servings.

title: apple cake
directions: Prepare apples and set aside.
Measure oil into bowl.
Add sugar and eggs; beat until creamy on low speed.
Sift flour and measure; sift again with salt, soda and baking powder.
Add the flour mixture a little at a time.
Fold in pecans and apples.
Put in pan lined with wax paper.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes. Use greased Bundt pan or 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Cream together margarine, oil, sugar, eggs and sour milk. Beat with mixer.
Mix dry ingredients together and add to creamed mixture.
Beat well.
Stir in shredded zuckini.
Pour butter into 9x12x2 pan.
Sprinkle with chocolate.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Let cool and serve.

title: strawberry fluff
directions: Thaw strawberries and mix with pudding.
Add Cool Whip and stir together, then chill.

title: white chocolate break-up
directions: Melt broken pieces of chocolate in microwave (approximately 30 seconds on High).
Stir chocolate until smooth.
Add pretzel pieces and peanuts.
Stir.
Spread very thin onto pieces of aluminum foil. Place in fridge until hard (approximately 1 hour). Break up pieces and enjoy.

title: never-fail devil cake
directions: Place all ingredients in bowl in order given; do not mix. After all ingredients have been added, beat well.
Place in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: orange sunbeam cookies
directions: Combine flour with baking powder, soda and salt.
Cut in margarine until crumbly.
Stir in remaining ingredients all at once, stirring with a fork until dough holds together.
Drop by teaspoon about 2-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes until golden brown.
Store in refrigerator.

title: easy mushroom appetizers
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease rectangular pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inches. Cook and stir mushrooms, onion and Worcestershire sauce in 2 tablespoons margarine in 10-inch skillet until brown.
Mix baking mix and 1/2 cup margarine in small bowl.
Add water; beat until soft dough forms.
Spread dough in pan.
Spread cream cheese over dough.
Top with mushroom mixture and Parmesan cheese.
Bake until crust is golden brown, 20 to 25 minutes.
Cut into about 1 1/2-inch squares.
Refrigerate any remaining appetizers.
Makes 54 appetizers.

title: cheese souffle
directions: Melt the butter.
Blend in the flour; add the salt.
Add the milk; stir smooth.
Add the cheese; stir until cheese melts. Cool.
Fold in the beaten egg yolk.
Fold in the beaten egg white. Bake in ungreased casserole at 300° for 1 hour.
Serves 1.

title: fired up chicken wings
directions: Preheat oven to
large
skillet, fry chicken wing pieces in oil
until slightly brown.
Remove from skillet and place on paper towels to drain.

title: french beef
directions: Brown meat; pour off drippings.
Add spaghetti sauce and onion.
Cook noodles and drain.
Mix noodles with sour cream and cream cheese until well coated.
Place noodles in 13 x 9-inch dish; cover with meat sauce.
Top with Cheddar cheese; sprinkle lightly with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour, or until heated through.
Let stand before cutting.

title: peanut or pecan brittle
directions: Mix sugar, syrup and water in heavy pan.
When it starts to boil, add margarine and stir often after it reaches 230°.
Add nuts at 280° and stir constantly until mixture reaches hard crack stage (305°).
Remove from heat; add soda and stir.
Pour into 1 large pan or 2 medium pans and spread to cool.
When cool, turn over and break into pieces.
Store in airtight container.

title: two apple pies
directions: Mix flour, spice and sugar; pour over apples.
Beat eggs; mix with melted margarine and apple mixture.
Pour into pie shells. Bake in a 400° oven for about 1/2 hour, or until done.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake in greased 9 x 13-inch pan at 325° for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar when done.

title: deluxe pound cake
directions: Cream oleo, sugar and Crisco.
Add 1 egg, at a time, beating each 1 minute.
Add 1/3 flour, beating continuously; add 1/2 cup milk and 1/3 flour.
Add the rest of the milk and flour.
Add extract last.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: apple bread
directions: Let sugar and apples set for 1 hour.
Mix with other ingredients after 1 hour.
Pour into a greased, paper-lined loaf pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: tuna chowder
directions: In a heavy bottomed soup pot, melt the butter and saute the celery, onion and potato for 5 minutes or until potato is soft, stirring constantly.
Sprinkle in the flour and mix thoroughly. Add the milk slowly, stirring.
Continue to stir until mixture thickens.
Stir in tuna, cheese, thyme, dill and salt and pepper to taste.
Pour into soup bowls garnished with the parsley.
Serves 4.

title: swedish brownies
directions: Beat eggs well; add sugar and continue beating for 5 minutes. Add flour, oil, salt and flavoring.
Beat well again.
Fold in chopped maraschino cherries (if desired).
Pour into 8-inch square pan.
Sprinkle top with walnuts and then with granulated sugar. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cut into squares while still warm.

title: chicken "n" biscuits
directions: Wash chicken tenders; place in single layer in microwave dish. Add 1/4 cup water; poach 12 minutes, turning over after 6 minutes.
Let stand until cool.
Cut into large bites.
Saute pepper and onion in 1 stick melted butter for 3 to 5 minutes, until tender.
Blend in flour.
Add chicken broth and water; mix well.
Cook 4 to 6 minutes, stirring every 2 minutes, until thick. Add chicken, mushrooms, pimientos, salt and pepper.
Beat egg yolks in milk; add to above mixture.
Cook for 10 minutes, stirring every 2 minutes.
One cup frozen peas may be added the last 5 minutes, if desired.
Serve over Bisquick baking powder biscuits, mashed potatoes or puff pastry cups.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: quick peanut butter fudge
directions: Sift
together sugar and nonfat dry milk and set aside. In top of	2
quart
double
boiler (over boiling water), melt margarine and
cream	or
chunk style peanut butter.	Then add corn syrup, water
and vanilla.
Blend in sifted sugar and dry milk.
Add nuts (toast 3 1/3 minutes in microwave) and marshmallows.
(I put these
in
earlier	and let melt.) Pour in a greased baking dish and let set.
Cut into squares.

title: potluck casserole
directions: Boil chicken and cut in chunks.
Combine with both cans of soup, milk, carrots and peas.
Place in large casserole dish. Prepare stuffing following package directions.
Spread over mixture in the casserole dish.
Cook at 400° for 45 minutes, until bubbly.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Combine cabbage and water in large saucepan.
Cover and cook over medium heat for 15 minutes; drain well.
Place cabbage wedges in a 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Melt butter in saucepan over low heat.
Add flour, stirring well until thickened.
Add salt and pepper.
Pour sauce over cabbage.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes. Combine cheese, mayonnaise, chili sauce, onion and green pepper; mix.
Spread over cabbage.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: coffee snacking bars
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs, beaten.
Add flour and dry ingredients.
Add water, vanilla and coffee.
Mix well and add raisins and nuts.
Grease and spread in pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool and cut into bars.

title: meat loaf and sauce
directions: Pour over meat mixture and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes, basting occasionally with the sauce.
Serve surplus sauce as gravy.

title: tuna ball
directions: Combine all ingredients, except olives, in the bowl of a processor.
Pulse until well blended.
Form into a large ball, chilling if necessary to handle easily.
Garnish with olive slices in a spiral or however desired.
Chill.
Serve with crackers.

title: apple-cheese pie
directions: Mix apples, sugar and lemon juice.
Put in baking dish. Combine oleo, 3/4 cup sugar, flour and grated cheese.
Mix well by hand.
Sprinkle over and pat down on apples.
Bake at 350° until bubbly and brown.
(Amounts of oleo and sugar can be reduced a bit according to one's taste.)

title: fried cornmeal mush
directions: Moisten cornmeal with enough cold water to make a paste.
Stir paste into boiling salted water, beating thoroughly.
Stir until it thickens.
Cook at low heat for 10 to 15 minutes.
Pour hot into a narrow baking pan; let stand until cold and solid.
Cut in thick slices and fry on both sides in a well buttered hot skillet until nicely browned.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Place uncooked chicken in a 9 x 13 casserole dish. Mix all ingredients together and pour over chicken. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: victorian eggnog
directions: Bring cream and half and half to simmer in a large saucepan. Whisk yolks and sugar in a large bowl to blend.
Gradually whisk hot cream mixture into yolk mixture.
Return mixture to same saucepan.
Stir over medium-low heat until mixture thickens and leaves path on back of spoon when finger is drawn across (about 4 minutes). Do not boil.
Strain into bowl.
Stir in nutmeg and cool slightly. Divide warm or cold mixture among 6 cups or glasses. Stir 1 tablespoon sherry into each. Sprinkle additional nutmeg over each and serve.

title: peanut butter oatmeal cookies
directions: In a saucepan, mix milk, butter, sugar and cocoa.
Boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat and stir in peanut butter and vanilla. Gradually stir in oats, mixing well.
Drop on wax paper and allow to cool.

title: punch
directions: Mix together, letting sherbet gradually melt.
Makes 1 large punch bowl full.

title: chocolate cake icing
directions: Mix and bring to a boil.
Boil 2 minutes.
Remove from heat and let stand for 10 minutes.
This is important!
Then beat until thick and spread on cooled cake.
Makes enough for 3 layer cake.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Grease glass loaf pan with vegetable oil.
In bowl cream together cream cheese adding sugar and sour cream.
Fold in fruit and marshmallows.
Pour into loaf pan.
Freeze at least 8 hours before serving.
Thaw 30 minutes before serving.
Cut into colorful slices for a refreshing salad.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients; pour into baking dish.

title: cheese rice and pork chops
directions: Grease a shallow baking pan.
Mix flour, garlic salt, salt and pepper together.
Dredge pork chops in seasoned flour.
Heat shortening in a frying pan and brown chops.

title: ambrosia pie
directions: Whip the cream.
Combine all other ingredients and fold into cream.
Pour into crumb pie shell and chill overnight.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Stir all ingredients together.
Put into a 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Top with French fried onions.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: two bean chili
directions: In a 6 quart Dutch oven, over medium heat, cook beef, green pepper and onion with chili powder and pepper until beef is browned and vegetables are tender, stirring to separate meat.
Spoon off fat.
Add tomato juice, kidney beans and great northern beans. Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover:cook 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Makes 6 cups or 6 servings.

title: fresh tomato soup(servings: 4)
directions: Cut tomatoes into wedges and place in 1 1/2-quart saucepan with all ingredients, except yogurt.
Simmer, uncovered, 30 minutes.
Strain to remove tomato skins and seeds.
Adjust seasonings.
Garnish with spoonfuls of yogurt.

title: lila's dark buns
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup warm water.
Mix with oatmeal, Crisco, molasses, brown sugar, salt and egg.
Pour 4 1/2 cups hot water over all.
Add flour.
Make into buns, let rise and bake at 350°.

title: smart and sassy shrimp
directions: Mince ginger root and garlic; set aside.
Mix soy sauce, sherry, ketchup, red pepper and sugar; set aside.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Place beans in bottom of greased casserole.
Place corn over beans.
Mix
water
chestnuts, onions, sour cream, cheese and soup.
Pour
over
vegetables covered with cracker crumbs. Bake at 325° until brown (approximately 30 minutes).

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash with butter, salt, pepper and garlic.
Cook until tender; mash and add eggs, cheese, milk and cracker crumbs.
Pour into buttered casserole dish; top with cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Pour rice into a large casserole dish.
Mix the 3 soups together and pour over the rice.
Place chicken breasts on top of rice.
Cover.
Bake 1 hour and 45 minutes at 350°.
This is very good.

title: egg and sausage casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch dish. Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Uncover and bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes or until set.

title: baked chicken parmesan
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Brush chicken with salad dressing; coat with combined crumbs and cheese.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Place in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Bake 1 hour or until tender.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Combine shortening and boiling water.
Stir until shortening is melted.
Combine eggs, sugar and salt.
Beat in cold water. Soften yeast in lukewarm water.
Combine the three mixtures and add the flour.
Cover and chill overnight.
Roll for cinnamon rolls or shape for coffee cake.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes for rolls, longer for coffee cake.

title: vegetable dip for raw veggies
directions: Mix with mixer and let set for a couple of hours.

title: apple crisp
directions: Place apples in the bottom of a greased baking dish.
Mix flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and the egg with a fork until the mixture is crumbly.
Place on top of the apples.
Pour 1/4 cup melted butter over top.
Sprinkle with cinnamon if desired.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Use a 1 1/2-quart glass oblong baking dish.
Serves 6.

title: double layer sweet potato pie
directions: Mix cream cheese, 1 tablespoon milk and sugar in a large bowl with a wire whisk until smooth.
Gently stir in whipped topping. Spread on bottom of crust.

title: eggplant bhorta
directions: Cut the bottom part of the eggplant with stalk to discard it. Wash the eggplant and boil it in water by cooking in microwave at High energy for 9 minutes.
Drain the water by a colander.
Peel the eggplant and mash it.
Cut the tomato into small pieces, onion and the clove of garlic should be minced and kept ready.

title: egg sauce
directions: Add vinegar to beaten eggs.
Heat.
Stir until thick.
Pour over sliced hard-boiled eggs. A good sauce for greens.

title: french silk chocolate pie
directions: Cream butter, sugar, chocolate and vanilla.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating 5 minutes after each addition.
(Use medium speed on mixer.)
Turn into cooled, baked pie shell.
Chill 1 to 2 hours.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: salmon ball
directions: Drain salmon, remove skin and ribs.
Flake with a fork.
Cream the cream cheese and blend in lemon juice, onion, horseradish, salt, Worcestershire, cayenne and liquid smoke.
Blend well.
Add salmon.
Shape and roll in parsley and nuts.
Chill.

title: monterey jack salsa
directions: Blend all ingredients and serve with tortilla chips.

title: twice-baked potatoes
directions: Prick potatoes with a fork.
Bake at 375° for 45 to 50 minutes or until tender.
Cut in half lengthwise.
Gently scoop out pulp, leaving a thin shell.

title: cold curry dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Chill at least 1 hour before serving.
Serve with raw chilled vegetables or on chips.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: my favorite pound cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, beating well after each addition.
Add milk and flour that has been sifted with salt alternately beginning and ending with flour.
Add flavoring.
Bake in 10-inch tube cake pan for 1 hour and 25 minutes at 325°.
Makes 25 servings.

title: avocado and corn salsa
directions: Blanch corn in boiling water for 3 minutes.
Drain and cool under cold water.
Cut the kernels from the cobs and place in a large bowl.
Add all the other ingredients and mix well.
Serve with warm tortillas.

title: banana split cake
directions: Combine crumbs and melted margarine.
Line 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan with crust.
Combine sugar, softened margarine, eggs and vanilla. Beat at high speed 15 minutes and spread over crust.
Slice bananas over top.
Spread crushed pineapple and fruit cocktail over bananas.
Spread Cool Whip over top.
Place cherries on top. Cover and refrigerate for 24 hours.

title: spaghetti alla puttanesca
directions: Heat oil in a large skillet; add garlic and anchovies.
Saute over low heat about 1 minute; do not brown.
Stir in tomatoes with their juice, olives, capers, red pepper, oregano and black pepper. Cook over medium heat, stirring to break up tomatoes, until the sauce thickens, about 15 minutes.
Stir in parsley; simmer 2 minutes.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: In a saucepan combine sugar, vinegar, turmeric and mustard. Bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and cool (sugar should be dissolved).
Drain sauerkraut, bean sprouts and water chestnuts. Slice chestnuts.
Mix kraut, bean sprouts, sliced chestnuts, chopped celery, sliced onion rings and mix in cooled liquid.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: sand tarts
directions: Cream the margarine and powdered sugar together.
Add vanilla, water and nuts, then add flour, blending well.
Roll into balls or little crescents with hands.
Bake in a 325° oven until slightly browned.
Dust with powdered sugar, if desired.

title: tasty berries
directions: Heat water, berries, sugar and lemon juice, stirring as little as possible.
Dissolve cornstarch in cold water.
Add to berry mixture and cook until thick.
Set aside.
Heat milk and marshmallows in double boiler until melted, then cool.
Whip Dream Whip and add to cooled marshmallows.

title: zucchini salad bowl
directions: In a large bowl, combine the first 7 ingredients.
Sprinkle with a little salt and pepper.
Toss; cover and chill.
Pour the Italian dressing over salad; toss lightly to coat vegetables. Makes 6 servings.

title: mexican pork chops
directions: Salt and pepper pork chops; brown in a large skillet.
Place a slice of onion and green pepper on each pork chop.
Mix tomato paste and water; pour over chops.
Simmer for 45 minutes or until tender.
Serve with rice.

title: deluxe oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine shortening and sugar in a large bowl. Cream until light and fluffy.
Beat in egg and stir in banana and oats.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Combine all ingredients except the whipped topping.
Fold in whipped topping last.
Garnish with marshmallows, pecans, even maraschino cherries, if desired.
Refrigerate.
Makes a pretty, fluffy salad great for hot summer days.

title: corn relish
directions: Cut corn from cob; grate corn, celery, peppers and onion. Combine all ingredients.
Add salt to taste.
Boil 1/2 hour. Process 20 minutes in pint jars.
(Carrots may also be grated and added.)

title: baked macaroni with cheese
directions: Cook macaroni as directed on package.
Rinse and drain.
Melt butter.
Stir in flour, salt, pepper, mustard and paprika. When well blended, add milk slowly, stirring constantly over low heat until mixture thickens and boils.
Add cheese and Worcestershire sauce until cheese has melted.
Add drained macaroni and pour mixture into greased 2-quart baking dish. Bake in moderately hot oven at 400°.

title: italian breakfast casserole
directions: Grease 2 x 13-inch pan.
Place bread slices in bottom.
Layer cheese and pepperoni on top.
Mix together eggs, milk and spices with a whisk.
Pour over all.
Refrigerate overnight or bake immediately in 300° oven for 50 minutes or until set.

title: lemon ice box pie
directions: Soften cream cheese to room temperature.
Add milk and blend until smooth.
Add lemonade and beat thoroughly again.
Pour into crusts. (Will be completely full.)
Freeze well.
Slice and serve frozen.

title: sausage and rice casserole
directions: Boil soup and rice in water.
Brown sausage and drain.
Mix onion, pepper, celery and mushrooms together.
Melt some butter in the sausage.
Mix all the ingredients in large bowl.
Pour into baking dish and bake 20 minutes at 325°.

title: zucchini jelly
directions: Boil zucchini in 1 1/2 cups water for 2 to 6 minutes.
Drain. Add sugar, pineapple and lemon juice. Boil 6 minutes.
Add Jell-O and boil 2 minutes. Put in jars and cool, then put in freezer.

title: baked string beans with cheese
directions: Place beans in a greased baking dish.
Dot with butter. Sprinkle with salt, paprika, cayenne and grated cheese.
Pour over them the milk or stock.
Cover dish.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: raspberry pie supreme
directions: Spread raspberries in unbaked pie shell.
Stir sour cream and combined sugar, flour and salt together, mixing well.
Spoon over berries, spreading to edge of crust.
Sprinkle top with 2 teaspoons sugar.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake for 30 minutes more, or until topping is lightly browned.
Cool at room temperature; serve fresh.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix unsifted dry ingredients.
Add eggs, chopped onions and enough milk to make a stiff batter.
Drop by spoonfuls into hot grease.
Brown on both sides. Drain. Serves 4 to 6.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a large skillet, cook bacon over medium-high heat until crisp.
Drain on paper towels.
Reserve 1/2 cup drippings in the skillet.
Crumble bacon and set aside.
Cook mushrooms and onion in drippings over medium-high heat until tender, stirring occasionally.
Blend in flour, salt and pepper. Add chicken broth and half and half.
Stir constantly over medium-high heat until mixture thickens and bubbles.
Remove from heat.
Stir in sherry.

title: summer zucchini in italian beer batter
directions: Beat everything together except egg whites and zucchini. Beat till smooth, fold in egg whites.
Dip zucchini into batter and fry in deep hot fat (about 375°) for 2 to 5 minutes.
Drain and serve immediately.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together.
Add tomato sauce and eggs, mix well.
Add ground beef and mix well.
Bake in 9 x 5-inch loaf pan at 375° for 2 hours.

title: spritz cookies
directions: Thoroughly cream together butter and sugar.
Add egg, milk, vanilla and almond extract; beat well.
Stir flour and baking powder together thoroughly.
Gradually add to creamed mixture, mixing until smooth.
Force dough through cookie press onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Decorate as desired.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 48 cookies.

title: individual cheese cakes
directions: Blend cream cheese, eggs, sugar and vanilla until smooth.
Put vanilla wafer in bottom of each cupcake paper or foil cup, which has been put in a muffin pan.
(Foil cup works the best.)
Bake at 375° for 15 to 18 minutes.
Top with cherry pie filling or any pie filling you like.
Refrigerate.
Makes about 18.

title: spinach dip
directions: Cook spinach according to package directions; drain well. Stir in remaining ingredients and chill.

title: pretzel jello
directions: Mix pretzels, margarine and sugar in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 8 minutes at 400°.
(Do not overbake.)
Cool.

title: strawberry-lime slush(low-fat, low cholesterol, low sodium, low calorie)
directions: Reserve 4 strawberries for garnish, if desired.
Place crushed ice and 1 pint of strawberries in blender or food processor. Cover and blend until mixture is almost smooth.
Pour into 1-quart (or larger) pitcher.

title: peanut butter cup pie
directions: Mix peanut butter and honey.
Heat 20 seconds in microwave. Stir in cereal.
Press into pie plate.
Prepare pudding and pour it over the pie plate mixture.
Chill well.
Serves 4.

title: polynesian bars(sugar-free)
directions: Cook until smooth and thick; cool.
Spread cooled filling over crumb mixture and cover with other half of crumb mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cabbage concoction
directions: In bottom of electric skillet or heavy skillet, layer cabbage. Slice carrots as desired.
Layer over cabbage.
Cut potatoes into quarters; layer over carrots and cabbage.
Salt and pepper.
Layer sausage over vegetables.
Add just enough water to steam and steam until done.

title: chicken a la king
directions: Mix sour cream and soup.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir over medium heat until hot.
Do not boil.
Serve on toast or pastry shells.

title: crock-pot beef round roast
directions: Place roast in crock-pot.
Mix sliced onion, undiluted condensed canned soup, seasoning and water and pour over roast. Cover and cook 8 to 10 hours on low setting.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: apricot nectar salad
directions: Dissolve jello.
Add apricot nectar.
Chill.
Add remaining ingredients and refrigerate in mold or bowl to jell (about 6 hours).

title: easy low-fat chili(makes 7 servings)
directions: Rinse and drain all beans.
In a large saucepan, cook the onion and pepper in 1/2 cup of water until tender.
Add beans, tomato paste, tomatoes, seasonings and remaining water.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat, simmer covered, about 20 minutes.

title: people puppy chow
directions: Melt chocolate chips and peanut butter in large saucepan over low heat, stirring constantly.
Add cereal; stir gently until coated.
Place confectioners sugar in large paper bag.
Add cereal; shake until cereal is coated.
Spread in single layer in 10 x 15-inch pan.
Let stand until dry.
Store in covered container.
Yield:
18 servings.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all together; pour into loaf pan.
Bake 1 1/2 hours in a 400° oven.

title: cold coconut cake
directions: Bake cake as directed.
When cake is ready, poke holes in top of cake.
Pour cream of coconut and condensed milk on top.
Let set until cool.
While cooling, mix frozen coconut and Cool Whip together.
When cool, spread mixture on top of cake.
Keep refrigerated.

title: dressing
directions: Crumble cornbread and loaf bread or biscuits.
Add sage and onions.
Mix with chicken broth, cream of chicken soup and water. (Add more liquid if needed.)
Bake in a glass baking dish in a 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix sugar and oil together.
Add eggs and mix well.
Combine dry ingredients and stir in.
Mix until smooth.
Add pecans and carrots.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: slumgullion
directions: In skillet, brown the ground beef.
While ground beef is cooking, add the onion, green chilies and the chopped up, whole, peeled tomatoes.
After the meat is cooked real good with the other ingredients, go ahead and add the corn and then peas.
Let it cook for a few more minutes, then set aside.

title: potato hamburger bake
directions: Brown beef and onion; drain well.
Line large casserole with half of Tater Tots; place meat mixture over Taters.
Add soups and wine which have been mixed together.
Top with remaining Tater Tots.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: cajun cake
directions: Drain mandarin oranges.
Add juice to oil to equal 1 cup (can add water to bring to 1 cup).
Put eggs, oil mixture and cake mix in bowl and mix.
Add oranges to mixture and beat.
Bake at 350° according to mix instructions.

title: pizza snacks
directions: Brown sausage; drain.
Add oregano and garlic.
On greased baking sheet, flatten biscuits to 4-inch circles with floured custard cup; leave a rim.
Fill with tomato paste and sausage. Sprinkle with cheeses.
Bake at 425° about 10 minutes.

title: boiled raisin cake
directions: Bring first 9 ingredients to
a boil and let stand until cool. Sift flour, soda and baking powder together.
Add all at once to cooled liquid.
Pour into 2 greased loaf pans and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: quiche lorraine
directions: Brown bacon, then fry onion, mushrooms and ham in the grease. Sprinkle cheese into bottom of pie crust, then add bacon and ham. Beat the remaining ingredients together and pour over the cheese, bacon and ham mixture.
Bake in 375° oven for 45 minutes.
Knife inserted in center should come out clean.
Let stand for 15 minutes before cutting.
Enjoy.

title: world's shortest recipe - shrimp and rice
directions: In bowl, mix shrimp, tails intact, and salsa.
Cover; chill 1 hour.
Meanwhile, cook rice; add chiles, scallions, salt and pepper.
Mix. Skewer salsa coated shrimp; broil or grill until done.
Place on rice.
Serves 4.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Dip meat in flour.
Brown in hot fat.
Add onion, garlic, mushrooms, sour cream, soup, mushroom liquid and seasonings. Simmer 1 hour.
Serve over noodles or rice.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: First, you need to roll the cookie dough up in flat balls and put them in the oven in a big pan for about 10 minutes.
You need about a tablespoon of chocolate chips.
After you cook them, put them in the refrigerator for 3 to 5 minutes, then take them out. They are ready for a great serving.

title: italian salad
directions: Mix; chill for 24 hours.

title: fruit cup
directions: Mix all ingredients together, pour in cups and then freeze. Take out of freezer before serving and allow to thaw to "slushy" stage.
Great for brunch!

title: whoopie pies
directions: Combine "Cream" ingredients and spoon into centers of two cookies.
Looks like a "Moon Pie."

title: caramel cake
directions: Combine sour cream and milk.
Cream butter; gradually add sugar, beating well at medium speed of an electric mixer.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.

title: donna's cherry chiffon pie
directions: Heat pie filling, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; slowly add gelatin and stir until dissolved.
Add flavoring.
Chill until almost set.
Whip with rotary or electric mixer until fluffy. Beat egg whites until they hold a soft peak.
Fold into gelatin mixture.
Pour into pie shell and chill until firm.
Serve with whipped topping or whipped cream, if desired.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Melt butter in 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Add crushed pretzels and sugar.
Press and bake for 10 minutes at 350°.
Cool. Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add pineapple and frozen strawberries.
Let partially set.
Mix cream cheese, Cool Whip and powdered sugar.
Spread on cooled pretzel layer.
Add strawberry mixture on top when soft-set.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: regina's easy liver 'n onions
directions: Fry bacon until crisp; remove from pan and crumble.
Dust liver with flour.
Brown in bacon drippings.
Add bacon and remaining ingredients.
Cover; simmer 30 minutes or until liver is tender.
Uncover.
Cook for a few minutes to thicken sauce. Serves 4.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Cook and stir onion, celery, green pepper and garlic in butter until onion is tender.
Remove from heat.
Stir in tomato sauce, water and seasonings.
Simmer uncovered 10 minutes.
Add water, if needed.
Stir in shrimp.
Heat to boiling.
Cover and cook over medium heat 10 to 20 minutes or until shrimp are pink and tender. Serve over rice.
Makes 6 servings.

title: beef nacho casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Brown meat and drain.
Stir in salsa, corn, Miracle Whip and chili powder.
Layer 1/2 each of meat mixture, chips and cheese in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Repeat layers.

title: easy cheeses
directions: Use equal portions of flour, butter and cheese.
Rub butter into flour with salt, pepper and a touch of cayenne pepper.
Add finely grated cheese and knead into a ball.
Cover with foil or put into plastic bag and refrigerate at least 30 minutes.
It will keep in refrigerator for up to 1 week.
Roll out to about 1/4 inch thick.
Cut or stamp cookie cutters into bite size pieces and put on cookie sheet.

title: italian delight
directions: Brown beef, onion and garlic in skillet, mix tomato soup and tomato paste together, add to meat mixture, add whole kernel corn. Boil noodles.
Layer in casserole the meat mixture, noodles, cheese and repeat.
End with meat mixture and cheese on top.
Bake at 350° about 45 minutes or until bubbly.

title: riviera peaches
directions: Place 2 peach halves in each dessert dish.
Melt jelly over low
heat.
Pour over peaches.
Chill several hours.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Crush 1 cup of pretzels.
Mix with the butter and 1/2 cup of sugar.
Spread in bottom
of a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Bake at 325° for 5 to 6 minutes.

title: cheddar cheese pepper bread
directions: Spray ring mold pan with butter flavor Pam.
Sprinkle some shredded cheese in bottom.
Take two cans biscuits and cut each biscuit in half.
Lay biscuit halves in bottom with small crack between each.
Put a jalapeno slice on each.
Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese.
Do another layer the same, then do a third layer and put cheese only.
Bake in a 400° oven for 20 minutes, or until golden brown.

title: tapioca mandarin
directions: Mix pudding and jello with rapidly boiling water.
Remove from heat and chill for 2 hours.
After 2 hours, whip mixture, then fold in drained mandarin oranges and the Cool Whip.
Chill and serve.

title: chicken divan
directions: Boil chicken.
Cut up chicken in bite-sized pieces.
Place in a baking dish.
Mix the soups and milk; warm on stove.
Pour over chicken.
Prepare the stuffing as it says on box.
Place on top of chicken in clumps.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.

title: corn souffle
directions: Add salt, sugar, pepper, flour and melted butter to cut corn. Add beaten eggs and milk to corn mixture.
Pour into greased baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes, or until set.
Serves 6.

title: apple butter crock-pot
directions: Put all ingredients in crock-pot on low for 9 to 12 hours. Stir occasionally. Can be frozen.

title: creamed corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: pistachio cake
directions: Place all ingredients in one bowl.
Mix at low speed for 1 minute and at high speed for 3 minutes.
Pour into Bundt or tube pan.
Cook at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Sprinkle confectioners sugar when cool.

title: polish sausage vidalia onions
directions: Skin and scoop out middle of Vidalia onion.
Bake until done. Scoop out rest of onion and cut up.
Cut up sausage.
Mix together with shredded cheese.
Put in onion.
Sprinkle more cheese on top.
Put back in oven and bake 1 to 2 minutes until cheese melts.

title: pickled beets
directions: Combine water, vinegar, sugar, cinnamon, salt and cloves. Heat to boiling.
Add beets and onion.
Cover pan and simmer for 5 minutes.
Chill.
Makes 1 pint.

title: indiana hawaiian chicken ginger
directions: Wash and drain the chicken.
Salt and pepper them.
Place in crock-pot.
Mix together the Catalina dressing, apricot preserves, chopped pepper and onion and pour sauce mixture over the chicken.

title: mama's nut cake
directions: Cream margarine, eggs and sugar.
Add salt and baking powder to flour and mix with mixture.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 375° for 1 1/2 hours.
Place a pan of water on bottom of oven.

title: refreshing dessert
directions: Stem and wash several large bunches seedless green grapes. Add sour cream, 1 cup pecans, wine and brown sugar.
Toss through grapes and chill well.
Before serving, fold in 1 cup pecans and sprinkle lightly with mace.

title: miniature meatballs
directions: Mix ground beef, dry bread crumbs, onion, milk, egg, parsley, salt, pepper and Worcestershire sauce.
Gently shape into one-inch balls.

title: three berry compote
directions: Combine the first 7 ingredients in a bowl; stir well.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Garnish with mint sprigs.
Makes 4 servings.

title: oven macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni until tender, but firm.
Drain and rinse in hot water.
In a greased baking dish, place macaroni, butter, milk, salt, pepper and 1/2 cup cheese.
Mix well, then top with remaining cheese.
Bake in a 375° oven for 45 minutes or until desired crispness.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: hamburg things
directions: Put small roll of meat into the center of a flat biscuit. Wrap biscuit completely around mixture.
Pinch dough to seal.
Put on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° until golden brown, approximately 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 40 per pound of meat mixture.
Great right out of oven or cold.
Kids love them with ketchup.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients, except potato chips.
Place in a casserole dish.
Top with crumbled potato chips.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes at 400°.

title: greek spaghetti
directions: Saute onion in melted butter.
Add garlic salt and rosemary and remove from heat.
Salt and pepper meat and brown, add tomatoes with juice, tomato sauce and cooking wine.
Cook until thick, about 15 to 20 minutes.
Grease a 9 x 12-inch glass dish. Layer 1/2 meat sauce, all of spaghetti, spread soup on top of spaghetti, 1/2 of grated cheese, 1/2 of olives, remaining meat sauce, rest of cheese and rest of olives.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes, uncovered.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Cook macaroni and drain.
Brown hamburger and onion and drain.
Mix all ingredients together and pour into a casserole dish.
Bake at 400 degrees for 30 minutes.
Bake covered for first 15 minutes and then uncover.

title: mudworks
directions: Find an area in the yard that is good dirt with few rocks, sticks and leaves.
Loosen an area with a shovel or spade suitable for working, about 3 x 3 feet.
Add water from hose or bucket if too dry.
Mix with hands and spade or other tools. Enjoy creating mud pies, patties and other shapes.
Dry on plywood cookie sheets, then wash with soap and water.

title: german potato salad
directions: Fry bacon in large skillet until crisp.
Drain on paper towels and crumble.
Reserve 1/4 cup drippings.
In a large bowl, combine potatoes, green pepper, onion and crumbled bacon.

title: cake good
directions: Mix and bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: easy puff pastry
directions: Add salt and sugar to flour in mixing bowl; cut butter into flour as fine as possible, having butter very cold.
Beat eggs for 5 minutes; add lemon juice to eggs.
Add the cold water and mix flour into a stiff dough.
Lift dough to well floured board.
Roll out into rectangular shape; fold all four sides onto the dough. Roll again; repeat this process 4 times.
Fold again and wrap in a napkin, place on plate and stand on ice or let stand in refrigerator until thoroughly chilled.
Roll out again and use for patties, pie crust or tart shells.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour the boiling water over the oatmeal; let stand for 10 minutes to soak and cool.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs (well beaten).
Add oatmeal; mix well.
Add dry ingredients and beat.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: ooey gooey bar
directions: Mix cake mix, pecans, butter and 1 egg and pat in pan bottom (9 x 13).
Cream cheese and sugar.
Add 2 eggs and vanilla.
Mix well. Will be soupy.
Pour over crust.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes, until brown and firm on top.
May add coconut on top.

title: depression potato soup
directions: Peel and prepare vegetables.
In large saucepan, saute onion in margarine until clear.
Add vegetables, 2 teaspoons salt and cover with water; cook until vegetables are tender.

title: summer squash soup
directions: *Even a few more veggies are good.

title: buffet potatoes
directions: Combine potatoes and 1/2 cup butter.
Stir in sour cream, soup, onion, Cheddar, salt and pepper.
Place in 13 x 9-inch pan. Combine corn flakes and 1/2 cup butter, melted.
Sprinkle over top.
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Uncover and continue to bake for 20 minutes, or until potatoes are soft.

title: barbecue
directions: Cook altogether and simmer.

title: steak and gravy
directions: Cut steak into serving pieces.
Add salt and pepper to flour; mix well.
Dredge steak in flour.
Heat oil and brown meat on both sides.
Add remaining flour mixture to oil in pan, stirring well to form paste.
Brown, then add hot water and chopped onion. Bring to boil.
Add browned steak and simmer for 1/2 hour or until steak is tender.
Serve over mashed potatoes or cooked rice.

title: apple bread
directions: Place chopped apples and nuts in a bowl and add sugar.
Let stand 1 hour before mixing.
Stir often until moisture rises. Sift flour and spices in a bowl and stir in oil, eggs and vanilla. Add nuts and apple mixture to batter.
Bake at 325° until done (about 1 hour).
Makes 2 small loaves.
Wrap while hot.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix well; pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: additive-free canine cookies
directions: Blend flour and dry milk.
Add other ingredients and stir until well blended.
Gradually add 1 1/2 cups of cold water until dough is proper consistency.
Roll out on lightly floured surface.
Cut into 12 to 18 pieces or size to fit your dog.

title: greenbrier salad
directions: Dissolve lime jello and marshmallows in boiling water and cook for 10 minutes.
Add crushed pineapple and stir, then add cream cheese and fold in whipping cream.

title: chocolate chip icing
directions: Bring butter, sugar and milk to a boil and cook to almost soft ball stage.
Add chocolate chips and nuts.
Beat until chips are melted and pour quickly over cooled cake. (This icing gets hard like fudge.)

title: old fashioned egg custard
directions: Mix sugar and flour thoroughly.
Add well-beaten eggs, milk, flavoring and melted butter.
Pour into 9-inch unbaked pastry shell and bake very slowly in 350° oven for 45 minutes or until center is firm.
Nutmeg may be sprinkled on top if desired.

title: 7-layer bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan, melt the butter.
Sprinkle over it evenly the graham cracker crumbs and press them down.
Sprinkle on top the shredded coconut evenly. Next, add chocolate chips.
Next, add butterscotch chips.
Next, add condensed milk, dribbled evenly.
Finally, add the chopped nuts, and bake for 30 minutes.
Cool on wire rack and cut into squares.

title: pickled eggs
directions: Add sugar, salt and spices to vinegar (dilute 1/3 with water if strong) and simmer about 8 minutes.
Strain and pour over the peeled eggs arranged in a quart jar.
Seal and let stand 2 days before using.

title: chicken noodle casserole
directions: Boil and debone chicken.
Boil noodles in chicken stock.
Cook seasonings in oleo until transparent.
Add chicken, mushrooms, soup, onion tops and parsley.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Pour into casserole and cover with bread crumbs.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: egg salad
directions: Chop eggs up in a bowl.
Add the salt, pepper, relish and mayonnaise; mix well.
Chill or serve warm.

title: cheese dip
directions: Finely chop peppers.
Slowly melt cheese and other ingredients.
Stir until smooth and creamy.
Serve with nachos.

title: eggnog pie
directions: Toast coconut; set aside. Combine pie filling, sugar and nutmeg in saucepan. Add egg, cream, milk and bourbon. Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture comes to a full boil. Pour into bowl. Cover with plastic wrap and chill until cool, about 1 hour.

title: zucchini carrot bread
directions: Combine first five ingredients in a mixing bowl and set aside. Combine, oil, eggs, sugar and vanilla in a large bowl. Beat well. Stir in zucchini and carrots. Add flour mixture stirring just until moistened. Stir in the pecans and cereal.
Pour batter into two greased and floured loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool loaves 10 minutes in pans. Remove to wire racks and cool completely. Yields 2 loaves.

title: no cook divinity
directions: Beat dry frosting mix, corn syrup, vanilla and boiling water in small bowl on low speed until blended.
Beat on high speed until stiff peaks form (about 5 minutes).
Transfer to large bowl. Gradually beat in sugar on low speed.
Stir in nuts.
Drop mixture by teaspoonful onto wax paper.
Let stand until candy feels firm (about 4 hours).
Turn over and allow to dry (about 12 hours).
Store in airtight container up to 2 months.

title: easy pot roast
directions: Place roast in a large glass casserole dish and add vegetables.
Mix gravy according to package directions, reducing water by 1/8 cup.
Pour over roast and cover.
Cook 2 1/2 to 3 hours at 400° or until meat pulls apart easily.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: quick-n-easy chili con queso dip
directions: Bring water to boil in double boiler.
Cut Velveeta cheese into large dice squares and melt in double boiler.
When cheese is melted, add in Ro-Tel tomatoes and milk.
Stir approximately 3 to 5 minutes or until all ingredients are well mixed.
Serve warm as a dip or pour over chips.

title: golden sour cream chicken
directions: Add 1 tablespoon of garlic powder to sour cream.
Mix well. (Add more garlic powder if you like garlic.)
Dip each cutlet half into the sour cream mixture and coat completely, then dip in flavored bread crumbs.
Roll cutlet jelly roll fashion and place, seam side down, in roasting pan.
Top with pats of margarine. Heat soup mixed with 1 can of water.
Pour over cutlets and bake 40 to 45 minutes in a 350° oven.
Delicious cold.

title: gale's egg salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in a medium bowl. Stir until well blended. Refrigerate until cold. Makes a good sandwich.

title: million dollar pound cake
directions: Cream butter; gradually add sugar, beating well at medium speed of an electric mixer.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Add flour to cream mixture, alternately with milk, beginning and ending with flour; mix just until blended after each addition.
Stir in flavoring; pour batter into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 40 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center of cake comes out clean.
Cool in pan 15 minutes.
Remove from pan and let cool.

title: spicy black-eyed peas
directions: Sort and wash peas; place in a large Dutch oven.
Add water to cover peas 2-inches; let soak 8 hours.
Drain peas and return to Dutch oven.
Add 5 cups water and remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil; cover, reduce heat and simmer 45 minutes to 1 hour or until peas are tender, stirring occasionally.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: yogurt pie
directions: Combine 1/2 cup peaches with yogurt and Cool Whip.
Pour into crust and top with remaining 1/2 cup peaches.
Refrigerate for 45 minutes.

title: fruit cake
directions: Melt oleo.
Add sugar; mix well.
Add beaten eggs, wafer crumbs, milk and flavoring; mix well.
Add remaining ingredients. Bake for 1 hour at 325° in 1 large pan or 4 small pans.

title: quick coconut cake
directions: Mix sugar and sour cream together.
Add 1 1/2 packages coconut to mixture.
Place filling between layers and sprinkle with remainder of coconut; let stand overnight or several hours before serving.
Keep stored in refrigerator.

title: sauteed riverfront catfish cakes
directions: In food processor, blend scallops and cream together until a thick paste is formed. Fold in the rest of the ingredients except catfish; then fold in catfish. Makes about 20 1-1/2 ounce cakes. Saute in butter.

title: low calorie strawberry shortcake
directions: Add strawberries to jello and water. Break up cake and place in dish.
Pour mixture over top and refrigerate until set.

title: singleton's sweetheart punch
directions: Freeze 1 quart	of
cherry
soda
for
beverage
cubes. Chill remaining drinks.
When
ready
to serve, shave or crack beverage cubes, place
in punch bowl.
Add other sodas slowly. Garnish with orange and lemon slices.

title: green olive focaccia bread
directions: In large bowl, mix flour, yeast, sugar and salt.
Stir in hot water, milk and olive oil.
Mix in enough flour to make dough soft.
Add the olives and knead 4 minutes.

title: easy banana cake
directions: Combine and pour into 8 x 8-inch pan; bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: hickory stick
directions: Mix meat and all ingredients in a large roaster.
Mix well and marinate overnight in refrigerator, then mix again and form into rolls, 4 large or 6 small.
Bake on broiling pan for 3 1/2 hours at 250°.
Let cool and wrap.
Refrigerate or freeze.

title: coke-cocoa cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients in large mixing bowl.
In small pan, bring oleo and Coke to a boil.
Pour over dry ingredients and beat well.
Stir in marshmallows.
Pour in greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.
Top with Coke-Cocoa Icing.

title: mustard potatoes
directions: Cook and dice potatoes.
Dice the onion.
Melt the margarine and cook onion until limp.
Stir in the flour and add the stock. Cook over low heat and add the salt, pepper and the mustard.
Cook slowly, about ten minutes or until slightly thickened.
Pour over the potatoes and bake about 15 minutes in 350° oven.
Especially good with ham, ham loaf or chicken.

title: soft chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix flour and baking soda together. Combine butter, sugar, pudding and vanilla.
Beat until smooth.
Beat in eggs.
Gradually add flour mixture.
Stir in chips.
Batter will be stiff.
Drop by teaspoon 2 inches apart onto lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: chicken and dressing
directions: Mix
chicken
with
soup.
Put in casserole dish.
Pour milk over
chicken.
Top with stuffing.	Pour broth over all. Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: earthquake cake
directions: In greased 9 x 13-inch pan, spread pecans across bottom. Sprinkle coconut over pecans.
Mix cake mix as directed.
Pour over pecans and coconut.
In saucepan, melt margarine and cream cheese.
Add 10x sugar and stir until smooth.
Pour over cake mix. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: company casserole
directions: Boil noodles in salted water for 10 minutes; drain.
Brown meat; drain.
Stir in tomato sauce and remove from heat.
Combine cottage cheese, cream cheese, sour cream, green onions and green pepper.
Spread half the noodles in buttered 2-quart casserole. Cover with cheese mixture.
Top with remaining noodles and pour melted butter over top.
Put beef mixture over noodles.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: individual corn puddings
directions: Set oven for slow, 325°.
Combine all ingredients; mix well. Divide among 4 to 6 baking cups.
Set in pan of warm water.
Bake 45 minutes, or until firm in center.

title: jamaican festival
directions: Sift the first four ingredients.
Add the cornmeal and sugar. Add vanilla to the water.
Add the water to the dry ingredients, binding to form a soft dough.
Knead lightly.
Leave, covered, for 30 minutes.
Divide the dough into 8 portions.
Flour hands.
Knead lightly then roll and pull each portion to form a 6 x 1 1/2-inch length about 1/8-inch thick.
Dip Festival in flour and cornmeal mixture, then fry in plenty of hot oil until golden brown.
Pierce with a fork while frying.
If serving with fried fish, fry the Festival after the fish in the same oil.
Makes 8.

title: cream puff dessert
directions: Melt oleo in hot water and add flour.
Whisk together until dough forms into a ball.
Turn off heat and add eggs, one at a time, mixing in well with whisk.
Spread over greased 11 x 15-inch pan and bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Allow to cool.

title: grandma's carrot bread
directions: Mix sugar, margarine and eggs.
Sift together flour, cinnamon, soda, baking powder and salt.
Add flour mixture.
Add carrots and nuts.
Put in bread pan and bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: turkey dressing
directions: Crumble cornbread and biscuit in large bowl (should be in very small pieces).
Saute onions and celery in margarine in a black iron skillet.
Add to bread mixture.
Add finely chopped eggs, soup, sage, salt and pepper.
Add just enough buttermilk to make dressing moist and of the right consistency.

title: macaroni pie
directions: Layer cheese and macaroni alternately.
Beat eggs and milk together; pour over layers of macaroni and cheese.
Bake 20 minutes at 400° or until brown.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Spread pineapple on bottom of 1 1/2 to 2-quart dish.
Mix sugar and flour and sprinkle over pineapple.
Mix butter, crumbled crackers and grated cheese.
Sprinkle on top of flour and sugar; cover with 1/4 cup pineapple juice.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: mexican frito salad
directions: Brown 1 pound of hamburger meat. Add taco seasoning, drain and cool. Prepare lettuce, tomatoes and green onions. Add hamburger mixture and grated cheddar cheese and one can of Ranch Style Beans. Mix in Catalina dressing. Add Fritos just before serving.

title: snicker surprise salad
directions: Core and dice apples; leave skin on.
Cut bars 3 or 4 times lengthwise and then across to fairly small chunks.
Fold in La Creme.

title: ad lib soup
directions: Put all ingredients into blender container.
Cover and puree until smooth.
Pour into saucepan; heat over medium heat until hot.
Makes one serving, but increase portions as needed.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Mix cornstarch, sugar and salt in top of double boiler.
Add boiling water and blend thoroughly. Cook over direct heat, stirring constantly, until mixture is thick and clear.

Beat egg yolks and stir in a little of the hot mixture; pour back into double boiler and cook 2 minutes longer with constant stirring. Remove from heat. Add lemon juice, butter and lemon rind, mixing well. Cool and pour into pie shell. Beat egg whites until light. Add the 6 tablespoons sugar gradually and continue beating until stiff. Spread over pie filling so as to touch edges of crust all around and place in a moderate oven at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes or until golden brown. Cool before cutting.

title: microwave roux
directions: Cook on High for 4 minutes; stir.
Cook on High for 1 minute; stir.
Cook on High for 1 minute; stir.
Cook on High for 30 seconds; stir.
Keep cooking for 30 seconds at a time until dark enough.

title: italian pasta salad
directions: Toss all ingredients lightly and garnish with tomato.

title: mystery pie
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold in sugar and crackers.
Add vanilla and baking powder.
Bake in ungreased pie pan 375 degrees for 25-30 minutes.
Let cool and top with whipped cream.
Let stand in refrigerator 12 hours and serve.
Sprinkle with pecans, if desired.

title: cajun cake
directions: Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan and flour.
Mix first 5 ingredients together and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Add coconut and chopped pecans; stir and pour over cake while it's hot.

title: flour tortillas
directions: Mix flour, salt and baking powder. Cut Crisco in like for pie crust. Mix in water. Form a ball and knead 5 minutes. Let rest on table for 1/2 hour covered with bowl.

title: banana squares
directions: Grease an 8 x 13-inch pan well. Cream sugar and shortening in mixer. Add eggs.
Beat well. Add sour cream and remaining ingredients. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until done.

title: glazed ham-raisin balls
directions: Thoroughly mix ham, pork, milk, cereal, egg, onion, salt, pepper and thyme.
Shape into 8-10 balls, using about 1/4 cup of ham mixture for each.
Place in 11x7x1 1/2 inch
baking pan. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 20 minutes.
In small saucepan, combine brown sugar, corn syrup, vinegar and dry mustard; bring to a boil.
Pour over ham balls and bake for 20 minutes, basting with sauce once or twice.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients in a saucepan.
Cook for 10 minutes (a hard boil).
Stir in 1 teaspoon baking soda.
Spread quickly on greased pan or cookie sheet.
Let cool and turn out.

title: quick cheese cake
directions: Line pan
with	1 package of crescent rolls.
Cream the cream cheese,
sugar, egg yolk, vanilla and lemon juice.	Pour on top of rolls.
Place remaining package of crescent rolls on top of cheese mixture.
Fork whip egg white and spread on top. Sprinkle with nuts
and
bake.
Bake
at 350° in ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan
for 25 minutes.
When cool, if desired, sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: alberta toomey's total cake
directions: Mix cereal and orange juice or crushed pineapple in a large bowl and let stand for 2 minutes.
Then add other ingredients in order as listed.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: easy good frosting
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff; slowly add powdered sugar and beat well.
Add butter, vanilla extract, and salt.
Spread on cake.
(Add food coloring if desired.)

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Place half of strawberries in saucepan with cornstarch, sugar, water and lemon juice.
Cook, stirring often, until berries are soft and mixture is thickened.
Cool.
Stir in remaining berries. Pour into pastry shell.
Chill until firm.
Serve with whipped cream and garnish with whole strawberries.

title: pecan chess pie
directions: Melt butter; add sugar, cornmeal, eggs, vanilla, milk, vinegar and nuts.
Pour into unbaked pie crust.
Bake for 1 hour at 325°.

title: autumn salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Make cranberry sauce and add to jello.
Chill until syrupy.
Fold in other ingredients and chill until firm.

title: cheese cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Beat in the egg, then dry ingredients.
Line an 8 x 8-inch baking dish (greased) with dough. If the dough is hard to handle, then chill first.
Drain crushed pineapple and spread when filling is ready.

title: easy red beans and rice(makes 10 servings. prep time: 15 minutes.)
directions: Bring water, rice and butter to hard boil.
Cover and simmer for 20 minutes.
Put a little oil in large frying pan and saute meat and onion.
Brown for five minutes and add tomatoes and beans with seasonings.
Heat to boiling, then reduce heat to simmer and cover for about 15 minutes.
Remove lid and let simmer about 15 more minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: apple "dump" cake
directions: Dump apple pie filling in dish.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over apples.
Sprinkle brown sugar on top of cake mix.
Then the oats, butter and nuts.
Bake 60 minutes at 325°.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Heat oil in large skillet.
Add onion, pepper, celery and garlic.
Cook until just tender.
Add mushrooms, tomatoes and seasonings.
Simmer uncovered 10 to 15 minutes or until somewhat thickened.
Stir in shrimp and continue cooking until shrimp is just heated through.
Serve over steamed rice.
Season with fresh chopped parsley just before serving.
Serves 4.

title: fruited pot roast
directions: Brown roast in hot oil; add wine and vegetables.
Season with salt and pepper.
Cook 2 1/2 to 3 hours on low heat.
Soak dried fruit in hot water for 1 hour.
Add to roast last 45 minutes of cooking time.
Remove meat and make gravy with 1/2 cup water and 3 tablespoons flour.

title: ham loaf
directions: Mix and place in a loaf pan or form into a loaf and place in a casserole.
Bake at 350° about 2 hours.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix flour, salt and baking soda.
Set aside.
Mix shortening and peanut butter.
Add both kinds of sugar.
Mix well.
Add eggs and beat well.
Stir flour mixture into peanut butter mixture. Roll into one big ball.
Drop dough from a teaspoon onto a baking sheet.
Flatten with a fork.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes until lightly browned.
Makes 5 to 6 dozen cookies.

title: pepperoni mushroom pizza
directions: Mix rice, egg and Cheddar cheese.
Press into a 10-inch pie plate.
Bake at 400° for 4 minutes or microwave for 2 minutes.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Melt butter in pan.
Add chopped onion and chicken.
Cook until onions become transparent.
Add mushroom soup and milk. Should be as thick as a gravy sauce.
Add cheese (as much as you like to your taste).
Simmer until cheese is all melted.
Serve over cooked spaghetti.

title: stir-fry chicken and cabbage
directions: Sprinkle seasoned salt and garlic salt on chicken.
Fry chicken and carrots in oil until carrots are tender and chicken browns.
Add cabbage and tomatoes; fry until cooked.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Serves 4.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef and onion and drain.
Mix together the tomatoes, tomato paste, water, 1 tablespoon of parsley, garlic powder and oregano and add to meat; heat to boiling.

title: beef soup
directions: Brown beef and drain.
Place in deep pan and add water and simmer.
Add the rest of the ingredients after one hour and simmer for 3 to 4 hours.
Serve with noodles and hot rolls.

title: oven fried potatoes
directions: Spray a large baking sheet with Pam.
Wash potatoes; cut into 1/2-inch slices.
Do not peel potatoes.
Mix water and oil in a large bowl.
Add potatoes; toss until coated.
Place on pan; sprinkle with seasoned salt.
Bake at 475° for 15 minutes.
Turn over and bake an additional 15 minutes.
Makes 4 servings, 119 calories per serving.

title: holly's magic bars
directions: In 13 x 9-inch baking pan, melt butter and crumbs, mix together.
Pour sweetened condensed milk evenly over crumbs. Top with chocolate chips, coconut and nuts.
Press down gently.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool.
Cut.

title: beef stew
directions: In a 3-quart casserole, combine meat, water, sliced onion, bay leaf, salt, Worcestershire sauce, sugar, pepper, garlic powder and cloves.
Cover.
Microwave at High 5 minutes.
Reduce power to Medium and microwave 40 minutes, stirring occasionally to prevent sticking.
Remove bay leaf. Add vegetables.
Cover.
Microwave 35 to 45 minutes, or until meat and vegetables are tender.
Blend flour into water; stir into stew.
Microwave at High 3 to 4 minutes, or until bubbly, stirring once or twice.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Depending on size of vegetables, time will be longer if all ingredients are added at once.
Serves 6 to 8.
Can also be done on the stove or in slow pot.

title: chocolate covered cherry cake
directions: Mix well with fork.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool; spread icing on cake.

title: almond cookies(china)
directions: Preheat oven to 350.
Cream sugars with the margarine.
Add the egg and almond extract.
Beat until fluffy.
Sift flour and baking powder together and fold into the mixture a little at a time.
Beat lightly to make a smooth dough.
DO NOT knead the mixture too much, or the cookies will be hard.
Shape the dough into balls the size of a walnut.
Dip the top of the cookies into sesame seeds (you may need to slightly dampen the top of each with a little water).
Lightly press an almond half into the center of the dough ball and flatten a little.
Place the cookies about 1 inch apart on a cookie sheet.
Bake 8-10 minutes or until golden brown.
Store in air-tight container.
Makes 24 cookies.

title: creamy french dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together well and refrigerate.

title: tossed tuna salad
directions: Drain tuna.
Slice green pepper into strips.
Slice zucchini into thin rounds.
Cut pimiento into thin strips.
Toss lettuce, tomato, green pepper, zucchini, onion, pimiento and olives. Gently toss in tuna.
Combine mayonnaise, vinegar, oil, paprika and cayenne; blend well.
Pour over salad, tossing to serve. Makes 4 servings.

title: crab salad
directions: Mix well and keep in refrigerator.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Cook eggplant in a little water; mash.
Beat well.
Saute onion in butter.
Add to mashed eggplant with salt and pepper. Turn into greased 1-quart casserole.
Top with bread crumbs and cheese mixed together.
Bake in preheated oven at 375° for 30 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: georgia peach shortcake
directions: Grease and flour 2 (9-inch) square pans.
Beat egg yolks. Gradually add 1/2 cup sugar.
Combine flour, cocoa, 1/4 cup sugar and baking soda.
Add alternately with water and 1 teaspoon vanilla on low speed.
Beat egg whites in small mixing bowl until foamy.
Add 2 tablespoons sugar and beat until stiff.
Carefully fold beaten eggs to chocolate mixture.
Spread batter into pan. Bake at 375° for 14 to 16 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes.
Beat cream, confectioners sugar and 1 teaspoon vanilla until stiff.
Frost one cake with 1 cup of whipped cream.
Fill center with peaches. Place second cake on top and repeat.
Chill 1 hour.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients, except corn flakes and butter.
Pour in 2 1/2-quart greased casserole.
Crush corn flakes; stir in butter.
Sprinkle on potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes. Serves 10 to 12.

title: hot spiced wassail
directions: Put spices in top of percolator.
Add juices to the bottom and perk.
Or tie spices in cheesecloth, add to juices and simmer, covered, for 10 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: peppercorn chicken breasts
directions: Place chicken between sheets of plastic wrap.
Pound with flat edge of mallet to about 1/4-inch thickness.
Sprinkle with the peppercorns.

title: wiener schnitzel
directions: Cut meat into halves.
This should give you 4 pieces.
Pound the meat until they are tender.
Sprinkle both sides of meat with the seasoned salt; press them lightly into the flour.
Dip in eggs until covered and then transfer them into the bread crumbs.
Heat 1/2 cup oil (may vary depending on pan size) until hot.
Turn heat to medium, lay the meat (schnitzel) in the oil, cooking each side 2 to 3 minutes or until golden brown.
Take schnitzel out and put into plate with lemon slice on top.
Serve with potato salad or tossed salad.

title: hush puppies
directions: Serve these golden, light and delicately sweet muffins with a cake-like texture for breakfast or brunch or with baked ham for dinner.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Drain green beans, peas and corn.
Chop green pepper, onion and celery.
Mix all ingredients in large bowl and refrigerate overnight.

title: fudge balls
directions: Mix together by kneading.
Form into small balls.
Roll in crushed nuts or flaked coconut.

title: chocolate snowballs
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and vanilla until fluffy.
Sift flour with cocoa and add to creamed mixture.
Use back of wooden or other large spoon to blend thoroughly.
Add pecans, again using back of spoon to blend thoroughly.
Dough will be very thick. Roll teaspoonfuls of dough into small balls and bake on ungreased nonstick baking sheet in 325° oven for 20 minutes.
Cool and roll in powdered sugar.
Store in tins or other covered containers.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Mix salt, pepper and flour.
Sprinkle between layers of potatoes and onions.
Add milk, dot with butter and bake in oven.

title: chicken loaf
directions: Beat eggs; add milk and remaining ingredients.
Bake in buttered loaf pan in moderate oven (325°) for 30 minutes.
Unmold, slice and serve with mushroom sauce.

title: cherry chocolate surprise
directions: Mix all ingredients according to package directions.
Oil pan lightly and sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: lobster bisque
directions: Combine chicken stock, onion, celery, cloves, bay leaf and peppercorns in saucepan.
Simmer for 30 minutes.
Strain, reserving stock.
Melt butter in saucepan.
Blend in flour.
Add milk gradually.
Cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Stir in lobster and reserved stock.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
Stir in hot cream at serving time.
Do not boil.
Garnish with paprika. Serves 6.

title: venison stew
directions: From an old recipe file of Winifred Loers Freund (Mrs. Ralph).

title: spice tea
directions: Boil tea bags, cinnamon sticks, whole cloves and water for 30 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients to pitcher and fill with water. Makes a gallon.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Place potatoes (seasoned with salt and pepper) in 9 x 13-inch pan; add pork chops and green beans.
Cover with mushroom soup. Put foil on top.
Bake at 350° until done, about 40 minutes. Uncover; brown and serve.

title: grilled stuffed franks
directions: Combine tomato sauce, sugar, mustard and garlic powder.
Stir well.
Slice frankfurters lengthwise to make a pocket.
Brush inside each pocket with sauce; sprinkle with onion.
Wrap each frankfurter with bacon, securing with a toothpick (wooden).
Cook frankfurters over hot coals 10 to 15 minutes or until bacon is crisp, turning often and basting with remaining sauce.
Serve in hot dog buns.
Serves 8.

title: mushroom burgers
directions: In a bowl mix eggs, mushrooms, flour, bread crumbs, onion and spice.
Mix well; flatten in small patties.
In skillet, heat oil and fry on both sides until golden.

title: pineapple cream pie
directions: Combine pineapple and pudding from the boxes and add sour cream; stir well.
Pour into baked crust.
Add Cool Whip on top. Refrigerate several hours before serving.

title: swedish nut cake
directions: Mix all ingredients by hand.
Pour onto greased cookie sheet. Bake at 325° for 20 to 30 minutes or until very light brown.

title: spicy raisin scones
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Lightly grease a baking sheet.
Combine flour, sugar and spices in a mixing bowl.
Cut butter or margarine into flour, with pastry blender or blending fork, until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Stir in raisins.
Combine milk and egg; add to flour mixture.
Stir until combined.

title: sausage balls
directions: In large bowl combine ingredients.
Knead to form soft dough. Shape into 1-inch balls.
Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 20 minutes in 350° oven until golden.
Serve hot.
Can be frozen. Makes 72 balls.

title: lemon meringue pie(excellent)
directions: Bake and cool pastry.
In saucepan combine the 1 cup sugar, the flour, cornstarch and salt.
Stir in water.
Cook and stir over medium heat until thickened and clear.
Add a little hot mixture to egg yolks; return all to hot mixture.
Cook 1 minute more; stir constantly.
Remove from heat; blend in butter, lemon peel and juice.
Pour mixture into pastry shell.
Beat egg whites until soft peaks form.
Gradually add the 6 tablespoons sugar; beat to stiff peaks.
Spread over hot filling.
Bake at 425° for five minutes, until brown.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Tear up bread and place in a 9 x 13-inch greased dish.
Brown and drain sausage.
Spoon sausage over bread.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Beat together eggs, milk, mustard, salt and pepper.
Pour mixture in casserole.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Serves 6 people.

title: spiced peaches
directions: To juice, add remaining ingredients.
Boil liquid and sugar 4 to 5 minutes.
Add peaches and simmer 5 minutes more.
Chill.

title: graham cracker village
directions: Mix shortening and vanilla in large mixing bowl.
Gradually beat in 2 cups powdered sugar.
Add 2 tablespoons milk and enough milk for piping consistency.
Will put together 10 buildings using 5 to 6 squares of graham crackers per house.

title: waikiki meatballs
directions: Mix meat, crumbs, onion, egg, salt, ginger and milk.
Shape mixture into balls.
Fry in melted shortening.
Remove and keep warm.
Mix cornstarch and sugar.
Stir in pineapple syrup, vinegar and soy sauce until smooth.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and boils.
Add meatballs, pineapple tidbits and green peppers.
Simmer for 10 minutes. Serve with rice.

title: salmon patties
directions: Heat skillet.
Melt Crisco in pan.
Drain salmon.
Mix in large bowl with all ingredients; mix well.
Drop by rounded tablespoonful into hot grease.
Brown and serve.
Cook about 5 minutes.

title: chicken marsala
directions: Dredge chicken in flour.
In large skillet, melt butter.
Add chicken to skillet and cook until browned on each side.
Remove to serving platter.
Add shallots to skillet; cook until tender. Stir in water, Marsala, mushrooms, parsley and salt.
Cook, stirring to deglaze the pan, until the mushrooms are tender. Return chicken to pan.
Cook, turning once, until both sides are coated and sauce thickens.

title: tuna cakes
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Salt and pepper to taste. Pat out into patties and fry in 1 tablespoon oil.
May add a slice of cheese on top.

title: fruit nibbles
directions: Combine rum, juice and extract.
Pour over fruit and refrigerate.
Serve with wooden picks.
(Can use other fruits.)

title: absolutely great pork chops!
directions: Season meat with salt and pepper; brown in skillet.
Combine remaining ingredients; pour over meat.
Cover; simmer for 45 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: johnny marzetti
directions: Fry and stir the chuck.
Fry bacon; drain on a paper towel, crumble into bits and add to the fried chuck.
Saute onions, pepper and celery; mix with mushrooms.
Salt and pepper cooked, drained noodles.
Mix and store in refrigerator overnight.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Mix together pudding and milk.
Add Cool Whip, then place a layer of graham crackers in pan.
Add half of pudding mixture. Add layer of graham crackers.
Add half of pudding mixture.
Add layer of graham crackers.
Frost with canned chocolate frosting. Chill.

title: mediterranean chicken
directions: Rinse chicken well.
In a bag, combine flour, salt and pepper. Shake chicken (few pieces at a time) in flour mixture to coat.
In a large skillet, brown chicken in oil.
Remove from skillet.
Add mushrooms, parsley, garlic and thyme.
Cook until mushrooms are tender.
Add artichoke hearts and olives.
Return chicken to skillet.
Mix together tomato paste and wine.
Pour over chicken. Simmer covered 40 minutes or until chicken is no longer pink inside.
Sprinkle with additional parsley, if desired.

title: tomato gravy
directions: Melt bacon drippings in an iron skillet over medium heat; stir in flour until smooth and medium brown; stir in tomatoes, salt and pepper; simmer 20 minutes; and serve with biscuits.

title: breezy cheesy macaroni
directions: Cook macaroni as directed on package; drain in colander. Return macaroni to cooking pan.
Add cheese, milk and butter. Stir until cheese melts.
If necessary, place over low heat a few minutes to help the melting.
Ready to serve.
Serves 4.

title: bobbe ande pie
directions: Mix eggs with wire whisk very well.
Gradually add rest of ingredients.
Pour into unbaked 9-inch pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Turn down to 350° until set, about 30 minutes.

title: navy bean soup
directions: Wash beans and soak in water for 2 to 3 hours.
Drain water from beans and add 1 gallon fresh water.
Add whole onion, celery leaves, ham hocks and garlic.
Bring to a gentle boil and continue cooking this way for 2 hours.

title: carrots a la flamande
directions: Parboil carrots in salted water for 5 minutes; drain well. Melt 2 tablespoons butter in a saucepan.
Add the carrots, beef broth and sugar.
Cover and simmer until well cooked.
Reduce the broth until practically nothing and add the remaining butter and parsley.

title: diet no bake cookies
directions: Cook the first 4 ingredients in saucepan until it bubbles and gets thick.
Take off of stove.
Have ready the packs of Equal, oats, vanilla and raisins.
Mix all together and drop by teaspoonfuls on wax paper.

title: chicken picante
directions: Add equal amounts of water and picante sauce as per rice directions.
Saute onion, green peppers and garlic (if desired). Mix rice, sauteed veggies and chicken; place in greased baking pan.
Bake 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle shredded Cheddar cheese and sliced black olives on top and return to oven until cheese melts.

title: nutty marshmallow log
directions: Combine pecans and 1 cup powdered sugar; sprinkle evenly over a large sheet of waxed paper and set aside.
Melt marshmallows in top of a double boiler; stir in peanut butter.
Pour mixture over powdered sugar-pecan mixture.
Mix with hands until pecans and sugar are blended into marshmallow mixture and mixture resembles soft dough.
Shape into 2 rolls, 1-inch in diameter.
Let stand about 45 minutes.
Roll candy in remaining powdered sugar.
Let stand 30 minutes.
Cut into 1/4-inch slices.
Store in a covered container, separating
layers with waxed paper.
Yield:
About 100 slices.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream the fat, sugar and peanut butter. Add egg, then flour and soda sifted together.
Roll 1/2 teaspoon dough into a small ball and place on pan. Press flat with fork.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.

title: french oven toast
directions: Combine beaten eggs, salt, sugar, milk and almond extract. Dip sliced bread into mixture.
Place slices on well-greased cookie sheet and brown in extremely hot oven at 500°.
Turn toast after 10 minutes and brown on other side.
Serve with honey butter or maple syrup.
Makes 6 servings, 2 slices per serving.
(This toast may be reheated satisfactorily.)

title: ann's cherry crunch
directions: Mix together butter, flour and nuts.
Pat over bottom and sides of 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.
Let cool.
Blend together softened cream cheese, Cool Whip, lemon juice and powdered sugar.
Pour over crust and top with cherry pie filling.
Make a day in advance.

title: roast
directions: Put everything together in cooking bag. Cook on 425 degrees for about 1 hour, or until meat is done.

title: pecan kisses
directions: In a small bowl, beat egg whites with vinegar, extract and salt at high speed until soft peak forms.
Gradually add sugar. Continue beating until stiff peak forms. Fold in pecans.
Drop by teaspoons on cookie sheet covered with brown paper.
