Bake at 275° for 40 to 50 minutes until crisp and very lightly browned.
Makes about 48.

title: shish-kabob
directions: Marinate the steak in soy sauce with a dash of ginger added. Thread ingredients on skewers in whatever order you want.
Cook in oven or over grill.

title: magically moist chicken
directions: Brush chicken on all sides with real mayonnaise.
Place bread crumbs in large plastic
food
bag.
Add chicken 1 piece at a time.
Shake to coat well.
Place on rack in broiler pan. Bake at 400° for 45 minutes
or until golden brown and tender. Makes 4 servings.

title: lightning cake
directions: Soften butter, then cream.
Add sugar and beat until smooth. Add yolks and beat.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk and vanilla.
Pour dough into 8-inch layer cake pans.
Beat egg whites and add 1/3 cup sugar.
Spread egg white mixture on top of the dough.
Sprinkle nuts evenly on top of meringue.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until slightly brown.

title: chipped beef cheese ball
directions: Mix and form into ball.
Serve with crackers.

title: three bean salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and let stand in refrigerator overnight.

title: dijonnaise potatoes
directions: Scrub and dry potatoes; don't peel.
Cut into 3/4-inch slices. Place in casserole dish.
Pour melted butter over potatoes.
Add salt, pepper, garlic powder and mustard.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour or until tender, stirring occasionally.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream sugars and shortening.
Add eggs and vanilla, then add potato chips, nuts, flour, soda and salt.
Roll into balls.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: scallop fettucini
directions: Cook fettucini and drain.

title: peanut butter cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt over hot (not boiling) water, 1/2 cup peanut butter morsels.
Stir until smooth.
Set aside.
In small bowl, combine flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Set aside.
In large bowl, combine butter and sugar; beat until creamy. Blend in melted morsels.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Alternately blend in flour and milk.
Pour into two greased and floured 8-inch round pans.
Bake until crust is golden brown, 35 to 40 minutes. Cool 10 minutes.
Remove from pans.
Cool cake completely.
Fill layers and frost sides and top with Peanut Butter Cream Frosting.

title: ice cream
directions: Beat eggs; add evaporated milk, Eagle Brand milk and vanilla. Sift cornstarch and powdered sugar together; add to mixture.
Pour into freezer can, filling with milk to about 2 to 3 inches from top.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: fish a la creme
directions: Marinate fish in lemon juice for 10 minutes. Mix butter, soup and sour cream. Pour over fish. Broil 10 minutes. Bake in 350° oven until it starts to bubble or turn brown. Serves 2.

title: brown rim cookies
directions: Cream together the Crisco, salt, vanilla and sugar.
Add the beaten eggs and flour.
Mix together.
Drop by teaspoonful on a greased cookie sheet.
Flatten with a glass dipped in sugar.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: dirty rice
directions: Bake, uncovered, approximately 1 hour at 375°.

title: irish potato candy
directions: Boil the potato until soft.
Peel and mash. Add sugar until stiff enough to roll flat.
Spread over surface with peanut butter.
Roll, chill and slice.

title: baked breaded chicken
directions: mix all the above together and dip chicken in melted butter and roll in the above mixture.
bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour.

title: fudge pie
directions: Melt margarine.
Add eggs, cocoa and vanilla.
Sift in flour and sugar.
Stir all ingredients until blended.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
May be served warm or cool.
Delicious with vanilla ice cream, whipped cream or plain.

title: pimento spread
directions: Heat milk in double boiler, but do not boil.
Add grated cheese, work smooth.
Add to the other ingredients.
Will keep 10 days in refrigerator.

title: broccoli roll-ups
directions: Heat water or broth in a saucepan over medium heat.
Add green pepper, onion and mushrooms.
Cook and stir over medium heat for 5 minutes or until vegetables are lightly browned.
Add more liquid, if needed.
Add parsley, oregano, thyme and tomato sauce.
Simmer over very low heat for 10 minutes.

title: red bean gumbo
directions: Make roux.
Add onions and cook until they shrink a little. Add the beans blended in blender.
Let come to a boil and add approximately 3 cans of water.
Cook for about 25 minutes.
Lower fire and break eggs, one at a time, in a cup and drop in mixture until all 12 are dropped.
Make sure eggs are spaced.

title: spiced peaches
directions: Drain peaches; save syrup.
Combine syrup, sugar, vinegar, cinnamon sticks and cloves in a saucepan.
Bring to boil, then lower heat and simmer for 10 minutes.
Pour hot syrup over peaches.
Let cool, then store in refrigerator.

title: italian potatoes
directions: Line baking dish with foil.
Dice potatoes and onion and place in dish (8 x 12-inch).
Sprinkle with garlic salt and Italian seasoning.
Cut up butter over potatoes.
Close foil securely. Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Open foil and sprinkle with lemon juice. Stir and cook an additional 15 minutes or until done.

title: spanish rice
directions: Fry hamburger with onion, pepper, garlic powder, salt and pepper.
While hamburger is frying, cook rice until done.
Add drained hamburger mixture and tomato sauce.
Mix well and serve. We like to serve with lettuce salad and garlic bread.

title: moose milk
directions: Mix several seconds in the blender. Serve in cocktail glasses.

title: pumpkin pie cake
directions: Mix and pour into a 13 x 9-inch cake pan, lined with waxed paper.
Sprinkle following mixture over mixture in pan.

title: katie's artichoke dip
directions: Chop artichoke hearts into small pieces.
Mix with mayonnaise and cheese.
Bake at 325° for about 20 minutes or until bubbling. Serve with crisp baked pita pieces or Triscuits.

title: elephant stew
directions: Cut elephants into small pieces (this usually takes about 2 months).
Add enough water for brown gravy.
Cook over kerosene fire at 465° for about 4 weeks.
Serves about 3,800.
If more are expected, add the rabbits, but only if necessary, because most people do not like hare in their stew.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Chill at least 2 hours.

title: perch, bass or crappie cocktail
directions: Bring water to boil and add sugar and salt.
Drop fish into water.
Boil until done, 3 to 5 minutes.
Plunge into ice water to cool.
Serve with cocktail sauce as you would crab or shrimp cocktail.
Delicious!

title: cashew chicken
directions: Beat egg and milk together; soak chicken in mixture overnight. Dredge in flour and fry in hot oil until golden brown; drain.

title: cheese grits
directions: Bring water to boil; add salt and grits.
Stir and cook until thick, about 4 minutes.
While this mixture is hot, add remaining ingredients.
Mix well, then pour into greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° until firm, about 35 to 40 minutes.

title: pastel banana bobs
directions: Note:
Need 16 wooden ice cream sticks.

title: yum yum salad
directions: Combine pineapple and sugar.
Cook for 3 minutes.
Add Jell-O and cream cheese; stir until well mixed.
Cook until mixture begins to congeal.
Add celery, apple and nuts.
Prepare Dream Whip. Leave out the vanilla.
Fold into Jell-O mixture.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Chill 6 hours or overnight.
Serves 12.

title: white brownies
directions: Mix and bake in a greased 13 x 9-inch pan for 35 to 40 minutes on 350°.

title: macaroni and cheese casserole
directions: Melt margarine in saucepan.
Saute onion until transparent. Blend in flour and seasonings.
Stir in milk gradually; cook until thickened.
Add cheese; stir until melted.
Add macaroni.
Pour into a greased 2-quart baking dish.
Slice tomato and arrange on top.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese over surface.
Bake in a moderate 375° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: sausage bread
directions: Note:
Hot or sweet may be used.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients in casserole dish and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Let butter get room temperature.
Mix butter and sugar, putting in one egg at a time while mixing.
Sift flour 2 or 3 times, then add flour to butter, sugar and eggs.
Mix well, then add 7-Up.
Pour into well-greased and floured Bundt pan. Bake 1 hour at 335°.

title: spanish salad
directions: Chop for salad.
Just before serving, add 1 package Fritos and dressing to taste.

title: vegetable juice
directions: Chop celery, green pepper and onions.
Cook these in a pressure cooker in 1 pint of water for 5 minutes.
When finished, run through blender to make pulp.
Add this and other ingredients to tomatoes.
Bring to a rolling boil and then put in jars. Process 10 minutes on number 5 pressure in pressure canner.

title: orange salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in refrigerator until set.
Chill before adding topping.

title: barbecue baked beans
directions: Saute bacon until almost crisp.
Add onion and continue to saute until onion is tender.
After draining fat, combine with remaining ingredients in 1-quart baking dish.
Set oven at 375° and bake, uncovered, for 45 to 50 minutes, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: unfried fries
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Slice each potato lengthwise into 1/4-inch slices, then cut each slice lengthwise into matchsticks. Mix egg whites and Cajun spice in a bowl.
Add potatoes and mix to coat.
Spread on baking sheet that has been sprayed with nonstick spray.
Spread in single layer, leaving space between.
Place on bottom shelf of oven.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes.
Turn every 6 to 8 minutes to brown evenly.

title: kahlua
directions: Simmer for 45 minutes.
Remove from heat and leave overnight, then strain.
Add 5 cups of vodka and put in bottles.
Leave for six weeks.

title: fork cookies
directions: Cream the
sugars
with
the
Crisco.
Add the eggs and flavoring; beat.
Add other ingredients.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto cookie sheet.
Use
a salad fork to press down.
Dip fork in water to keep from sticking.
Bake at 400° about 8 minutes.

title: fudge brownie pie
directions: Use 8-inch glass pie plate. Mix all ingredients together and mix well.
Pour into greased pie plate and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
It makes its own crust.
Top with whipped cream. Yields 8 servings.

title: cee's yams and apples
directions: Parboil the yams until tender; peel and slice.
Slice the apples, leaving peels on.
Alternate layers of yams and apples in a 9 x 12-inch Pyrex dish with apples ending up on top layer.
Mix the sugar, water, salt and cornstarch.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Add the butter; stir until melted.
Pour over yams and apples; sprinkle with cinnamon.
Cover with foil; bake at 350° for 1 hour.
This is a crowd pleaser at our house!

title: homemade chili
directions: Cook kidney beans in 2 quarts of water and 1 teaspoon salt until beans are soft (approximately 6 hours).
Cook ground beef with onion; season with salt and pepper.
Add bell pepper, garlic clove, kidney beans (undrained), chili powder, tomato sauces and whole tomatoes.

title: carrot bran muffins
directions: Sift together flour, soda, baking powder, salt and cinnamon. Add bran.
Set aside.
Beat eggs.
Add oil, sugar and molasses. Add carrots, flour mixture and raisins.
Fill 24 greased muffin tins 3/4 full.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Yields 24 large muffins.

title: texas pecan pie
directions: Arrange pecans in bottom of pie shell.
(If using frozen shells, use both.)
Combine eggs, oleo, syrup and vanilla until well blended.
Combine sugar and flour; add to egg mixture.
Pour over pecans in shell(s).
Let stand until pecans rise to the top. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: overnite salad
directions: Drain pineapple and oranges (keep juices).
Place juices, lemon juice and water in saucepan.
Stir in pudding mix; cook and stir over medium heat until mixture comes to full boil.
Remove from heat and cool.
Add in pineapple, oranges and marshmallows. Fold in Cool Whip, chill overnight.
Before serving fold in bananas.

title: macaroni and cheese casserole
directions: Cook macaroni according to directions.
Drain and place in a buttered casserole dish.
Melt butter in a double boiler, then add flour, salt and pepper.
Stir well.
Add milk slowly until sauce thickens.
Cut cheese into cubes and add to sauce, stirring constantly, until cheese has melted.
Pour cheese sauce over macaroni and top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: blueberry jello mold
directions: Dissolve 1 package jello in hot water (1 cup) and 1 cup juice from blueberries and gel firmly in refrigerator.
Dissolve 2nd package jello into 1 cup hot water and 1/2 cup cold water.
When slightly set, whip jello.
Prepare mixture of cream cheese, whipped topping, cream, vanilla and sugar; when partially thickened, add to whipped jello and blend together.
Pour this part over the first gelled part in the mold.
Refrigerate to gel firmly.

title: buttermilk pound cake
directions: Cream butter with sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well to incorporate each one.
Add vanilla.
Add buttermilk alternately with the dry ingredients which have been sifted together.
Beat until smooth.

title: bean soup
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large pot and simmer 2 hours, stirring occasionally.
Serve with hot cornbread and onion wedges.

title: oven-fried yogurt chicken
directions: Skin chicken thighs.
Mix dry ingredients.
Coat thighs with yogurt, then bread crumb mixture.
Place in baking dish.
Drizzle margarine over the chicken.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes or until tender.

title: chicken imperial
directions: Place one 3 to 4 pound frying hen in a large covered soup kettle with enough water to cover the bird.
Add a bay leaf, salt, pepper and poultry seasoning to taste.
Make sure you have removed the entrails from the bird, but include the giblets (heart, liver and neck) in the pot.

title: homemade cracker jacks
directions: Put Ritz Bits and peanuts into a large roaster.
Mix sugar, syrup and oleo; boil for 5 minutes.
Add soda and vanilla.
Pour over dry ingredients in roaster.
Mix well.
Bake 20 minutes. Burns very quickly.
Cool a few minutes and spread out on wax paper.
Store in sealed container.
Spray Pam on spoon to prevent sticking.

title: microwave two minute fudge
directions: Grease an 8-inch square baking pan. Microwave the chocolate chips and milk, uncovered, in a 2-quart bowl on High for 2 minutes. Stir until smooth. Stir in sugar and vanilla, then nuts until well blended.
Pour into prepared pan, spreading evenly. Chill until firm, about 1 1/2 hours.
Cut into 16 (2-inch) pieces.

title: shoo-fly cake
directions: Make crumbs of first 3 ingredients; reserve 1 cup of crumbs. Mix last 4 ingredients together, then add the crumbs.
Mix together.
Sprinkle the reserved cup of crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: barbecued roast
directions: Brown roast in large saucepan.
Place onion chunks on roast. Combine red pepper, brown sugar, dry mustard, Worcestershire sauce, pepper sauce, catsup, vinegar, water, liquid smoke and chili powder in bowl; mix well.
Pour over roast.
Cook for 2 hours, or to desired degree of doneness.
Yields 12 servings.

title: taco topped potatoes
directions: Scrub potatoes; prick several times with fork.
Microwave until done; let stand 2 minutes.
Brown the ground beef and onion in a large skillet, stirring until beef crumbles; drain.
Stir in seasoning mixture and water; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; simmer, stirring occasionally, for 15 minutes, or until liquid evaporates.
Stir in taco sauce; cook until thoroughly heated. Cut an "X" to within 1/2-inch of bottom of each potato.
Squeeze potatoes from opposite sides and ends to open.
Fluff potato pulp with fork.
Spoon meat mixture on potatoes; sprinkle with cheese. Yields 4 servings.

title: grape-nuts pudding
directions: Put Grape-Nuts in milk.
Beat eggs.
Add sugar and vanilla. Add to Grape-Nuts mixture.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.
Serve warm with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: chicken cordon bleu
directions: Stuff each 1/2 chicken breast with one slice Swiss cheese and one slice of ham.
Then wrap and secure each chicken breast with bacon.
Pour sour cream and mushroom soup, mixed together, over the chicken.
Bake, uncovered, in casserole dish at 275° for 3 hours.
Serve with rice.

title: homemade eggrolls
directions: Mix in large bowl.
Spoon mixture onto eggroll wrap.
Flour about 2 or three.
Put in deep fry oil until done medium brown at 350°.

title: green tomato relish
directions: After grinding vegetables, drain in large cloth bag for 2 or more hours.
Add sugar, vinegar and spices; cook 30 minutes.
Put in clean hot jars and seal.
This is good on dried beans.
(For red relish, use half ripe tomatoes.)

title: butterfinger cake
directions: Cook cake per mix directions.

title: chicken biscuit stew
directions: Heat oven to 375° in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Melt margarine.
Blend in flour, salt and pepper.
Add chicken broth and milk; cook, stirring until thickened.
Add chicken, onion, peas and carrots.
Simmer until bubbly.
Separate biscuits and arrange over chicken mixture.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Serves 5 to 6.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Grate potatoes and onion finely.
Put into bowl.
Stir in rest of ingredients.
Drop into 1/4-inch deep fat in skillet.
Brown; drain on paper towels.

title: cherry coconut macaroons
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto a well-greased baking sheet about 1-inch apart. Bake at 325° for 12 to 15 minutes or until delicately browned. Remove from oven immediately.

title: corn pudding
directions: Put corn into 2-quart casserole dish.
In small bowl, beat eggs and sugar; add salt and pepper.
Pour over corn.
Put pats of butter on top and sprinkle nutmeg, if desired.
Bake in 325° oven for 45 minutes.
Bake slowly or filling may curdle.
Makes wonderful rich vegetable dish.

title: hot pepper jelly
directions: Grind together all peppers only.

title: rum cake
directions: Before you start, sample the rum for quality, good, isn't it? Select a large mixing bowl.
Take out measuring cup, spoons, etc. Sample rum again for quality.
It must be just right.
With a large mixer beat 1 cup butter in a large fluffy bowl.
Add one teaspoon sugar and beat agin.
Meanwhile check rum again.
Add 2 large eggs, 2 cups fruit and beat until high.
If fruit get stuck in beaters, pry loose with screwdriver.
Sample rum again, check for consistency.
Next sift in three cups baking powder and a pinch of rum, 1 teaspoon soda and a cup pepper and salt.
Fold in chopped buttermilk and strained nuts.
Tample rum again.
Add 1 bablespoon brown sugar or whatever color is available.
Mix well.
Grease oven.
Heat pan to 350°.
Pour whole mess in oven.
Take rum out in mifty finutes.
Serves 0.

title: cheesy green pasta
directions: Drain beans, reserving 1/2 cup liquid.
Combine the beans liquid with the remaining ingredients.
Heat through.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Mix
together
and
pour into oblong pan.
Bake at 350° until done (35 to 40 minutes).

title: frozen snickers
directions: Crush graham crackers into fine crumbs and place in an 8 X 8 baking dish.
Mix all other ingredients together.
Pour into dish, being careful not to disturb crumbs.
Freeze until firm.
Remove from freezer 10 minutes before serving.
Cut into 8 equal portions.

title: meatball vegetable medley
directions: Mix ground beef, onion soup mix, egg, milk and bread (cubed) together.
Shape into meatballs.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until done.

In a large electric skillet, put frozen corn on one side, meatballs in the middle and frozen green beans on other side. Pour cream of mushroom soup mixed with milk over the top of each. Cook at 325° for 30 minutes or until corn and green beans are done. Stir occasionally.
Serve.

title: onion cheese bread
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Saute onion in Crisco until golden.
Mix egg and milk; blend in Bisquick.
Add onion and 1/2 cheese. Spread dough in greased 8 x 1 1/2-inch round glass baking dish. Sprinkle top with the other 1/2 cheese and poppy seed.
Sprinkle melted butter over that.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.
Serve hot. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: lemon icebox pie
directions: Mix milk, lemon juice and rind.
Stir until thick.
Add beaten egg yolks. Mix melted shortening with vanilla wafer crumbs and press firmly into pan.
Pour filling into pan and top with meringue.
Beat 2 egg whites very stiff.
Add 2 tablespoons of sugar.
Blend well.
Spread on pie. Place in oven until brown. Let cool and chill in refrigerator.

title: planters holiday nuts 'n' spice cookies
directions: Finely chop 1 1/2 cups nuts.
Combine flour, chopped nuts and baking powder; set aside.
In saucepan, heat sugar, molasses, water, allspice and cinnamon to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Stir in margarine until melted.
Blend in flour mixture.
Chill 1 hour. Divide dough into 4 equal pieces.
Roll each piece into 1/8-inch thickness.
With floured cookie cutters, cut out dough.
Place on ungreased baking sheets.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly browned.
Remove from baking sheets; cool.
Frost with sugar glaze and decorate with remaining nuts, sprinkles and candies.
Makes about 6 dozen.

title: quick and easy skillet
directions: Saute onion in oleo and add to browned meat in skillet.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and simmer for 18 minutes.
Yield: 8 servings.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Trim broccoli; pare stems. Separate flowerets; cut stems into 1/2-inch slices. Cut potato on 1/2-inch cubes. Saut onion and garlic in butter in a kettle or Dutch oven until tender, about 3 minutes. Add curry powder, chicken broth, water and salt to kettle. Bring to boil; add broccoli and potato. Return to boiling; lower heat. Cover; simmer 20 minutes or until broccoli and potato are tender. Puree mixture, part at a time in container of electric blender. Reheat mixture in a large saucepan over low heat. Stir in half and half until piping hot. Taste; add additional seasoning, if needed. Garnish with sour cream.

title: vanilla slice and bake cookies
directions: Cream butter; gradually add sugar, mix well (use mixer).
Add egg and vanilla; beat well.
Combine flour, soda and salt; add to creamed mixture, beat well.
Stir in pecans.
Shape dough into two 12-inch rolls, wrap in wax paper, chill or freeze at least 2 hours.
Unwrap rolls, and cut into 1/4-inch slices; place in ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool on rack.
Yields 7 dozen.

title: cheesy brussel sprouts
directions: Cook Brussel sprouts according to package directions.
Immerse into cold water to stop cooking.
Slice each Brussel sprout in quarters lengthwise.
Toss with melted butter and season with salt and pepper.
Pour into shallow baking pan and spread to single layer.
Sprinkle with cheese and broil until cheese is melted and bubbly.

title: pineapple bread pudding
directions: Cream butter and sugar, beat in eggs one at a time.
Add rest of ingredients, then fold in bread.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes in a round casserole that has been greased with butter.
Cook uncovered.

title: funnel cakes
directions: In a small bowl with a wire whisk, beat eggs until frothy. Gradually beat in milk.
Add flour, sugar, baking powder and salt. Beat until smooth.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown meat in oil until pink color disappears.
Crumble with fork.
Stir in tomatoes, tomato juice, prego, soup mix and grape jelly.
Cook, stirring often for 15-20 minutes until jelly melts and sauce is hot.

title: bread pudding
directions: Brown sausage.
Grate cheese.
Cut bread into 1/2 inch cubes. Put bread in 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Cover with sausage and remaining bread.
Melt butter and brush top of bread.
Sprinkle remaining cheese on top.
Combine milk, eggs, salt and pepper. Pour over other ingredients.
Set baking dish in pan.
Add warm water to halfway up side.
Bake until set, approximately 50 minutes at 325°.

title: sausage rice casserole
directions: Crumble sausage and brown; drain grease and add vegetables. Cook until tender.
Add almonds, saving some for garnish.
In another pan, combine soup, water and rice.
Simmer for 20 minutes. Add salt and margarine; stir well.
Combine all in a greased 3-qt. dish.
Sprinkle reserved almonds on top and bake, uncovered, at 350 degrees for 1 hour.

title: applesauce
directions: Wash, peel and cut the core out of the apples.
Add water and salt.
Cook in a covered pot until the apples are soft.
Put in sugar while the apples are still hot.
Let it simmer in a pan until the sugar is all melted.
Add cinnamon for taste.
Serves 8.

title: spinach roll-ups
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cook noodles and allow to cool in bowl of cool water.
Saute onion in 2 tablespoons butter until tender. Combine spinach (squeeze out all water), onions, Mozzarella, sour cream and egg; set aside.
Melt 1/4 cup butter in saucepan; stir in flour, bouillon and pepper.
Stir in milk and half and half. Boil and stir until thick.
Remove noodles from water and pat dry with paper towels.
Spread spinach mixture over each noodle and roll up jelly-roll fashion.
Spread a small amount of sauce on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place rolls in dish.
Spoon remaining sauce over roll-ups.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes until hot and bubbly.

title: pineapple souffle
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs.
Add pineapple and bread. Put in buttered casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: graham cracker pralines
directions: Spray pan with Pam and line with graham crackers.
Sprinkle chopped nuts on top of crackers.
Boil oleo, butter
and sugar for 2 minutes; pour over graham crackers.
Bake 12 minutes at 320°.

title: quick salad
directions: Mix cottage cheese and jello.
Drain oranges and add.
Stir in Cool Whip.
Chill.

title: brownie cheesecake bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
In mixer bowl, beat flour, sugar, melted butter, cocoa, 2 eggs, milk, 2 teaspoons vanilla and baking powder until well blended.
Spread into pan.
In small mixer bowl, beat cream cheese, 2 tablespoons butter and cornstarch until fluffy.
Gradually add sweetened condensed milk, then remaining 1 egg and 1 teaspoon vanilla beating until smooth.
Pour over brownie batter.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes or until top is lightly browned.
Cool.
Refrigerate and cut into bars.
Store covered in refrigerator.

title: chili dip
directions: Soften cream cheese. Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Cover with the chili. Slice the cheese in thin slices and place on top.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until bubbly. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Pack
raw fish in pint jars (no need to worry about the bones as they will come all apart after pressure cooked).
Add 1 teaspoon
salt
on	top
of firmly packed jars.
Cover with water. Seal
with
canning top and process for 1 1/2 hours at 15	pounds pressure.	Cool
well after processing is finished and
store like
any other canned goods.
Very good if cooked like
hush puppies
and served while hot, always.
Quart jars require	2 hours
of
processing
at 15 pounds pressure.
For spicy catfish, add 1 pod of dried hot pepper.

title: cheddar-egg stuffed biscuit
directions: Make biscuits.
Cook onion, green pepper and egg.
Mix bacon bits into egg mixture.
Remove from heat when cooked; set aside. Carefully separate baked biscuits into 2 layers.
Sprinkle cheese into center of biscuits and top with egg mixture.
Heat again in microwave or toaster oven for 2 to 3 minutes.

title: chinese almond cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Make cookies into small balls and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Place whole almond on top of each cookie; press down to flatten.
Bake for 15 to 18 minutes.
Makes about 4 1/2 dozen.

title: clam chowder
directions: Pare potatoes and cook in boiling water with salt until tender, about 10 to 15 minutes.
Drain and cut into bite-size cubes.
In large frypan, cook bacon until crisp.
Remove from pan and chop into small pieces.
Cook onion in bacon drippings until clear.
Add clams with broth and simmer 5 minutes.

title: taco dip
directions: Layer in a loaf pan and chill.
Serve with Tostitos.
This can also be served as a main dish.

title: traditional scripture cake
directions: Heat oven to 300°.
Grease and flour 10-inch tube pan.
Mix 1 1/2 cups flour, baking powder, spices and salt in medium bowl. Beat sugar, margarine and honey in large bowl with electric mixer on medium speed until light and fluffy.
Add egg yolks, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add flour mixture alternately with milk, beating after each addition until smooth.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix ingredients in medium saucepan.
Simmer until bubbling. Place in 2 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Add 3 strips of bacon on top.
Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.

title: seven-up salad
directions: Put Seven-Up in pot. Add marshmallows. Cook over low heat until mixture comes to a boil and marshmallows are well melted. Set off heat. Add jello and mix well.
Put in refrigerator.
Keep check on mixture and stir occasionally.
When mixture is cold and about ready to set, add pineapple, nuts, cherries and whipped cream last.
Mix well.
Let salad set for several hours.

title: mahogany chiffon cake
directions: Combine boiling water and cocoa powder; cool. Combine flour, sugar, soda and salt in a large bowl. Make a well in middle; add egg yolks, oil and vanilla. Beat until smooth; beat in cocoa mixture. Beat egg whites and cream of tartar very stiff. Fold gently into batter just until blended.

Bake in ungreased angel food cake pan at 325° for 60 to 70 minutes. Hang on funnel or bottle until cold (like angel food cake). Glaze or ice as desired. Good for birthday cakes. Cut with serrated knife with a sawing motion.

title: german apple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and spread in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes. Cool cake.

title: white fudge
directions: In
large saucepan, combine first 5 ingredients.
Bring to a boil
slowly,
stirring
until sugar is dissolved.	Boil without stirring over medium heat to 236° on a candy thermometer.
Remove from heat and let stand 15 minutes.
Do not stir. Add vanilla. Stir
with	wooden spoon until mixture starts to lose its gloss, about
minutes.	Stir in cherries and walnuts.
Pour
into buttered
shallow pan.
Cool; then cut into squares.

title: spiced peaches
directions: Add syrup drained off the peaches to the hot mixture of sugar, vinegar, cloves and cinnamon stick which has been allowed to simmer a few minutes.
Pour mixture over peach halves and allow 48 hours before serving.
One clove can be stuck in center of each peach half.
Looks pretty for serving.

title: mostaccioli
directions: Cook noodles in water; drain.
Brown hamburger; drain.
Mix spaghetti sauce with hamburger.
In a 9 x 13-inch baking dish, put in half of the noodles.
Cover with half of sauce mixture.
Top with slices of Velveeta cheese and Parmesan cheese.
Repeat.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix first 3 ingredients and pour in 2-quart casserole dish.
Top with fruit and dot with butter.
Cook until top is brown.

title: cheesy layered salad
directions: Put a layer of lettuce in 2 1/2-quart bowl.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper and 1 tablespoon of the sugar.

title: lentils with rice
directions: Put water and lentils in medium-sized pot.
Bring to boil. Cover and cook over medium heat for 20 minutes.
Slice onions. Heat oil in skillet and add onions.
Stir until golden brown.
Add rice, salt and pepper to lentils and water and cook until rice is done, approximately 20 minutes.
Add oil and onions.
Cook for 5 minutes.
Can be eaten warm or cold.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Prepare and bake cake mix according to package directions. Cool completely.
Prepare pudding mix according to directions. Crumble half of cake into bottom of a large bowl (a small punch bowl works well).
Top with layers of the pudding, pineapple, cherry pie filling, whipped topping and nuts.
If desired, reserve a few cherries from second can of cherry pie filling for garnish. Repeat layers, using the remaining cake, pudding, pineapple, cherry pie filling and nuts.
Top with remaining whipped topping.
Garnish with reserved cherries, if desired.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Beat eggs; add to butter and sugar mixture.
Sift flour, soda and salt, then stir with fork. Add bananas (pulp).
Stir in pecans (chopped).
Bake in 2 greased loaf pans (5 x 9-inch) for 50 minutes at 350°.

title: reese's peanut butter candy
directions: Mix together crushed graham crackers, butter, peanut butter and sugar and spread in buttered cake pan.
Melt chocolate chips and pour over peanut butter mixture.
Chill.
Let set 15 minutes before cutting into bars.

title: sweet-hot cocktail meatballs
directions: In large bowl, combine egg, crumbs, milk, onion, garlic, salt and pepper.
Add beef; mix well.
Shape into 1-inch meatballs and place in oblong baking dish.
Bake in 350° oven for 15 to 18 minutes or until done.
Drain.
Combine picante and cranberry sauces in large saucepan over medium heat until smooth.
Add meatballs and simmer.
Can place in crock-pot to keep warm.

title: salsa stovall chicken enchiladas
directions: Boil chicken and season with salt, pepper, poultry seasoning, onion and garlic.
Shred meat and let cool.
Spray a saucepan with Pam.
Heat and saute one seeded jalapeno pepper, onion and a little chopped cilantro.
Add one can of enchilada sauce, chicken and chili powder to taste.
Cook 5 minutes.

title: original toll house cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Sift together flour, baking soda and salt; set aside.
Combine butter, brown sugar, granulated sugar, vanilla and water; beat until creamy.
Add egg and flour mixture, mixing well.
Stir in chocolate morsels and chopped nuts.
Drop by teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 20 minutes.

title: summer pasta salad
directions: Prepare pasta as directed on package. Drain.
Mix tuna, hard-boiled eggs, pimientos and olives into pasta.

title: scampi primavera
directions: Cook spaghetti as directed on package.
Meanwhile, heat oil in large skillet.
Cook and stir garlic with lemon peel and/or a little lemon juice about 30 seconds.
Add vegetables and shrimp and cook and stir over medium heat until shrimp turn pink, about 3 to 4 minutes.
Sprinkle with lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Stir in basil and parsley.
Serve over spaghetti.
Makes 8 servings.

title: mississippi corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into ungreased 9 x 9-inch pan. Cook 25 minutes at 375°.

title: homemade biscuit mix(this recipe makes homemade biscuits easy!)
directions: Sift dry ingredients together twice.
Cut in shortening until mixture resembles coarse cornmeal.
Store at room temperature in a covered container.

title: cream puff delight
directions: Place butter, water and salt in heavy saucepan and heat.
When boiling, add flour all at once, stirring vigorously over low heat until mixture leaves sides of pan in smooth mass.
Remove from heat.
Beat in eggs one at a time.
Beat until smooth.
Drop by tablespoon on greased baking sheet about 2 inches apart.
Have batter a little high in center.
Bake at 450° for 20 minutes, then reduce heat to 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool.

title: pork steak and bean bake
directions: In a skillet, brown steaks on both sides, then remove from pan and add 1/2 teaspoon salt, ketchup, brown sugar and vinegar to pan drippings.
Stir together.
Add pork and beans, lima beans and kidney beans.
Place bean mixture into a baking pan or dish and lay pork steaks on top.
Add the teaspoon of salt on top of the steaks.
Cover tightly and bake in oven for 1 hour at 325°. Remove cover and bake an additional 15 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: seafood casserole
directions: Cook rice and set aside.
Saute green pepper, onion and celery until soft; add mushrooms and saute.
Mix all together with seafood.
Add mayonnaise, rice and curry powder.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Top with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Cook vegetables in boiling water just until tender (do not overcook).
Drain well.

title: baked chicken croquettes
directions: Mix chicken and bread crumbs, salt and pepper to taste.
Boil milk and butter together; pour slowly over beaten egg.
Put back on heat and stir until thickness of cream.
Pour over chicken while hot; mold into croquettes and roll in cracker dust.
When cold, brush with melted butter.
Put in greased pan and bake until brown.

title: spanish rice
directions: Melt shortening in iron frying pan.
Add rice and stir until golden brown.
Remove from heat.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Cover and simmer over low heat for 30 minutes or until rice is tender and has absorbed water and juices.
Keep tightly covered until ready to serve.

title: baked chicken rolls with cheese
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Lightly grease small baking sheet. Place chicken breasts between sheets of waxed paper and pound to 1/4-inch thickness, using mallet or rolling pin.
Season chicken with salt and pepper.
Combine crumbs, Romano cheese, paprika and thyme in shallow dish.
Place one cheese stick in at short end of each chicken breast.
Roll up chicken, enclosing cheese.
Brush chicken rolls with olive oil; dip in bread crumb mixture.

title: salad delight
directions: Mix and refrigerate.
May be frozen up to one year.

title: seafood neapolitan
directions: Melt margarine and saute scallops, shrimp, onions and garlic. Stir in Hollandaise Sauce that has been made according to directions on package.
Add wine and stir.
Stir in pasta and serve.

title: cheese balls
directions: Blend together with equal parts or cream and mayonnaise. Chill.
Form into small oblong rolls (size of a peanut).
Roll in crushed or chopped nuts.
Store in refrigerator until time to service.
Nice with crackers.

title: butterfinger cake
directions: Make cake as on box in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool.
Poke holes with a knife in cake.
Pour butterscotch topping and evaporated milk on top.
Let sit in refrigerator 2 to 3 hours.
Spread whipped cream.
Top with chopped Butterfinger bars.

title: crunch crowned brownie bars
directions: Prepare brownie mix as directed for cake-like brownies. Spread in greased 15 x 10 1/2-inch jelly roll pan.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Combine and toss broccoli, nuts, raisins, apples, and grapes. Pour dressing over salad.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Mix chicken, sour cream, chicken soup, Jack cheese, Colby cheese, chilies, onion and pepper together in mixing bowl. Place 3/4 cup of mixture on each tortilla. Roll up and place seam side down in 2-quart oblong glass baking dish. Sprinkle 1/2 cup Colby cheese on top. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes just until heated through well and cheese is bubbly. Yields 6 servings.

title: dried apple pie
directions: Soak for 1 hour the apples and warm water.
Cook apples in warm water until soft.
Then add sugar and cinnamon.

title: butterscotch bars
directions: Melt margarine.
Add brown sugar and mix well.
Add eggs and vanilla and mix well.
Mix in dry ingredients.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool and cut into bars.

title: fruit salad
directions: Cut all fruits into small pieces.
Any fresh fruit can be used.
Mix fruit together in a large bowl.
Add coconut and nuts; mix.
Fold in Cool Whip and marshmallows.
Let chill.

title: lemon bars
directions: Mix well.
Press in pan (9 x 13-inch) greased.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook frozen broccoli according to package directions.
Cook rice.
Combine broccoli, rice, Cheez Whiz and celery soup (do not add water).
Mix well.
